48 // Return the evaluation of {condition} if {ValidationTag::validate} is true,
49 // DCHECK that it is true and always return true otherwise.
50 // Note that this needs to be a macro, because the "likely" annotation does not
51 // survive inlining.
52 #ifdef DEBUG
53 #define VALIDATE(condition) \
54  (ValidationTag::validate ? V8_LIKELY(condition) \
55  : ValidateAssumeTrue(condition, #condition))
56 
57 V8_INLINE bool ValidateAssumeTrue(bool condition, const char* message) {
58  DCHECK_WITH_MSG(condition, message);
59  return true;
60 }
61 #else
62 #define VALIDATE(condition) (!ValidationTag::validate || V8_LIKELY(condition))
63 #endif
64 
65 #define CHECK_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(feat) \
66  DCHECK(this->module_->origin == kWasmOrigin); \
67  if (!VALIDATE(this->enabled_.has_##feat())) { \
68  this->DecodeError( \
69  "Invalid opcode 0x%02x (enable with --experimental-wasm-" #feat ")", \
70  opcode); \
71  return 0; \
72  } \
73  this->detected_->add_##feat()

75 static constexpr LoadType GetLoadType(WasmOpcode opcode) {
76  // Hard-code the list of load types. The opcodes are highly unlikely to
77  // ever change, and we have some checks here to guard against that.
78  static_assert(sizeof(LoadType) == sizeof(uint8_t), "LoadType is compact");
79  constexpr uint8_t kMinOpcode = kExprI32LoadMem;
80  constexpr uint8_t kMaxOpcode = kExprI64LoadMem32U;
81  constexpr LoadType kLoadTypes[] = {
82  LoadType::kI32Load, LoadType::kI64Load, LoadType::kF32Load,
83  LoadType::kF64Load, LoadType::kI32Load8S, LoadType::kI32Load8U,
84  LoadType::kI32Load16S, LoadType::kI32Load16U, LoadType::kI64Load8S,
85  LoadType::kI64Load8U, LoadType::kI64Load16S, LoadType::kI64Load16U,
86  LoadType::kI64Load32S, LoadType::kI64Load32U};
87  static_assert(arraysize(kLoadTypes) == kMaxOpcode - kMinOpcode + 1);
88  DCHECK_LE(kMinOpcode, opcode);
89  DCHECK_GE(kMaxOpcode, opcode);
90  return kLoadTypes[opcode - kMinOpcode];
91 }
92 
93 static constexpr StoreType GetStoreType(WasmOpcode opcode) {
94  // Hard-code the list of store types. The opcodes are highly unlikely to
95  // ever change, and we have some checks here to guard against that.
96  static_assert(sizeof(StoreType) == sizeof(uint8_t), "StoreType is compact");
97  constexpr uint8_t kMinOpcode = kExprI32StoreMem;
98  constexpr uint8_t kMaxOpcode = kExprI64StoreMem32;
99  constexpr StoreType kStoreTypes[] = {
100  StoreType::kI32Store, StoreType::kI64Store, StoreType::kF32Store,
101  StoreType::kF64Store, StoreType::kI32Store8, StoreType::kI32Store16,
102  StoreType::kI64Store8, StoreType::kI64Store16, StoreType::kI64Store32};
103  static_assert(arraysize(kStoreTypes) == kMaxOpcode - kMinOpcode + 1);
104  DCHECK_LE(kMinOpcode, opcode);
105  DCHECK_GE(kMaxOpcode, opcode);
106  return kStoreTypes[opcode - kMinOpcode];
107 }

179 // Decoder error with explicit PC and optional format arguments.
180 // Depending on the validation tag and the number of arguments, this forwards to
181 // a V8_NOINLINE and V8_PRESERVE_MOST method of the decoder.
182 template <typename ValidationTag, typename... Args>
183 V8_INLINE void DecodeError(Decoder* decoder, const uint8_t* pc, const char* str,
184  Args&&... args) {
185  // Decode errors can only happen if we are validating; the compiler should
186  // know this e.g. from the VALIDATE macro, but this assumption tells it again
187  // that this path is impossible.
188  V8_ASSUME(ValidationTag::validate);
189  if constexpr (sizeof...(Args) == 0) {
190  decoder->error(pc, str);
191  } else {
192  decoder->errorf(pc, str, std::forward<Args>(args)...);
193  }
194 }
195 
196 // Decoder error without explicit PC and with optional format arguments.
197 // Depending on the validation tag and the number of arguments, this forwards to
198 // a V8_NOINLINE and V8_PRESERVE_MOST method of the decoder.
199 template <typename ValidationTag, typename... Args>
200 V8_INLINE void DecodeError(Decoder* decoder, const char* str, Args&&... args) {
201  // Decode errors can only happen if we are validating; the compiler should
202  // know this e.g. from the VALIDATE macro, but this assumption tells it again
203  // that this path is impossible.
204  V8_ASSUME(ValidationTag::validate);
205  if constexpr (sizeof...(Args) == 0) {
206  decoder->error(str);
207  } else {
208  decoder->errorf(str, std::forward<Args>(args)...);
209  }
210 }

214 template <typename ValidationTag>
215 std::pair<HeapType, uint32_t> read_heap_type(Decoder* decoder,
216  const uint8_t* pc,
217  WasmEnabledFeatures enabled,
218  WasmDetectedFeatures* detected) {
219  auto [heap_index, length] =
220  decoder->read_i33v<ValidationTag>(pc, "heap type");
221  Exactness exactness = Exactness::kAnySubtype;
222  uint32_t type_index;
223  if (heap_index < 0) {
224  int64_t min_1_byte_leb128 = -64;
225  if (!VALIDATE(heap_index >= min_1_byte_leb128)) {
226  DecodeError<ValidationTag>(decoder, pc, "Unknown heap type %" PRId64,
227  heap_index);
228  return {kWasmBottom, length};
229  }
230  uint8_t uint_7_mask = 0x7F;
231  uint8_t code = static_cast<ValueTypeCode>(heap_index) & uint_7_mask;
232  bool is_shared = false;
233  if (code == kSharedFlagCode) {
234  if (!VALIDATE(enabled.has_shared())) {
235  DecodeError<ValidationTag>(
236  decoder, pc,
237  "invalid heap type 0x%hhx, enable with --experimental-wasm-shared",
238  kSharedFlagCode);
239  return {kWasmBottom, length};
240  }
241  code = decoder->read_u8<ValidationTag>(pc + length, "heap type");
242  length++;
243  is_shared = true;
244  }
245  switch (code) {
246  case kNoFuncCode:
247  case kFuncRefCode:
248  if (!VALIDATE(!is_shared)) {
249  DecodeError<ValidationTag>(
250  decoder, pc,
251  "invalid heap type '%s', shared function references are not "
252  "supported",
253  HeapType::from_code(code, is_shared).name().c_str());
254  return {kWasmBottom, 0};
255  }
256  [[fallthrough]];
257  case kEqRefCode:
258  case kI31RefCode:
259  case kStructRefCode:
260  case kArrayRefCode:
261  case kAnyRefCode:
262  case kNoneCode:
263  case kNoExternCode:
264  case kExternRefCode:
265  return {HeapType::from_code(code, is_shared), length};
266  case kNoExnCode:
267  case kExnRefCode:
268  if (!VALIDATE(enabled.has_exnref())) {
269  DecodeError<ValidationTag>(
270  decoder, pc,
271  "invalid heap type '%s', enable with --experimental-wasm-exnref",
272  HeapType::from_code(code, is_shared).name().c_str());
273  return {kWasmBottom, 0};
274  }
275  if (!VALIDATE(!detected->has_legacy_eh() ||
276  v8_flags.wasm_allow_mixed_eh_for_testing)) {
277  DecodeError<ValidationTag>(
278  decoder, pc,
279  "module uses a mix of legacy and new exception handling "
280  "instructions");
281  return {kWasmBottom, 0};
282  }
283  if (!VALIDATE(!is_shared)) {
284  DecodeError<ValidationTag>(
285  decoder, pc,
286  "invalid heap type '%s', shared exception references are not "
287  "supported",
288  HeapType::from_code(code, is_shared).name().c_str());
289  return {kWasmBottom, 0};
290  }
291  detected->add_exnref();
292  return {HeapType::from_code(code, is_shared), length};
293  case kStringRefCode:
294  case kStringViewWtf8Code:
295  case kStringViewWtf16Code:
296  case kStringViewIterCode:
297  if (!VALIDATE(enabled.has_stringref())) {
298  DecodeError<ValidationTag>(
299  decoder, pc,
300  "invalid heap type '%s', enable with "
301  "--experimental-wasm-stringref",
302  HeapType::from_code(code, is_shared).name().c_str());
303  return {kWasmBottom, 0};
304  }
305  return {HeapType::from_code(code, is_shared), length};
306  case kNoContCode:
307  case kContRefCode:
308  if (!VALIDATE(enabled.has_wasmfx())) {
309  DecodeError<ValidationTag>(
310  decoder, pc,
311  "invalid heap type '%s', enable with "
312  "--experimental-wasm-wasmfx",
313  HeapType::from_code(code, is_shared).name().c_str());
314  return {kWasmBottom, 0};
315  }
316  if (!VALIDATE(!is_shared)) {
317  DecodeError<ValidationTag>(
318  decoder, pc,
319  "invalid heap type '%s', shared continuation references are not "
320  "supported",
321  HeapType::from_code(code, is_shared).name().c_str());
322  return {kWasmBottom, 0};
323  }
324  return {HeapType::from_code(code, is_shared), length};
325  case kExactCode: {
326  if (!VALIDATE(enabled.has_custom_descriptors())) {
327  DecodeError<ValidationTag>(decoder, pc,
328  "invalid heap type 'exact', enable with "
329  "--experimental-wasm-custom-descriptors");
330  return {kWasmBottom, 0};
331  }
332  auto [nested_index, index_length] =
333  decoder->read_u32v<ValidationTag>(pc + 1, "type index");
334  type_index = nested_index;
335  exactness = Exactness::kExact;
336  length += index_length;
337  break;
338  }
339  default:
340  DecodeError<ValidationTag>(decoder, pc, "Unknown heap type %" PRId64,
341  heap_index);
342  return {kWasmBottom, length};
343  }
344  } else {
345  type_index = static_cast<uint32_t>(heap_index);
346  }
347  if (!VALIDATE(type_index < kV8MaxWasmTypes)) {
348  DecodeError<ValidationTag>(
349  decoder, pc,
350  "Type index %u is greater than the maximum number %zu "
351  "of type definitions supported by V8",
352  type_index, kV8MaxWasmTypes);
353  return {kWasmBottom, length};
354  }
355  // We don't have a module yet, so we can only fill in default values:
356  bool kDefaultShared = false;
357  RefTypeKind kDefaultKind = RefTypeKind::kOther;
358  return {HeapType::Index(ModuleTypeIndex{type_index}, kDefaultShared,
359  kDefaultKind, exactness),
360  length};
361 }
362 
363 // Read a value type starting at address {pc} using {decoder}.
364 // No bytes are consumed.
365 // Returns the read value type and the number of bytes read (a.k.a. length).
366 template <typename ValidationTag>
367 std::pair<ValueType, uint32_t> read_value_type(Decoder* decoder,
368  const uint8_t* pc,
369  WasmEnabledFeatures enabled,
370  WasmDetectedFeatures* detected) {
371  uint8_t val = decoder->read_u8<ValidationTag>(pc, "value type opcode");
372  if (!VALIDATE(decoder->ok())) {
373  return {kWasmBottom, 0};
374  }
375  ValueTypeCode code = static_cast<ValueTypeCode>(val);
376  switch (code) {
377  case kEqRefCode:
378  case kI31RefCode:
379  case kStructRefCode:
380  case kArrayRefCode:
381  case kAnyRefCode:
382  case kNoneCode:
383  case kNoExternCode:
384  case kNoFuncCode:
385  case kExternRefCode:
386  case kFuncRefCode:
387  return {ValueType::RefNull(HeapType::from_code(code, false)), 1};
388  case kNoExnCode:
389  case kExnRefCode:
390  if (!VALIDATE(enabled.has_exnref())) {
391  DecodeError<ValidationTag>(
392  decoder, pc,
393  "invalid value type '%s', enable with --experimental-wasm-exnref",
394  HeapType::from_code(code, false).name().c_str());
395  return {kWasmBottom, 0};
396  }
397  if (!VALIDATE(!detected->has_legacy_eh() ||
398  v8_flags.wasm_allow_mixed_eh_for_testing)) {
399  DecodeError<ValidationTag>(
400  decoder, pc,
401  "module uses a mix of legacy and new exception handling "
402  "instructions");
403  return {kWasmBottom, 0};
404  }
405  detected->add_exnref();
406  return {code == kExnRefCode ? kWasmExnRef : kWasmNullExnRef, 1};
407  case kStringRefCode:
408  case kStringViewWtf8Code:
409  case kStringViewWtf16Code:
410  case kStringViewIterCode: {
411  if (!VALIDATE(enabled.has_stringref())) {
412  DecodeError<ValidationTag>(
413  decoder, pc,
414  "invalid value type '%sref', enable with "
415  "--experimental-wasm-stringref",
416  HeapType::from_code(code, false).name().c_str());
417  return {kWasmBottom, 0};
418  }
419  // String views are not nullable, so interpret the shorthand accordingly.
420  ValueType type = code == kStringRefCode
421  ? kWasmStringRef
422  : ValueType::Ref(HeapType::from_code(code, false));
423  return {type, 1};
424  }
425  case kContRefCode:
426  case kNoContCode:
427  if (!VALIDATE(enabled.has_wasmfx())) {
428  DecodeError<ValidationTag>(
429  decoder, pc,
430  "invalid value type '%s', enable with --experimental-wasm-wasmfx",
431  HeapType::from_code(code, false).name().c_str());
432  return {kWasmBottom, 0};
433  }
434  return {code == kContRefCode ? kWasmContRef : kWasmNullContRef, 1};
435  case kI32Code:
436  return {kWasmI32, 1};
437  case kI64Code:
438  return {kWasmI64, 1};
439  case kF32Code:
440  return {kWasmF32, 1};
441  case kF64Code:
442  return {kWasmF64, 1};
443  case kRefCode:
444  case kRefNullCode: {
445  Nullability nullability = code == kRefNullCode ? kNullable : kNonNullable;
446  auto [heap_type, length] =
447  read_heap_type<ValidationTag>(decoder, pc + 1, enabled, detected);
448  if (!VALIDATE(!heap_type.is_string_view() ||
449  nullability == kNonNullable)) {
450  DecodeError<ValidationTag>(decoder, pc,
451  "nullable string views don't exist");
452  return {kWasmBottom, 0};
453  }
454  ValueType type = heap_type.is_bottom()
455  ? kWasmBottom
456  : ValueType::RefMaybeNull(heap_type, nullability);
457  return {type, length + 1};
458  }
459  case kS128Code: {
460  if (!VALIDATE(CheckHardwareSupportsSimd())) {
461  if (v8_flags.correctness_fuzzer_suppressions) {
462  FATAL("Aborting on missing Wasm SIMD support");
463  }
464  DecodeError<ValidationTag>(decoder, pc, "Wasm SIMD unsupported");
465  return {kWasmBottom, 0};
466  }
467  return {kWasmS128, 1};
468  }
469  // Although these codes are included in ValueTypeCode, they technically
470  // do not correspond to value types and are only used in specific
471  // contexts. The caller of this function is responsible for handling them.
472  case kVoidCode:
473  case kI8Code:
474  case kI16Code:
475  case kF16Code:
476  case kExactCode:
477  // Fall through to the error reporting below.
478  break;
479  }
480  // Anything that doesn't match an enumeration value is an invalid type code.
481  if constexpr (!ValidationTag::validate) UNREACHABLE();
482  DecodeError<ValidationTag>(decoder, pc, "invalid value type 0x%hhx", code);
483  return {kWasmBottom, 0};
484 }
485 
486 template <typename ValidationTag>
487 bool ValidateHeapType(Decoder* decoder, const uint8_t* pc,
488  const WasmModule* module, HeapType type) {
489  if (!VALIDATE(!type.is_bottom())) return false;
490  if (!type.is_index()) return true;
491  // A {nullptr} module is accepted if we are not validating anyway (e.g. for
492  // opcode length computation).
493  if (!ValidationTag::validate && module == nullptr) return true;
494  if (!VALIDATE(type.ref_index().index < module->types.size())) {
495  DecodeError<ValidationTag>(decoder, pc, "Type index %u is out of bounds",
496  type.ref_index().index);
497  return false;
498  }
499  return true;
500 }
501 
502 template <typename ValidationTag>
503 bool ValidateValueType(Decoder* decoder, const uint8_t* pc,
504  const WasmModule* module, ValueType type) {
505  if (!VALIDATE(!type.is_bottom())) return false;
506  if (V8_LIKELY(!type.is_object_reference())) return true;
507  return ValidateHeapType<ValidationTag>(decoder, pc, module, type.heap_type());
508 }
509 
510 // Updates {unfinished_type} in-place using information from {module}.
511 static void Populate(HeapType* unfinished_type, const WasmModule* module) {
512  if (!unfinished_type->has_index()) return;
513  DCHECK(module->has_type(unfinished_type->ref_index()));
514  const TypeDefinition& type_def = module->type(unfinished_type->ref_index());
515  unfinished_type->Populate(type_def.is_shared,
516  static_cast<RefTypeKind>(type_def.kind));
517 }
518 
519 // Updates {unfinished_type} in-place using information from {module}.
520 static void Populate(ValueType* unfinished_type, const WasmModule* module) {
521  if (!unfinished_type->has_index()) return;
522  DCHECK(module->has_type(unfinished_type->ref_index()));
523  const TypeDefinition& type_def = module->type(unfinished_type->ref_index());
524  unfinished_type->Populate(type_def.is_shared,
525  static_cast<RefTypeKind>(type_def.kind));
526 }

532 // Helpers for decoding different kinds of immediates which follow bytecodes.
533 struct ImmI32Immediate {
534  int32_t value;
535  uint32_t length;
536 
537  template <typename ValidationTag>
538  ImmI32Immediate(Decoder* decoder, const uint8_t* pc, ValidationTag = {}) {
539  std::tie(value, length) = decoder->read_i32v<ValidationTag>(pc, "immi32");
540  }
541 };

543 struct ImmI64Immediate {
544  int64_t value;
545  uint32_t length;
546 
547  template <typename ValidationTag>
548  ImmI64Immediate(Decoder* decoder, const uint8_t* pc, ValidationTag = {}) {
549  std::tie(value, length) = decoder->read_i64v<ValidationTag>(pc, "immi64");
550  }
551 };
552 
553 struct ImmF32Immediate {
554  float value;
555  uint32_t length = 4;
556 
557  template <typename ValidationTag>
558  ImmF32Immediate(Decoder* decoder, const uint8_t* pc, ValidationTag = {}) {
559  // We can't use base::bit_cast here because calling any helper function
560  // that returns a float would potentially flip NaN bits per C++ semantics,
561  // so we have to inline the memcpy call directly.
562  uint32_t tmp = decoder->read_u32<ValidationTag>(pc, "immf32");
563  memcpy(&value, &tmp, sizeof(value));
564  }
565 };
566 
567 struct ImmF64Immediate {
568  double value;
569  uint32_t length = 8;
570 
571  template <typename ValidationTag>
572  ImmF64Immediate(Decoder* decoder, const uint8_t* pc, ValidationTag = {}) {
573  // Avoid base::bit_cast because it might not preserve the signalling bit
574  // of a NaN.
575  uint64_t tmp = decoder->read_u64<ValidationTag>(pc, "immf64");
576  memcpy(&value, &tmp, sizeof(value));
577  }
578 };
579 
580 struct BrOnCastFlags {
581  enum Values {
582  SRC_IS_NULL = 1,
583  RES_IS_NULL = 1 << 1,
584  };
585 
586  bool src_is_null = false;
587  bool res_is_null = false;
588 
589  BrOnCastFlags() = default;
590  explicit BrOnCastFlags(uint8_t value)
591  : src_is_null((value & BrOnCastFlags::SRC_IS_NULL) != 0),
592  res_is_null((value & BrOnCastFlags::RES_IS_NULL) != 0) {
593  DCHECK_LE(value, BrOnCastFlags::SRC_IS_NULL | BrOnCastFlags::RES_IS_NULL);
594  }
595 };
596 
597 struct BrOnCastImmediate {
598  BrOnCastFlags flags;
599  uint8_t raw_value = 0;
600  uint32_t length = 1;
601 
602  template <typename ValidationTag>
603  BrOnCastImmediate(Decoder* decoder, const uint8_t* pc, ValidationTag = {}) {
604  raw_value = decoder->read_u8<ValidationTag>(pc, "br_on_cast flags");
605  if (raw_value > (BrOnCastFlags::SRC_IS_NULL | BrOnCastFlags::RES_IS_NULL)) {
606  decoder->errorf(pc, "invalid br_on_cast flags %u", raw_value);
607  return;
608  }
609  flags = BrOnCastFlags(raw_value);
610  }
611 };

740 struct SelectTypeImmediate {
741  uint32_t length;
742  ValueType type;
743 
744  template <typename ValidationTag>
745  SelectTypeImmediate(WasmEnabledFeatures enabled,
746  WasmDetectedFeatures* detected, Decoder* decoder,
747  const uint8_t* pc, ValidationTag = {}) {
748  uint8_t num_types;
749  std::tie(num_types, length) =
750  decoder->read_u32v<ValidationTag>(pc, "number of select types");
751  if (!VALIDATE(num_types == 1)) {
752  DecodeError<ValidationTag>(
753  decoder, pc,
754  "Invalid number of types. Select accepts exactly one type");
755  return;
756  }
757  uint32_t type_length;
758  std::tie(type, type_length) =
759  value_type_reader::read_value_type<ValidationTag>(decoder, pc + length,
760  enabled, detected);
761  length += type_length;
762  }
763 };

765 struct BlockTypeImmediate {
766  uint32_t length = 1;
767  // After decoding, either {sig_index} is set XOR {sig} points to
768  // {single_return_sig_storage}.
769  ModuleTypeIndex sig_index = ModuleTypeIndex::Invalid();
770  FunctionSig sig{0, 0, single_return_sig_storage};
771  // Internal field, potentially pointed to by {sig}. Do not access directly.
772  ValueType single_return_sig_storage[1];
773 
774  // Do not copy or move, as {sig} might point to {single_return_sig_storage} so
775  // this cannot trivially be copied. If needed, define those operators later.
776  BlockTypeImmediate(const BlockTypeImmediate&) = delete;
777  BlockTypeImmediate(BlockTypeImmediate&&) = delete;
778  BlockTypeImmediate& operator=(const BlockTypeImmediate&) = delete;
779  BlockTypeImmediate& operator=(BlockTypeImmediate&&) = delete;
780 
781  template <typename ValidationTag>
782  BlockTypeImmediate(WasmEnabledFeatures enabled,
783  WasmDetectedFeatures* detected, Decoder* decoder,
784  const uint8_t* pc, ValidationTag = {}) {
785  int64_t block_type;
786  std::tie(block_type, length) =
787  decoder->read_i33v<ValidationTag>(pc, "block type");
788  if (block_type < 0) {
789  // All valid negative types are 1 byte in length, so we check against the
790  // minimum 1-byte LEB128 value.
791  constexpr int64_t min_1_byte_leb128 = -64;
792  if (!VALIDATE(block_type >= min_1_byte_leb128)) {
793  DecodeError<ValidationTag>(decoder, pc, "invalid block type %" PRId64,
794  block_type);
795  return;
796  }
797  if (static_cast<ValueTypeCode>(block_type & 0x7F) != kVoidCode) {
798  sig = FunctionSig{1, 0, single_return_sig_storage};
799  std::tie(single_return_sig_storage[0], length) =
800  value_type_reader::read_value_type<ValidationTag>(
801  decoder, pc, enabled, detected);
802  }
803  } else {
804  sig = FunctionSig{0, 0, nullptr};
805  sig_index = ModuleTypeIndex{static_cast<uint32_t>(block_type)};
806  }
807  }
808 
809  uint32_t in_arity() const {
810  return static_cast<uint32_t>(sig.parameter_count());
811  }
812  uint32_t out_arity() const {
813  return static_cast<uint32_t>(sig.return_count());
814  }
815  ValueType in_type(uint32_t index) const { return sig.GetParam(index); }
816  ValueType out_type(uint32_t index) const { return sig.GetReturn(index); }
817 };
818

844 struct MemoryOrderImmediate {
845  AtomicMemoryOrder order;
846  static constexpr uint32_t length = 1;
847 
848  template <typename ValidationTag>
849  MemoryOrderImmediate(Decoder* decoder, const uint8_t* pc,
850  ValidationTag validate = {}) {
851  const uint8_t raw_order = decoder->read_u8<ValidationTag>(pc);
852  switch (raw_order) {
853  case 0:
854  order = AtomicMemoryOrder::kSeqCst;
855  break;
856  case 1:
857  order = AtomicMemoryOrder::kAcqRel;
858  break;
859  default:
860  // Store the decoded value. This way the disassembler can "restore" the
861  // original (invalid) value.
862  order = static_cast<AtomicMemoryOrder>(raw_order);
863  if (ValidationTag::validate) {
864  DecodeError<ValidationTag>(decoder, pc, "invalid memory ordering %u",
865  raw_order);
866  }
867  break;
868  }
869  }
870 };

886 struct BranchTableImmediate {
887  uint32_t table_count;
888  const uint8_t* start;
889  const uint8_t* table;

891  template <typename ValidationTag>
892  BranchTableImmediate(Decoder* decoder, const uint8_t* pc,
893  ValidationTag = {}) {
894  start = pc;
895  uint32_t len;
896  std::tie(table_count, len) =
897  decoder->read_u32v<ValidationTag>(pc, "table count");
898  table = pc + len;
899  }
900 };

904 // A helper to iterate over a branch table.
905 template <typename ValidationTag>
906 class BranchTableIterator {
907  public:
908  uint32_t cur_index() const { return index_; }
909  bool has_next() const {
910  return VALIDATE(decoder_->ok()) && index_ <= table_count_;
911  }
912  uint32_t next() {
913  DCHECK(has_next());
914  index_++;
915  auto [result, length] =
916  decoder_->read_u32v<ValidationTag>(pc_, "branch table entry");
917  pc_ += length;
918  return result;
919  }
920  // Length, including the length of the {BranchTableImmediate}, but not the
921  // opcode. Must be called after consuming the table entries.
922  uint32_t length() const {
923  DCHECK(!has_next());
924  return static_cast<uint32_t>(pc_ - start_);
925  }
926  const uint8_t* pc() const { return pc_; }
927 
928  BranchTableIterator(Decoder* decoder, const BranchTableImmediate& imm)
929  : decoder_(decoder),
930  start_(imm.start),
931  pc_(imm.table),
932  table_count_(imm.table_count) {}
933 
934  private:
935  Decoder* const decoder_;
936  const uint8_t* const start_;
937  const uint8_t* pc_;
938  uint32_t index_ = 0; // the current index.
939  const uint32_t table_count_; // the count of entries, not including default.
940 };

942 struct CatchCase {
943  CatchKind kind;
944  // The union contains a TagIndexImmediate iff kind == kCatch or kind ==
945  // kCatchRef.
946  union MaybeTagIndex {
947  uint8_t empty;
948  TagIndexImmediate tag_imm;
949  } maybe_tag;
950  BranchDepthImmediate br_imm;
951 };
952 
953 // A helper to iterate over a try table.
954 template <typename ValidationTag>
955 class TryTableIterator {
956  public:
957  uint32_t cur_index() const { return index_; }
958  bool has_next() const {
959  return VALIDATE(decoder_->ok()) && index_ < table_count_;
960  }
961 
962  CatchCase next() {
963  uint8_t kind =
964  static_cast<CatchKind>(decoder_->read_u8<ValidationTag>(pc_));
965  pc_ += 1;
966  CatchCase::MaybeTagIndex maybe_tag{0};
967  if (kind == kCatch || kind == kCatchRef) {
968  maybe_tag.tag_imm = TagIndexImmediate(decoder_, pc_, ValidationTag{});
969  pc_ += maybe_tag.tag_imm.length;
970  }
971  BranchDepthImmediate br_imm(decoder_, pc_, ValidationTag{});
972  pc_ += br_imm.length;
973  index_++;
974  return CatchCase{static_cast<CatchKind>(kind), maybe_tag, br_imm};
975  }
976 
977  // Length, including the length of the {TryTableImmediate}, but not the
978  // opcode. Must be called after consumingthe table entries.
979  uint32_t length() const {
980  DCHECK(!has_next());
981  return static_cast<uint32_t>(pc_ - start_);
982  }
983  const uint8_t* pc() const { return pc_; }
984 
985  TryTableIterator(Decoder* decoder, const TryTableImmediate& imm)
986  : decoder_(decoder),
987  start_(imm.start),
988  pc_(imm.table),
989  table_count_(imm.table_count) {}
990 
991  private:
992  Decoder* const decoder_;
993  const uint8_t* const start_;
994  const uint8_t* pc_;
995  uint32_t index_ = 0; // the current index.
996  const uint32_t table_count_; // the count of entries, not including default.
997 };

999 using EffectHandlerTableImmediate = BranchTableImmediate;

1001 struct HandlerCase {
1002  SwitchKind kind; // Regular handler or a switch site.
1003  TagIndexImmediate tag; // Tag defining this handler site.
1004  union MaybeHandlerDepth {
1005  uint8_t empty;
1006  BranchDepthImmediate br;
1007  } maybe_depth;
1008 };
1009 
1010 // A helper to iterate over a handler table.
1011 template <typename ValidationTag>
1012 class EffectHandlerTableIterator {
1013  public:
1014  uint32_t cur_index() const { return index_; }
1015  bool has_next() const {
1016  return VALIDATE(decoder_->ok()) && index_ < table_count_;
1017  }
1018 
1019  HandlerCase next() {
1020  uint8_t kind =
1021  static_cast<CatchKind>(decoder_->read_u8<ValidationTag>(pc_));
1022  pc_ += 1;
1023  TagIndexImmediate tag = TagIndexImmediate(decoder_, pc_, ValidationTag{});
1024  pc_ += tag.length;
1025 
1026  HandlerCase::MaybeHandlerDepth maybe_depth{0};
1027 
1028  if (kind == kOnSuspend) {
1029  maybe_depth.br = BranchDepthImmediate(decoder_, pc_, ValidationTag{});
1030  pc_ += maybe_depth.br.length;
1031  }
1032  index_++;
1033 
1034  return HandlerCase{static_cast<SwitchKind>(kind), tag, maybe_depth};
1035  }
1036 
1037  // Length, including the length of the {EffectHandlerTableImmediate}, but not
1038  // the opcode. Must be called after consuming the table entries.
1039  uint32_t length() const {
1040  DCHECK(!has_next());
1041  return static_cast<uint32_t>(pc_ - start_);
1042  }
1043  const uint8_t* pc() const { return pc_; }
1044 
1045  EffectHandlerTableIterator(Decoder* decoder,
1046  const EffectHandlerTableImmediate& imm)
1047  : decoder_(decoder),
1048  start_(imm.start),
1049  pc_(imm.table),
1050  table_count_(imm.table_count) {}
1051 
1052  private:
1053  Decoder* const decoder_;
1054  const uint8_t* const start_;
1055  const uint8_t* pc_;
1056  uint32_t index_ = 0; // the current index.
1057  const uint32_t table_count_;
1058 };

1060 struct MemoryAccessImmediate {
1061  uint32_t alignment;
1062  uint32_t mem_index;
1063  uint64_t offset;
1064  const WasmMemory* memory = nullptr;
1065 
1066  uint32_t length;
1067 
1068  template <typename ValidationTag>
1069  V8_INLINE MemoryAccessImmediate(Decoder* decoder, const uint8_t* pc,
1070  uint32_t max_alignment, ValidationTag = {}) {
1071  // Check for the fast path (two single-byte LEBs, mem index 0).
1072  const bool two_bytes = !ValidationTag::validate || decoder->end() - pc >= 2;
1073  const bool use_fast_path = two_bytes && !(pc[0] & 0xc0) && !(pc[1] & 0x80);
1074  if (V8_LIKELY(use_fast_path)) {
1075  alignment = pc[0];
1076  mem_index = 0;
1077  offset = pc[1];
1078  length = 2;
1079  } else {
1080  ConstructSlow<ValidationTag>(decoder, pc, max_alignment);
1081  }
1082  if (!VALIDATE(alignment <= max_alignment)) {
1083  DecodeError<ValidationTag>(
1084  decoder, pc,
1085  "invalid alignment; expected maximum alignment is %u, "
1086  "actual alignment is %u",
1087  max_alignment, alignment);
1088  }
1089  }
1090 
1091  private:
1092  template <typename ValidationTag>
1093  V8_NOINLINE V8_PRESERVE_MOST void ConstructSlow(Decoder* decoder,
1094  const uint8_t* pc,
1095  uint32_t max_alignment) {
1096  uint32_t alignment_length;
1097  std::tie(alignment, alignment_length) =
1098  decoder->read_u32v<ValidationTag>(pc, "alignment");
1099  length = alignment_length;
1100  if (alignment & 0x40) {
1101  alignment &= ~0x40;
1102  uint32_t mem_index_length;
1103  std::tie(mem_index, mem_index_length) =
1104  decoder->read_u32v<ValidationTag>(pc + length, "memory index");
1105  length += mem_index_length;
1106  } else {
1107  mem_index = 0;
1108  }
1109  uint32_t offset_length;
1110  std::tie(offset, offset_length) =
1111  decoder->read_u64v<ValidationTag>(pc + length, "offset");
1112  length += offset_length;
1113  }
1114 };
1115

1225  const uint8_t* pc_for_errors = nullptr;
1226 
1227  explicit PcForErrors(const uint8_t* pc) : pc_for_errors(pc) {}
1228 
1229  const uint8_t* pc() const { return pc_for_errors; }
1230 };
1231 
1232 // An entry on the value stack.
1233 template <typename ValidationTag>
1234 struct ValueBase : public PcForErrors<ValidationTag::validate> {
1235  ValueType type = kWasmVoid;
1236 
1237  ValueBase(const uint8_t* pc, ValueType type)
1238  : PcForErrors<ValidationTag::validate>(pc), type(type) {}
1239 };
1240 
1241 template <typename Value>
1242 struct Merge {
1243  uint32_t arity = 0;
1244  union { // Either multiple values or a single value.
1245  Value* array;
1246  Value first;
1247  } vals = {nullptr}; // Initialize {array} with {nullptr}.
1248 
1249  // Tracks whether this merge was ever reached. Uses precise reachability, like
1250  // Reachability::kReachable.
1251  bool reached;
1252 
1253  explicit Merge(bool reached = false) : reached(reached) {}
1254 
1255  Value& operator[](uint32_t i) {
1256  DCHECK_GT(arity, i);
1257  return arity == 1 ? vals.first : vals.array[i];
1258  }
1259 };
1260 
1261 enum ControlKind : uint8_t {
1262  kControlIf,
1263  kControlIfElse,
1264  kControlBlock,
1265  kControlLoop,
1266  kControlTry,
1267  kControlTryTable,
1268  kControlTryCatch,
1269  kControlTryCatchAll,
1270 };
1271 
1272 enum Reachability : uint8_t {
1273  // reachable code.
1274  kReachable,
1275  // reachable code in unreachable block (implies normal validation).
1276  kSpecOnlyReachable,
1277  // code unreachable in its own block (implies polymorphic validation).
1278  kUnreachable
1279 };
1280 
1281 // An entry on the control stack (i.e. if, block, loop, or try).
1282 template <typename Value, typename ValidationTag>
1283 struct ControlBase : public PcForErrors<ValidationTag::validate> {
1284  ControlKind kind = kControlBlock;
1285  Reachability reachability = kReachable;
1286 
1287  // For try-table.
1288  base::Vector<CatchCase> catch_cases;
1289 
1290  uint32_t stack_depth = 0; // Stack height at the beginning of the construct.
1291  uint32_t init_stack_depth = 0; // Height of "locals initialization" stack
1292  // at the beginning of the construct.
1293  int32_t previous_catch = -1; // Depth of the innermost catch containing this
1294  // 'try'.
1295 
1296  // Values merged into the start or end of this control construct.
1297  Merge<Value> start_merge;
1298  Merge<Value> end_merge;
1299 
1300  bool might_throw = false;
1301 
1302  MOVE_ONLY_NO_DEFAULT_CONSTRUCTOR(ControlBase);
1303 
1304  ControlBase(Zone* zone, ControlKind kind, uint32_t stack_depth,
1305  uint32_t init_stack_depth, const uint8_t* pc,
1306  Reachability reachability)
1307  : PcForErrors<ValidationTag::validate>(pc),
1308  kind(kind),
1309  reachability(reachability),
1310  stack_depth(stack_depth),
1311  init_stack_depth(init_stack_depth),
1312  start_merge(reachability == kReachable) {}
1313 
1314  // Check whether the current block is reachable.
1315  bool reachable() const { return reachability == kReachable; }
1316 
1317  // Check whether the rest of the block is unreachable.
1318  // Note that this is different from {!reachable()}, as there is also the
1319  // "indirect unreachable state", for which both {reachable()} and
1320  // {unreachable()} return false.
1321  bool unreachable() const { return reachability == kUnreachable; }
1322 
1323  // Return the reachability of new control structs started in this block.
1324  Reachability innerReachability() const {
1325  return reachability == kReachable ? kReachable : kSpecOnlyReachable;
1326  }
1327 
1328  bool is_if() const { return is_onearmed_if() || is_if_else(); }
1329  bool is_onearmed_if() const { return kind == kControlIf; }
1330  bool is_if_else() const { return kind == kControlIfElse; }
1331  bool is_block() const { return kind == kControlBlock; }
1332  bool is_loop() const { return kind == kControlLoop; }
1333  bool is_incomplete_try() const { return kind == kControlTry; }
1334  bool is_try_catch() const { return kind == kControlTryCatch; }
1335  bool is_try_catchall() const { return kind == kControlTryCatchAll; }
1336  bool is_try() const {
1337  return is_incomplete_try() || is_try_catch() || is_try_catchall();
1338  }
1339  bool is_try_table() { return kind == kControlTryTable; }
1340 
1341  Merge<Value>* br_merge() {
1342  return is_loop() ? &this->start_merge : &this->end_merge;
1343  }
1344 };

1615 // This is a global constant invalid instruction trace, to be pointed at by
1616 // the current instruction trace pointer in the default case
1617 const std::pair<uint32_t, uint32_t> invalid_instruction_trace = {0, 0};
1618 
1619 // A fast vector implementation, without implicit bounds checks (see
1620 // https://crbug.com/1358853).
1621 template <typename T>
1622 class FastZoneVector {
1623  public:
1624  FastZoneVector() = default;
1625  explicit FastZoneVector(int initial_size, Zone* zone) {
1626  Grow(initial_size, zone);
1627  }
1628 
1629 #ifdef DEBUG
1630  ~FastZoneVector() {
1631  // Check that {Reset} was called on this vector.
1632  DCHECK_NULL(begin_);
1633  }
1634 #endif
1635 
1636  void Reset(Zone* zone) {
1637  if (begin_ == nullptr) return;
1638  if constexpr (!std::is_trivially_destructible_v<T>) {
1639  for (T* ptr = begin_; ptr != end_; ++ptr) {
1640  ptr->~T();
1641  }
1642  }
1643  zone->DeleteArray(begin_, capacity_end_ - begin_);
1644  begin_ = nullptr;
1645  end_ = nullptr;
1646  capacity_end_ = nullptr;
1647  }
1648 
1649  T* begin() const { return begin_; }
1650  T* end() const { return end_; }
1651 
1652  T& front() {
1653  DCHECK(!empty());
1654  return begin_[0];
1655  }
1656 
1657  T& back() {
1658  DCHECK(!empty());
1659  return end_[-1];
1660  }
1661 
1662  uint32_t size() const { return static_cast<uint32_t>(end_ - begin_); }
1663 
1664  bool empty() const { return begin_ == end_; }
1665 
1666  T& operator[](uint32_t index) {
1667  DCHECK_GE(size(), index);
1668  return begin_[index];
1669  }
1670 
1671  void shrink_to(uint32_t new_size) {
1672  static_assert(std::is_trivially_destructible_v<T>);
1673  DCHECK_GE(size(), new_size);
1674  end_ = begin_ + new_size;
1675  }
1676 
1677  void pop(uint32_t num = 1) {
1678  DCHECK_GE(size(), num);
1679  for (T* new_end = end_ - num; end_ != new_end;) {
1680  --end_;
1681  end_->~T();
1682  }
1683  }
1684 
1685  void push(T value) {
1686  DCHECK_GT(capacity_end_, end_);
1687  *end_ = std::move(value);
1688  ++end_;
1689  }
1690 
1691  template <typename... Args>
1692  void emplace_back(Args&&... args) {
1693  DCHECK_GT(capacity_end_, end_);
1694  new (end_) T{std::forward<Args>(args)...};
1695  ++end_;
1696  }
1697 
1698  V8_INLINE void EnsureMoreCapacity(int slots_needed, Zone* zone) {
1699  if (V8_LIKELY(capacity_end_ - end_ >= slots_needed)) return;
1700  Grow(slots_needed, zone);
1701  }
1702 
1703  private:
1704  V8_NOINLINE V8_PRESERVE_MOST void Grow(int slots_needed, Zone* zone) {
1705  size_t new_capacity = std::max(
1706  size_t{8}, base::bits::RoundUpToPowerOfTwo(size() + slots_needed));
1707  CHECK_GE(kMaxUInt32, new_capacity);
1708  DCHECK_LT(capacity_end_ - begin_, new_capacity);
1709  T* new_begin = zone->template AllocateArray<T>(new_capacity);
1710  if (begin_) {
1711  for (T *ptr = begin_, *new_ptr = new_begin; ptr != end_;
1712  ++ptr, ++new_ptr) {
1713  new (new_ptr) T{std::move(*ptr)};
1714  ptr->~T();
1715  }
1716  zone->DeleteArray(begin_, capacity_end_ - begin_);
1717  }
1718  end_ = new_begin + (end_ - begin_);
1719  begin_ = new_begin;
1720  capacity_end_ = new_begin + new_capacity;
1721  }
1722 
1723  // The array is zone-allocated inside {EnsureMoreCapacity}.
1724  T* begin_ = nullptr;
1725  T* end_ = nullptr;
1726  T* capacity_end_ = nullptr;
1727 };
1728 
1729 // Generic Wasm bytecode decoder with utilities for decoding immediates,
1730 // lengths, etc.
1731 template <typename ValidationTag, DecodingMode decoding_mode = kFunctionBody>
1732 class WasmDecoder : public Decoder {
1733  public:
1734  WasmDecoder(Zone* zone, const WasmModule* module, WasmEnabledFeatures enabled,
1735  WasmDetectedFeatures* detected, const FunctionSig* sig,
1736  bool is_shared, const uint8_t* start, const uint8_t* end,
1737  uint32_t buffer_offset = 0)
1738  : Decoder(start, end, buffer_offset),
1739  zone_(zone),
1740  module_(module),
1741  enabled_(enabled),
1742  detected_(detected),
1743  sig_(sig),
1744  is_shared_(is_shared) {
1745  current_inst_trace_ = &invalid_instruction_trace;
1746  if (V8_UNLIKELY(module_ && !module_->inst_traces.empty())) {
1747  auto last_trace = module_->inst_traces.end() - 1;
1748  auto first_inst_trace =
1749  std::lower_bound(module_->inst_traces.begin(), last_trace,
1750  std::make_pair(buffer_offset, 0),
1751  [](const std::pair<uint32_t, uint32_t>& a,
1752  const std::pair<uint32_t, uint32_t>& b) {
1753  return a.first < b.first;
1754  });
1755  if (V8_UNLIKELY(first_inst_trace != last_trace)) {
1756  current_inst_trace_ = &*first_inst_trace;
1757  }
1758  }
1759  }
1760 
1761  Zone* zone() const { return zone_; }
1762 
1763  uint32_t num_locals() const { return num_locals_; }
1764 
1765  base::Vector<ValueType> local_types() const {
1766  return base::VectorOf(local_types_, num_locals_);
1767  }
1768  ValueType local_type(uint32_t index) const {
1769  DCHECK_GE(num_locals_, index);
1770  return local_types_[index];
1771  }
1772 
1773  // Decodes local definitions in the current decoder.
1774  // The decoded locals will be appended to {this->local_types_}.
1775  // The decoder's pc is not advanced.
1776  // The total length of decoded locals is returned.
1777  uint32_t DecodeLocals(const uint8_t* pc) {
1778  DCHECK_NULL(local_types_);
1779  DCHECK_EQ(0, num_locals_);
1780 
1781  // In a first step, count the number of locals and store the decoded
1782  // entries.
1783  num_locals_ = static_cast<uint32_t>(this->sig_->parameter_count());
1784 
1785  // Decode local declarations, if any.
1786  auto [entries, entries_length] =
1787  read_u32v<ValidationTag>(pc, "local decls count");
1788 
1789  if (!VALIDATE(ok())) {
1790  DecodeError(pc, "invalid local decls count");
1791  return 0;
1792  }
1793  TRACE("local decls count: %u\n", entries);
1794 
1795  // Do an early validity check, to avoid allocating too much memory below.
1796  // Every entry needs at least two bytes (count plus type); if that many are
1797  // not available any more, flag that as an error.
1798  if (available_bytes() / 2 < entries) {
1799  DecodeError(pc, "local decls count bigger than remaining function size");
1800  return 0;
1801  }
1802 
1803  struct DecodedLocalEntry {
1804  uint32_t count;
1805  ValueType type;
1806  };
1807  base::SmallVector<DecodedLocalEntry, 8> decoded_locals(entries);
1808  uint32_t total_length = entries_length;
1809  for (uint32_t entry = 0; entry < entries; ++entry) {
1810  if (!VALIDATE(more())) {
1811  DecodeError(end(),
1812  "expected more local decls but reached end of input");
1813  return 0;
1814  }
1815 
1816  auto [count, count_length] =
1817  read_u32v<ValidationTag>(pc + total_length, "local count");
1818  if (!VALIDATE(ok())) {
1819  DecodeError(pc + total_length, "invalid local count");
1820  return 0;
1821  }
1822  DCHECK_LE(num_locals_, kV8MaxWasmFunctionLocals);
1823  if (!VALIDATE(count <= kV8MaxWasmFunctionLocals - num_locals_)) {
1824  DecodeError(pc + total_length, "local count too large");
1825  return 0;
1826  }
1827  total_length += count_length;
1828 
1829  auto [type, type_length] =
1830  value_type_reader::read_value_type<ValidationTag>(
1831  this, pc + total_length, enabled_, detected_);
1832  ValidateValueType(pc + total_length, type);
1833  if (!VALIDATE(ok())) return 0;
1834  if (module_) {
1835  value_type_reader::Populate(&type, module_);
1836  } else {
1837  DCHECK(!ValidationTag::validate);
1838  }
1839  if (!VALIDATE(!is_shared_ || type.is_shared())) {
1840  DecodeError(pc + total_length, "local must have shared type");
1841  return 0;
1842  }
1843  total_length += type_length;
1844 
1845  num_locals_ += count;
1846  decoded_locals[entry] = DecodedLocalEntry{count, type};
1847  }
1848  DCHECK(ok());
1849 
1850  if (num_locals_ > 0) {
1851  // Now build the array of local types from the parsed entries.
1852  local_types_ = zone_->AllocateArray<ValueType>(num_locals_);
1853  ValueType* locals_ptr = local_types_;
1854 
1855  if (sig_->parameter_count() > 0) {
1856  std::copy(sig_->parameters().begin(), sig_->parameters().end(),
1857  locals_ptr);
1858  locals_ptr += sig_->parameter_count();
1859  }
1860 
1861  for (auto& entry : decoded_locals) {
1862  std::fill_n(locals_ptr, entry.count, entry.type);
1863  locals_ptr += entry.count;
1864  }
1865  DCHECK_EQ(locals_ptr, local_types_ + num_locals_);
1866  }
1867  return total_length;
1868  }
1869 
1870  // Shorthand that forwards to the {DecodeError} functions above, passing our
1871  // {ValidationTag}.
1872  template <typename... Args>
1873  V8_INLINE void DecodeError(Args... args) {
1874  wasm::DecodeError<ValidationTag>(this, std::forward<Args>(args)...);
1875  }
1876 
1877  // Returns a BitVector of length {locals_count + 1} representing the set of
1878  // variables that are assigned in the loop starting at {pc}. The additional
1879  // position at the end of the vector represents possible assignments to
1880  // the instance cache.
1881  static BitVector* AnalyzeLoopAssignment(WasmDecoder* decoder,
1882  const uint8_t* pc,
1883  uint32_t locals_count, Zone* zone,
1884  bool* loop_is_innermost = nullptr) {
1885  if (pc >= decoder->end()) return nullptr;
1886  if (*pc != kExprLoop) return nullptr;
1887  // The number of locals_count is augmented by 1 so that the 'locals_count'
1888  // index can be used to track the instance cache.
1889  BitVector* assigned = zone->New<BitVector>(locals_count + 1, zone);
1890  int depth = -1; // We will increment the depth to 0 when we decode the
1891  // starting 'loop' opcode.
1892  if (loop_is_innermost) *loop_is_innermost = true;
1893  // Iteratively process all AST nodes nested inside the loop.
1894  while (pc < decoder->end() && VALIDATE(decoder->ok())) {
1895  WasmOpcode opcode = static_cast<WasmOpcode>(*pc);
1896  switch (opcode) {
1897  case kExprLoop:
1898  if (loop_is_innermost && depth >= 0) *loop_is_innermost = false;
1899  [[fallthrough]];
1900  case kExprIf:
1901  case kExprBlock:
1902  case kExprTry:
1903  case kExprTryTable:
1904  depth++;
1905  break;
1906  case kExprLocalSet:
1907  case kExprLocalTee: {
1908  IndexImmediate imm(decoder, pc + 1, "local index", validate);
1909  // Unverified code might have an out-of-bounds index.
1910  if (imm.index < locals_count) assigned->Add(imm.index);
1911  break;
1912  }
1913  case kExprMemoryGrow:
1914  case kExprCallFunction:
1915  case kExprCallIndirect:
1916  case kExprCallRef:
1917  // Add instance cache to the assigned set.
1918  assigned->Add(locals_count);
1919  break;
1920  case kExprEnd:
1921  depth--;
1922  break;
1923  default:
1924  break;
1925  }
1926  if (depth < 0) break;
1927  pc += OpcodeLength(decoder, pc);
1928  }
1929  return VALIDATE(decoder->ok()) ? assigned : nullptr;
1930  }
1931 
1932  bool Validate(const uint8_t* pc, TagIndexImmediate& imm) {
1933  size_t num_tags = module_->tags.size();
1934  if (!VALIDATE(imm.index < num_tags)) {
1935  DecodeError(pc, "Invalid tag index: %u", imm.index);
1936  return false;
1937  }
1938  V8_ASSUME(imm.index < num_tags);
1939  imm.tag = &module_->tags[imm.index];
1940  return true;
1941  }

1943  bool Validate(const uint8_t* pc, GlobalIndexImmediate& imm) {
1944  // We compare with the current size of the globals vector. This is important
1945  // if we are decoding a constant expression in the global section.
1946  size_t num_globals = module_->globals.size();
1947  if (!VALIDATE(imm.index < num_globals)) {
1948  DecodeError(pc, "Invalid global index: %u", imm.index);
1949  return false;
1950  }
1951  V8_ASSUME(imm.index < num_globals);
1952  imm.global = &module_->globals[imm.index];
1953  if (!VALIDATE(!is_shared_ || imm.global->shared)) {
1954  DecodeError(pc, "Cannot access non-shared global %d in a shared %s",
1955  imm.index,
1956  decoding_mode == kConstantExpression ? "constant expression"
1957  : "function");
1958  return false;
1959  }
1960 
1961  if constexpr (decoding_mode == kConstantExpression) {
1962  if (!VALIDATE(!imm.global->mutability)) {
1963  this->DecodeError(pc,
1964  "mutable globals cannot be used in constant "
1965  "expressions");
1966  return false;
1967  }
1968  }
1969 
1970  return true;
1971  }

1979  imm.shared = module_->type(imm.index).is_shared;
1980  return true;

2014  bool CanReturnCall(const FunctionSig* target_sig) {
2015  if (sig_->return_count() != target_sig->return_count()) return false;
2016  auto target_sig_it = target_sig->returns().begin();
2017  for (ValueType ret_type : sig_->returns()) {
2018  if (!IsSubtypeOf(*target_sig_it++, ret_type, this->module_)) return false;
2019  }
2020  return true;
2021  }

2023  bool Validate(const uint8_t* pc, CallFunctionImmediate& imm) {
2024  size_t num_functions = module_->functions.size();
2025  if (!VALIDATE(imm.index < num_functions)) {
2026  DecodeError(pc, "function index #%u is out of bounds", imm.index);
2027  return false;
2028  }
2029  if (is_shared_ && !module_->function_is_shared(imm.index)) {
2030  DecodeError(pc, "cannot call non-shared function %u", imm.index);
2031  return false;
2032  }
2033  V8_ASSUME(imm.index < num_functions);
2034  imm.sig = module_->functions[imm.index].sig;
2035  return true;
2036  }

2038  bool Validate(const uint8_t* pc, CallIndirectImmediate& imm) {
2039  if (!Validate(pc, imm.sig_imm)) return false;
2040  if (!Validate(pc + imm.sig_imm.length, imm.table_imm)) return false;
2041  ValueType table_type = imm.table_imm.table->type;
2042  if (!VALIDATE(table_type.ref_type_kind() == RefTypeKind::kFunction)) {
2043  DecodeError(
2044  pc, "call_indirect: immediate table #%u is not of a function type",
2045  imm.table_imm.index);
2046  return false;
2047  }
2048  // The type specified by the immediate does not need to have any static
2049  // relation (neither sub nor super) to the type of the table. The type
2050  // of the function will be checked at runtime.
2051 
2052  imm.sig = module_->signature(imm.sig_imm.index);
2053  return true;
2054  }

2057  size_t control_depth) {
2058  if (!VALIDATE(imm.depth < control_depth)) {
2059  DecodeError(pc, "invalid branch depth: %u", imm.depth);
2060  return false;
2061  }
2062  return true;
2063  }

2065  bool Validate(const uint8_t* pc, BranchTableImmediate& imm) {
2066  if (!VALIDATE(imm.table_count <= kV8MaxWasmFunctionBrTableSize)) {
2067  DecodeError(pc, "invalid table count (> max br_table size): %u",
2068  imm.table_count);
2069  return false;
2070  }
2071  return checkAvailable(imm.table_count);
2072  }

2074  bool Validate(const uint8_t* pc, WasmOpcode opcode, SimdLaneImmediate& imm) {
2075  uint8_t num_lanes = 0;
2076  switch (opcode) {
2077  case kExprF64x2ExtractLane:
2078  case kExprF64x2ReplaceLane:
2079  case kExprI64x2ExtractLane:
2080  case kExprI64x2ReplaceLane:
2081  case kExprS128Load64Lane:
2082  case kExprS128Store64Lane:
2083  num_lanes = 2;
2084  break;
2085  case kExprF32x4ExtractLane:
2086  case kExprF32x4ReplaceLane:
2087  case kExprI32x4ExtractLane:
2088  case kExprI32x4ReplaceLane:
2089  case kExprS128Load32Lane:
2090  case kExprS128Store32Lane:
2091  num_lanes = 4;
2092  break;
2093  case kExprF16x8ExtractLane:
2094  case kExprF16x8ReplaceLane:
2095  case kExprI16x8ExtractLaneS:
2096  case kExprI16x8ExtractLaneU:
2097  case kExprI16x8ReplaceLane:
2098  case kExprS128Load16Lane:
2099  case kExprS128Store16Lane:
2100  num_lanes = 8;
2101  break;
2102  case kExprI8x16ExtractLaneS:
2103  case kExprI8x16ExtractLaneU:
2104  case kExprI8x16ReplaceLane:
2105  case kExprS128Load8Lane:
2106  case kExprS128Store8Lane:
2107  num_lanes = 16;
2108  break;
2109  default:
2110  UNREACHABLE();
2111  break;
2112  }
2113  if (!VALIDATE(imm.lane >= 0 && imm.lane < num_lanes)) {
2114  DecodeError(pc, "invalid lane index");
2115  return false;
2116  } else {
2117  return true;
2118  }
2119  }
2120 
2121  bool Validate(const uint8_t* pc, Simd128Immediate& imm) {
2122  uint8_t max_lane = 0;
2123  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < kSimd128Size; ++i) {
2124  max_lane = std::max(max_lane, imm.value[i]);
2125  }
2126  // Shuffle indices must be in [0..31] for a 16 lane shuffle.
2127  if (!VALIDATE(max_lane < 2 * kSimd128Size)) {
2128  DecodeError(pc, "invalid shuffle mask");
2129  return false;
2130  }
2131  return true;
2132  }
2133 
2134  bool Validate(const uint8_t* pc, BlockTypeImmediate& imm) {
2135  if (imm.sig.all().begin() == nullptr) {
2136  // Then use {sig_index} to initialize the signature.
2137  if (!VALIDATE(module_->has_signature(imm.sig_index))) {
2138  DecodeError(pc, "block type index %u is not a signature definition",
2139  imm.sig_index);
2140  return false;
2141  }
2142  imm.sig = *module_->signature(imm.sig_index);
2143  if (imm.sig.parameter_count() > 0) {
2144  // Multi-value also allows blocks to return multiple values, but this
2145  // is already detected during signature decoding, so we don't need to
2146  // check again here.
2147  detected_->add_multi_value();
2148  }
2149  } else {
2150  // Then it's an MVP immediate with 0 parameters and 0-1 returns.
2151  DCHECK_EQ(0, imm.sig.parameter_count());
2152  DCHECK_GE(1, imm.sig.return_count());
2153  if (imm.sig.return_count()) {
2154  if (!ValidateValueType(pc, imm.sig.GetReturn(0))) return false;
2155  DCHECK_EQ(imm.sig.all().begin(), imm.single_return_sig_storage);
2156  value_type_reader::Populate(imm.single_return_sig_storage, module_);
2157  }
2158  }
2159  return true;
2160  }

2162  bool Validate(const uint8_t* pc, MemoryIndexImmediate& imm) {
2163  size_t num_memories = module_->memories.size();
2164  if (imm.index > 0 || imm.length > 1) {
2165  this->detected_->add_multi_memory();
2166  if (v8_flags.wasm_jitless) {
2167  DecodeError(pc, "Multiple memories not supported in Wasm jitless mode");
2168  return false;
2169  }
2170  }
2171 
2172  if (!VALIDATE(imm.index < num_memories)) {
2173  DecodeError(pc,
2174  "memory index %u exceeds number of declared memories (%zu)",
2175  imm.index, num_memories);
2176  return false;
2177  }
2178 
2179  V8_ASSUME(imm.index < num_memories);
2180  imm.memory = this->module_->memories.data() + imm.index;
2181 
2182  return true;
2183  }

2185  bool Validate(const uint8_t* pc, MemoryAccessImmediate& imm) {
2186  size_t num_memories = module_->memories.size();
2187  if (!VALIDATE(imm.mem_index < num_memories)) {
2188  DecodeError(pc,
2189  "memory index %u exceeds number of declared memories (%zu)",
2190  imm.mem_index, num_memories);
2191  return false;
2192  }
2193  if (!VALIDATE(this->module_->memories[imm.mem_index].is_memory64() ||
2194  imm.offset <= kMaxUInt32)) {
2195  this->DecodeError(pc, "memory offset outside 32-bit range: %" PRIu64,
2196  imm.offset);
2197  return false;
2198  }
2199 
2200  V8_ASSUME(imm.mem_index < num_memories);
2201  imm.memory = this->module_->memories.data() + imm.mem_index;
2202 
2203  return true;
2204  }

2273  // The following Validate* functions all validate an `IndexImmediate`, albeit

2290  }
2291 
2292  bool ValidateLocal(const uint8_t* pc, IndexImmediate& imm) {
2293  if (!VALIDATE(imm.index < num_locals())) {
2294  DecodeError(pc, "invalid local index: %u", imm.index);
2295  return false;
2296  }
2297  return true;
2298  }
2299 
2300  bool ValidateFunction(const uint8_t* pc, IndexImmediate& imm) {
2301  size_t num_functions = module_->functions.size();
2302  if (!VALIDATE(imm.index < num_functions)) {
2303  DecodeError(pc, "function index #%u is out of bounds", imm.index);
2304  return false;
2305  }
2306  V8_ASSUME(imm.index < num_functions);
2307  if (decoding_mode == kFunctionBody &&
2308  !VALIDATE(module_->functions[imm.index].declared)) {
2309  DecodeError(pc, "undeclared reference to function #%u", imm.index);
2310  return false;
2311  }
2312  return true;
2313  }
2314 
2315  bool ValidateCont(const uint8_t* pc, ContIndexImmediate& imm) {
2316  if (!VALIDATE(module_->has_cont_type(imm.index))) {
2317  DecodeError(pc, "invalid cont index: %u", imm.index.index);
2318  return false;
2319  }
2320  imm.cont_type = module_->cont_type(imm.index);
2321  imm.shared = module_->type(imm.index).is_shared;
2322 
2323  return true;
2324  }
2325 
2326  bool ValidateDataSegment(const uint8_t* pc, IndexImmediate& imm) {
2327  if (!VALIDATE(imm.index < module_->num_declared_data_segments)) {
2328  DecodeError(pc, "invalid data segment index: %u", imm.index);
2329  return false;
2330  }
2331  // TODO(14616): Data segments aren't available during eager validation.
2332  // Discussion: github.com/WebAssembly/shared-everything-threads/issues/83
2333  if (!VALIDATE(!is_shared_ || module_->data_segments[imm.index].shared)) {
2334  DecodeError(
2335  pc, "cannot refer to non-shared segment %u from a shared function",
2336  imm.index);
2337  return false;
2338  }
2339  return true;
2340  }
2341 
2342  bool Validate(const uint8_t* pc, SelectTypeImmediate& imm) {
2343  if (!VALIDATE(ValidateValueType(pc, imm.type))) return false;
2344  value_type_reader::Populate(&imm.type, module_);
2345  return true;
2346  }
2347 
2348  bool Validate(const uint8_t* pc, HeapTypeImmediate& imm) {
2349  if (!VALIDATE(ValidateHeapType(pc, imm.type))) return false;
2350  value_type_reader::Populate(&imm.type, module_);
2351  return true;
2352  }
2353 
2354  bool ValidateValueType(const uint8_t* pc, ValueType type) {
2355  return value_type_reader::ValidateValueType<ValidationTag>(this, pc,
2356  module_, type);
2357  }
2358 
2359  bool ValidateHeapType(const uint8_t* pc, HeapType type) {
2360  return value_type_reader::ValidateHeapType<ValidationTag>(this, pc, module_,
2361  type);
2362  }
2363 
2364  // Returns the length of the opcode under {pc}.
2365  template <typename... ImmediateObservers>
2366  static uint32_t OpcodeLength(WasmDecoder* decoder, const uint8_t* pc,
2367  ImmediateObservers&... ios) {
2368  WasmOpcode opcode = static_cast<WasmOpcode>(*pc);
2369  switch (opcode) {
2370  /********** Control opcodes **********/
2371  case kExprUnreachable:
2372  case kExprNop:
2373  case kExprNopForTestingUnsupportedInLiftoff:
2374  case kExprElse:
2375  case kExprEnd:
2376  case kExprReturn:
2377  return 1;
2378  case kExprTry:
2379  case kExprIf:
2380  case kExprLoop:
2381  case kExprBlock: {
2382  BlockTypeImmediate imm(WasmEnabledFeatures::All(), decoder->detected_,
2383  decoder, pc + 1, validate);
2384  (ios.BlockType(imm), ...);
2385  return 1 + imm.length;
2386  }
2387  case kExprRethrow:
2388  case kExprBr:
2389  case kExprBrIf:
2390  case kExprBrOnNull:
2391  case kExprBrOnNonNull:
2392  case kExprDelegate: {
2393  BranchDepthImmediate imm(decoder, pc + 1, validate);
2394  (ios.BranchDepth(imm), ...);
2395  return 1 + imm.length;
2396  }
2397  case kExprBrTable: {
2398  BranchTableImmediate imm(decoder, pc + 1, validate);
2399  (ios.BranchTable(imm), ...);
2400  BranchTableIterator<ValidationTag> iterator(decoder, imm);
2401  while (iterator.has_next()) iterator.next();
2402  return 1 + iterator.length();
2403  }
2404  case kExprTryTable: {
2405  BlockTypeImmediate block_type_imm(WasmEnabledFeatures::All(),
2406  decoder->detected_, decoder, pc + 1,
2407  validate);
2408  (ios.BlockType(block_type_imm), ...);
2409  TryTableImmediate try_table_imm(decoder, pc + 1 + block_type_imm.length,
2410  validate);
2411  (ios.TryTable(try_table_imm), ...);
2412  TryTableIterator<ValidationTag> iterator(decoder, try_table_imm);
2413  while (iterator.has_next()) iterator.next();
2414  return 1 + block_type_imm.length + iterator.length();
2415  }
2416  case kExprThrow:
2417  case kExprCatch: {
2418  TagIndexImmediate imm(decoder, pc + 1, validate);
2419  (ios.TagIndex(imm), ...);
2420  return 1 + imm.length;
2421  }
2422  case kExprThrowRef:
2423  return 1;
2424 
2425  /********** Core stack switching ********/
2426  case kExprContNew: {
2427  ContIndexImmediate imm(decoder, pc + 1, validate);
2428  (ios.TypeIndex(imm), ...);
2429  return 1 + imm.length;
2430  }
2431  case kExprContBind: {
2432  ContIndexImmediate src(decoder, pc + 1, validate);
2433  (ios.TypeIndex(src), ...);
2434  ContIndexImmediate dst(decoder, pc + 1 + src.length, validate);
2435  (ios.TypeIndex(dst), ...);
2436  return 1 + src.length + dst.length;
2437  }
2438  case kExprSuspend: {
2439  TagIndexImmediate imm(decoder, pc + 1, validate);
2440  (ios.TagIndex(imm), ...);
2441  return 1 + imm.length;
2442  }
2443  case kExprResume: {
2444  ContIndexImmediate src(decoder, pc + 1, validate);
2445  (ios.TypeIndex(src), ...);
2446  EffectHandlerTableImmediate handler_table(decoder, pc + 1 + src.length,
2447  validate);
2448  (ios.EffectHandlerTable(handler_table), ...);
2449  EffectHandlerTableIterator<ValidationTag> iterator(decoder,
2450  handler_table);
2451  while (iterator.has_next()) iterator.next();
2452  return 1 + src.length + iterator.length();
2453  }
2454  case kExprResumeThrow: {
2455  ContIndexImmediate src(decoder, pc + 1, validate);
2456  (ios.TypeIndex(src), ...);
2457  TagIndexImmediate event(decoder, pc + src.length + 1, validate);
2458  (ios.TagIndex(event), ...);
2459  EffectHandlerTableImmediate handler_table(
2460  decoder, pc + 1 + src.length + event.length, validate);
2461  (ios.EffectHandlerTable(handler_table), ...);
2462  EffectHandlerTableIterator<ValidationTag> iterator(decoder,
2463  handler_table);
2464  while (iterator.has_next()) iterator.next();
2465  return 1 + src.length + event.length + iterator.length();
2466  }
2467  case kExprSwitch: {
2468  ContIndexImmediate src(decoder, pc + 1, validate);
2469  (ios.TypeIndex(src), ...);
2470  TagIndexImmediate tag(decoder, pc + src.length + 1, validate);
2471  (ios.TagIndex(tag), ...);
2472  return 1 + src.length + tag.length;
2473  }
2474 
2475  /********** Misc opcodes **********/
2476  case kExprCallFunction:
2477  case kExprReturnCall: {
2478  CallFunctionImmediate imm(decoder, pc + 1, validate);
2479  (ios.FunctionIndex(imm), ...);
2480  return 1 + imm.length;
2481  }
2482  case kExprCallIndirect:
2483  case kExprReturnCallIndirect: {
2484  CallIndirectImmediate imm(decoder, pc + 1, validate);
2485  (ios.CallIndirect(imm), ...);
2486  return 1 + imm.length;
2487  }
2488  case kExprCallRef:
2489  case kExprReturnCallRef: {
2490  SigIndexImmediate imm(decoder, pc + 1, validate);
2491  (ios.TypeIndex(imm), ...);
2492  return 1 + imm.length;
2493  }
2494  case kExprDrop:
2495  case kExprSelect:
2496  case kExprCatchAll:
2497  case kExprRefEq:
2498  return 1;
2499  case kExprSelectWithType: {
2500  SelectTypeImmediate imm(WasmEnabledFeatures::All(), decoder->detected_,
2501  decoder, pc + 1, validate);
2502  (ios.SelectType(imm), ...);
2503  return 1 + imm.length;
2504  }
2505 
2506  case kExprLocalGet:
2507  case kExprLocalSet:
2508  case kExprLocalTee: {
2509  IndexImmediate imm(decoder, pc + 1, "local index", validate);
2510  (ios.LocalIndex(imm), ...);
2511  return 1 + imm.length;
2512  }
2513  case kExprGlobalGet:
2514  case kExprGlobalSet: {
2515  GlobalIndexImmediate imm(decoder, pc + 1, validate);
2516  (ios.GlobalIndex(imm), ...);
2517  return 1 + imm.length;
2518  }
2519  case kExprTableGet:
2520  case kExprTableSet: {
2521  TableIndexImmediate imm(decoder, pc + 1, validate);
2522  (ios.TableIndex(imm), ...);
2523  return 1 + imm.length;
2524  }
2525  case kExprI32Const: {
2526  ImmI32Immediate imm(decoder, pc + 1, validate);
2527  (ios.I32Const(imm), ...);
2528  return 1 + imm.length;
2529  }
2530  case kExprI64Const: {
2531  ImmI64Immediate imm(decoder, pc + 1, validate);
2532  (ios.I64Const(imm), ...);
2533  return 1 + imm.length;
2534  }
2535  case kExprF32Const:
2536  if (sizeof...(ios) > 0) {
2537  ImmF32Immediate imm(decoder, pc + 1, validate);
2538  (ios.F32Const(imm), ...);
2539  }
2540  return 5;
2541  case kExprF64Const:
2542  if (sizeof...(ios) > 0) {
2543  ImmF64Immediate imm(decoder, pc + 1, validate);
2544  (ios.F64Const(imm), ...);
2545  }
2546  return 9;
2547  case kExprRefNull: {
2548  HeapTypeImmediate imm(WasmEnabledFeatures::All(), decoder->detected_,
2549  decoder, pc + 1, validate);
2550  (ios.HeapType(imm), ...);
2551  return 1 + imm.length;
2552  }
2553  case kExprRefIsNull:
2554  case kExprRefAsNonNull:
2555  return 1;
2556  case kExprRefFunc: {
2557  IndexImmediate imm(decoder, pc + 1, "function index", validate);
2558  (ios.FunctionIndex(imm), ...);
2559  return 1 + imm.length;
2560  }
2561 
2562 #define DECLARE_OPCODE_CASE(name, ...) case kExpr##name:
2563  // clang-format off
2564  /********** Simple and memory opcodes **********/
2565  FOREACH_SIMPLE_OPCODE(DECLARE_OPCODE_CASE)
2566  FOREACH_SIMPLE_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(DECLARE_OPCODE_CASE)
2567  return 1;
2568  FOREACH_LOAD_MEM_OPCODE(DECLARE_OPCODE_CASE)
2569  FOREACH_STORE_MEM_OPCODE(DECLARE_OPCODE_CASE) {
2570  MemoryAccessImmediate imm(decoder, pc + 1, UINT32_MAX,
2571  validate);
2572  (ios.MemoryAccess(imm), ...);
2573  return 1 + imm.length;
2574  }
2575  // clang-format on
2576  case kExprMemoryGrow:
2577  case kExprMemorySize: {
2578  MemoryIndexImmediate imm(decoder, pc + 1, validate);
2579  (ios.MemoryIndex(imm), ...);
2580  return 1 + imm.length;
2581  }
2582 
2583  /********** Prefixed opcodes **********/
2584  case kNumericPrefix: {
2585  uint32_t length;
2586  std::tie(opcode, length) =
2587  decoder->read_prefixed_opcode<ValidationTag>(pc);
2588  switch (opcode) {
2589  case kExprI32SConvertSatF32:
2590  case kExprI32UConvertSatF32:
2591  case kExprI32SConvertSatF64:
2592  case kExprI32UConvertSatF64:
2593  case kExprI64SConvertSatF32:
2594  case kExprI64UConvertSatF32:
2595  case kExprI64SConvertSatF64:
2596  case kExprI64UConvertSatF64:
2597  return length;
2598  case kExprMemoryInit: {
2599  MemoryInitImmediate imm(decoder, pc + length, validate);
2600  (ios.MemoryInit(imm), ...);
2601  return length + imm.length;
2602  }
2603  case kExprDataDrop: {
2604  IndexImmediate imm(decoder, pc + length, "data segment index",
2605  validate);
2606  (ios.DataSegmentIndex(imm), ...);
2607  return length + imm.length;
2608  }
2609  case kExprMemoryCopy: {
2610  MemoryCopyImmediate imm(decoder, pc + length, validate);
2611  (ios.MemoryCopy(imm), ...);
2612  return length + imm.length;
2613  }
2614  case kExprMemoryFill: {
2615  MemoryIndexImmediate imm(decoder, pc + length, validate);
2616  (ios.MemoryIndex(imm), ...);
2617  return length + imm.length;
2618  }
2619  case kExprTableInit: {
2620  TableInitImmediate imm(decoder, pc + length, validate);
2621  (ios.TableInit(imm), ...);
2622  return length + imm.length;
2623  }
2624  case kExprElemDrop: {
2625  IndexImmediate imm(decoder, pc + length, "element segment index",
2626  validate);
2627  (ios.ElemSegmentIndex(imm), ...);
2628  return length + imm.length;
2629  }
2630  case kExprTableCopy: {
2631  TableCopyImmediate imm(decoder, pc + length, validate);
2632  (ios.TableCopy(imm), ...);
2633  return length + imm.length;
2634  }
2635  case kExprTableGrow:
2636  case kExprTableSize:
2637  case kExprTableFill: {
2638  TableIndexImmediate imm(decoder, pc + length, validate);
2639  (ios.TableIndex(imm), ...);
2640  return length + imm.length;
2641  }
2642  case kExprF32LoadMemF16:
2643  case kExprF32StoreMemF16: {
2644  MemoryAccessImmediate imm(decoder, pc + length, UINT32_MAX,
2645  validate);
2646  (ios.MemoryAccess(imm), ...);
2647  return length + imm.length;
2648  }
2649  default:
2650  // This path is only possible if we are validating.
2651  V8_ASSUME(ValidationTag::validate);
2652  decoder->DecodeError(pc, "invalid numeric opcode");
2653  return length;
2654  }
2655  }
2656  case kAsmJsPrefix: {
2657  uint32_t length;
2658  std::tie(opcode, length) =
2659  decoder->read_prefixed_opcode<ValidationTag>(pc);
2660  switch (opcode) {
2661  FOREACH_ASMJS_COMPAT_OPCODE(DECLARE_OPCODE_CASE)
2662  return length;
2663  default:
2664  // This path is only possible if we are validating.
2665  V8_ASSUME(ValidationTag::validate);
2666  decoder->DecodeError(pc, "invalid opcode");
2667  return length;
2668  }
2669  }
2670  case kSimdPrefix: {
2671  uint32_t length;
2672  std::tie(opcode, length) =
2673  decoder->read_prefixed_opcode<ValidationTag>(pc);
2674  switch (opcode) {
2675  // clang-format off
2676  FOREACH_SIMD_0_OPERAND_OPCODE(DECLARE_OPCODE_CASE)
2677  return length;
2678  FOREACH_SIMD_1_OPERAND_OPCODE(DECLARE_OPCODE_CASE)
2679  if (sizeof...(ios) > 0) {
2680  SimdLaneImmediate lane_imm(decoder, pc + length, validate);
2681  (ios.SimdLane(lane_imm), ...);
2682  }
2683  return length + 1;
2684  FOREACH_SIMD_MEM_OPCODE(DECLARE_OPCODE_CASE) {
2685  MemoryAccessImmediate imm(decoder, pc + length, UINT32_MAX,
2686  validate);
2687  (ios.MemoryAccess(imm), ...);
2688  return length + imm.length;
2689  }
2690  FOREACH_SIMD_MEM_1_OPERAND_OPCODE(DECLARE_OPCODE_CASE) {
2691  MemoryAccessImmediate imm(
2692  decoder, pc + length, UINT32_MAX,
2693  validate);
2694  if (sizeof...(ios) > 0) {
2695  SimdLaneImmediate lane_imm(decoder,
2696  pc + length + imm.length, validate);
2697  (ios.MemoryAccess(imm), ...);
2698  (ios.SimdLane(lane_imm), ...);
2699  }
2700  // 1 more byte for lane index immediate.
2701  return length + imm.length + 1;
2702  }
2703  // clang-format on
2704  // Shuffles require a byte per lane, or 16 immediate bytes.
2705  case kExprS128Const:
2706  case kExprI8x16Shuffle:
2707  if (sizeof...(ios) > 0) {
2708  Simd128Immediate imm(decoder, pc + length, validate);
2709  (ios.S128Const(imm), ...);
2710  }
2711  return length + kSimd128Size;
2712  default:
2713  // This path is only possible if we are validating.
2714  V8_ASSUME(ValidationTag::validate);
2715  decoder->DecodeError(pc, "invalid SIMD opcode");
2716  return length;
2717  }
2718  }
2719  case kAtomicPrefix: {
2720  uint32_t length;
2721  std::tie(opcode, length) =
2722  decoder->read_prefixed_opcode<ValidationTag>(pc, "atomic_index");
2723  switch (opcode) {
2724  FOREACH_ATOMIC_OPCODE(DECLARE_OPCODE_CASE) {
2725  MemoryAccessImmediate imm(decoder, pc + length, UINT32_MAX,
2726  validate);
2727  (ios.MemoryAccess(imm), ...);
2728  return length + imm.length;
2729  }
2730  FOREACH_ATOMIC_0_OPERAND_OPCODE(DECLARE_OPCODE_CASE) {
2731  // One unused zero-byte.
2732  return length + 1;
2733  }
2734  case kExprStructAtomicGet:
2735  case kExprStructAtomicGetS:
2736  case kExprStructAtomicGetU:
2737  case kExprStructAtomicSet:
2738  case kExprStructAtomicAdd:
2739  case kExprStructAtomicSub:
2740  case kExprStructAtomicAnd:
2741  case kExprStructAtomicOr:
2742  case kExprStructAtomicXor:
2743  case kExprStructAtomicExchange:
2744  case kExprStructAtomicCompareExchange: {
2745  MemoryOrderImmediate memory_order(decoder, pc + length, validate);
2746  (ios.MemoryOrder(memory_order), ...);
2747  FieldImmediate field(decoder, pc + length + memory_order.length,
2748  validate);
2749  (ios.Field(field), ...);
2750  return length + memory_order.length + field.length;
2751  }
2752  case kExprArrayAtomicGet:
2753  case kExprArrayAtomicGetS:
2754  case kExprArrayAtomicGetU:
2755  case kExprArrayAtomicSet:
2756  case kExprArrayAtomicAdd:
2757  case kExprArrayAtomicSub:
2758  case kExprArrayAtomicAnd:
2759  case kExprArrayAtomicOr:
2760  case kExprArrayAtomicXor:
2761  case kExprArrayAtomicExchange:
2762  case kExprArrayAtomicCompareExchange: {
2763  MemoryOrderImmediate memory_order(decoder, pc + length, validate);
2764  (ios.MemoryOrder(memory_order), ...);
2765  ArrayIndexImmediate array(decoder, pc + length, validate);
2766  (ios.TypeIndex(array), ...);
2767  return length + memory_order.length + array.length;
2768  }
2769  default:
2770  // This path is only possible if we are validating.
2771  V8_ASSUME(ValidationTag::validate);
2772  decoder->DecodeError(pc, "invalid Atomics opcode");
2773  return length;
2774  }
2775  }
2776  case kGCPrefix: {
2777  uint32_t length;
2778  std::tie(opcode, length) =
2779  decoder->read_prefixed_opcode<ValidationTag>(pc, "gc_index");
2780  switch (opcode) {
2781  case kExprStructNew:
2782  case kExprStructNewDefault:
2783  case kExprRefGetDesc: {
2784  StructIndexImmediate imm(decoder, pc + length, validate);
2785  (ios.TypeIndex(imm), ...);
2786  return length + imm.length;
2787  }
2788  case kExprStructGet:
2789  case kExprStructGetS:
2790  case kExprStructGetU:
2791  case kExprStructSet: {
2792  FieldImmediate imm(decoder, pc + length, validate);
2793  (ios.Field(imm), ...);
2794  return length + imm.length;
2795  }
2796  case kExprArrayNew:
2797  case kExprArrayNewDefault:
2798  case kExprArrayGet:
2799  case kExprArrayGetS:
2800  case kExprArrayGetU:
2801  case kExprArraySet: {
2802  ArrayIndexImmediate imm(decoder, pc + length, validate);
2803  (ios.TypeIndex(imm), ...);
2804  return length + imm.length;
2805  }
2806  case kExprArrayNewFixed: {
2807  ArrayIndexImmediate array_imm(decoder, pc + length, validate);
2808  IndexImmediate length_imm(decoder, pc + length + array_imm.length,
2809  "array length", validate);
2810  (ios.TypeIndex(array_imm), ...);
2811  (ios.Length(length_imm), ...);
2812  return length + array_imm.length + length_imm.length;
2813  }
2814  case kExprArrayCopy: {
2815  ArrayIndexImmediate dst_imm(decoder, pc + length, validate);
2816  ArrayIndexImmediate src_imm(decoder, pc + length + dst_imm.length,
2817  validate);
2818  (ios.ArrayCopy(dst_imm, src_imm), ...);
2819  return length + dst_imm.length + src_imm.length;
2820  }
2821  case kExprArrayFill: {
2822  ArrayIndexImmediate imm(decoder, pc + length, validate);
2823  (ios.TypeIndex(imm), ...);
2824  return length + imm.length;
2825  }
2826  case kExprArrayNewData:
2827  case kExprArrayNewElem:
2828  case kExprArrayInitData:
2829  case kExprArrayInitElem: {
2830  ArrayIndexImmediate array_imm(decoder, pc + length, validate);
2831  IndexImmediate data_imm(decoder, pc + length + array_imm.length,
2832  "segment index", validate);
2833  (ios.TypeIndex(array_imm), ...);
2834  (ios.DataSegmentIndex(data_imm), ...);
2835  return length + array_imm.length + data_imm.length;
2836  }
2837  case kExprRefCast:
2838  case kExprRefCastNull:
2839  case kExprRefCastNop:
2840  case kExprRefCastDesc:
2841  case kExprRefCastDescNull:
2842  case kExprRefTest:
2843  case kExprRefTestNull: {
2844  HeapTypeImmediate imm(WasmEnabledFeatures::All(),
2845  decoder->detected_, decoder, pc + length,
2846  validate);
2847  (ios.HeapType(imm), ...);
2848  return length + imm.length;
2849  }
2850  case kExprBrOnCast:
2851  case kExprBrOnCastFail:
2852  case kExprBrOnCastDesc:
2853  case kExprBrOnCastDescFail: {
2854  BrOnCastImmediate flags_imm(decoder, pc + length, validate);
2855  BranchDepthImmediate branch(decoder, pc + length + flags_imm.length,
2856  validate);
2857  HeapTypeImmediate source_imm(
2858  WasmEnabledFeatures::All(), decoder->detected_, decoder,
2859  pc + length + flags_imm.length + branch.length, validate);
2860  HeapTypeImmediate target_imm(WasmEnabledFeatures::All(),
2861  decoder->detected_, decoder,
2862  pc + length + flags_imm.length +
2863  branch.length + source_imm.length,
2864  validate);
2865  (ios.BrOnCastFlags(flags_imm), ...);
2866  (ios.BranchDepth(branch), ...);
2867  // This code has grown historically (while the GC proposal's design
2868  // evolved), but it's convenient: for the text format, we want to
2869  // pretend that we have two ValueTypes; whereas the mjsunit
2870  // module builder format cares only about the encapsulated
2871  // HeapTypes (and the raw flags value, see callback above).
2872  (ios.ValueType(ValueType::RefMaybeNull(
2873  source_imm.type,
2874  flags_imm.flags.src_is_null ? kNullable : kNonNullable)),
2875  ...);
2876  (ios.ValueType(ValueType::RefMaybeNull(
2877  target_imm.type,
2878  flags_imm.flags.res_is_null ? kNullable : kNonNullable)),
2879  ...);
2880  return length + flags_imm.length + branch.length +
2881  source_imm.length + target_imm.length;
2882  }
2883  case kExprRefI31:
2884  case kExprRefI31Shared:
2885  case kExprI31GetS:
2886  case kExprI31GetU:
2887  case kExprAnyConvertExtern:
2888  case kExprExternConvertAny:
2889  case kExprArrayLen:
2890  return length;
2891  case kExprStringNewUtf8:
2892  case kExprStringNewUtf8Try:
2893  case kExprStringNewLossyUtf8:
2894  case kExprStringNewWtf8:
2895  case kExprStringEncodeUtf8:
2896  case kExprStringEncodeLossyUtf8:
2897  case kExprStringEncodeWtf8:
2898  case kExprStringViewWtf8EncodeUtf8:
2899  case kExprStringViewWtf8EncodeLossyUtf8:
2900  case kExprStringViewWtf8EncodeWtf8:
2901  case kExprStringNewWtf16:
2902  case kExprStringEncodeWtf16:
2903  case kExprStringViewWtf16Encode: {
2904  MemoryIndexImmediate imm(decoder, pc + length, validate);
2905  (ios.MemoryIndex(imm), ...);
2906  return length + imm.length;
2907  }
2908  case kExprStringConst: {
2909  StringConstImmediate imm(decoder, pc + length, validate);
2910  (ios.StringConst(imm), ...);
2911  return length + imm.length;
2912  }
2913  case kExprStringMeasureUtf8:
2914  case kExprStringMeasureWtf8:
2915  case kExprStringNewUtf8Array:
2916  case kExprStringNewUtf8ArrayTry:
2917  case kExprStringNewLossyUtf8Array:
2918  case kExprStringNewWtf8Array:
2919  case kExprStringEncodeUtf8Array:
2920  case kExprStringEncodeLossyUtf8Array:
2921  case kExprStringEncodeWtf8Array:
2922  case kExprStringMeasureWtf16:
2923  case kExprStringConcat:
2924  case kExprStringEq:
2925  case kExprStringIsUSVSequence:
2926  case kExprStringAsWtf8:
2927  case kExprStringViewWtf8Advance:
2928  case kExprStringViewWtf8Slice:
2929  case kExprStringAsWtf16:
2930  case kExprStringViewWtf16Length:
2931  case kExprStringViewWtf16GetCodeunit:
2932  case kExprStringViewWtf16Slice:
2933  case kExprStringAsIter:
2934  case kExprStringViewIterNext:
2935  case kExprStringViewIterAdvance:
2936  case kExprStringViewIterRewind:
2937  case kExprStringViewIterSlice:
2938  case kExprStringNewWtf16Array:
2939  case kExprStringEncodeWtf16Array:
2940  case kExprStringCompare:
2941  case kExprStringFromCodePoint:
2942  case kExprStringHash:
2943  return length;
2944  default:
2945  // This path is only possible if we are validating.
2946  V8_ASSUME(ValidationTag::validate);
2947  decoder->DecodeError(pc, "invalid gc opcode");
2948  return length;
2949  }
2950  }
2951 
2952  // clang-format off
2953  // Prefixed opcodes (already handled, included here for completeness of
2954  // switch)
2955  FOREACH_SIMD_OPCODE(DECLARE_OPCODE_CASE)
2956  FOREACH_NUMERIC_OPCODE(DECLARE_OPCODE_CASE)
2957  FOREACH_ATOMIC_OPCODE(DECLARE_OPCODE_CASE)
2958  FOREACH_ATOMIC_0_OPERAND_OPCODE(DECLARE_OPCODE_CASE)
2959  FOREACH_GC_OPCODE(DECLARE_OPCODE_CASE)
2960  FOREACH_ATOMIC_GC_OPCODE(DECLARE_OPCODE_CASE)
2961  FOREACH_ASMJS_COMPAT_OPCODE(DECLARE_OPCODE_CASE)
2962  UNREACHABLE();
2963  // clang-format on
2964 #undef DECLARE_OPCODE_CASE
2965  }
2966  // Invalid modules will reach this point.
2967  if (ValidationTag::validate) {
2968  decoder->DecodeError(pc, "invalid opcode");
2969  }
2970  return 1;
2971  }
2972 
2973  static constexpr ValidationTag validate = {};
2974 
2975  Zone* const zone_;
2976 
2977  ValueType* local_types_ = nullptr;
2978  uint32_t num_locals_ = 0;
2979 
2980  const WasmModule* module_;
2981  const WasmEnabledFeatures enabled_;
2982  WasmDetectedFeatures* detected_;
2983  const FunctionSig* sig_;
2984  bool is_shared_;
2985  const std::pair<uint32_t, uint32_t>* current_inst_trace_;
2986 };
2987 
2988 // Only call this in contexts where {current_code_reachable_and_ok_} is known to
2989 // hold.
2990 #define CALL_INTERFACE(name, ...) \
2991  do { \
2992  DCHECK(!control_.empty()); \
2993  DCHECK(current_code_reachable_and_ok_); \
2994  DCHECK_EQ(current_code_reachable_and_ok_, \
2995  this->ok() && control_.back().reachable()); \
2996  interface_.name(this, ##__VA_ARGS__); \
2997  } while (false)
2998 #define CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(name, ...) \
2999  do { \
3000  DCHECK(!control_.empty()); \
3001  DCHECK_EQ(current_code_reachable_and_ok_, \
3002  this->ok() && control_.back().reachable()); \
3003  if (V8_LIKELY(current_code_reachable_and_ok_)) { \
3004  interface_.name(this, ##__VA_ARGS__); \
3005  } \
3006  } while (false)
3007 #define CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_PARENT_REACHABLE(name, ...) \
3008  do { \
3009  DCHECK(!control_.empty()); \
3010  if (VALIDATE(this->ok()) && \
3011  (control_.size() == 1 || control_at(1)->reachable())) { \
3012  interface_.name(this, ##__VA_ARGS__); \
3013  } \
3014  } while (false)
3015 
3016 // An empty class used in place of a {base::SmallVector} for cases where the
3017 // content is not needed afterwards.
3018 // This is used for implementations which set {kUsesPoppedArgs} to {false}.
3019 class NoVector {
3020  public:
3021  // Construct from anything; {NoVector} is always empty.
3022  template <typename... Ts>
3023  explicit NoVector(Ts&&...) V8_NOEXCEPT {}
3024 
3025  constexpr std::nullptr_t data() const { return nullptr; }
3026 };
