3028 template <typename ValidationTag, typename Interface,
3029  DecodingMode decoding_mode = kFunctionBody>
3030 class WasmFullDecoder : public WasmDecoder<ValidationTag, decoding_mode> {
3031  using Value = typename Interface::Value;
3032  using Control = typename Interface::Control;
3033  using ArgVector = base::Vector<Value>;
3034  using PoppedArgVector =
3035  std::conditional_t<Interface::kUsesPoppedArgs,
3036  base::SmallVector<Value, 8>, NoVector>;
3037  using ReturnVector = base::SmallVector<Value, 2>;
3038 
3039  // All Value types should be trivially copyable for performance. We push, pop,
3040  // and store them in local variables.
3041  ASSERT_TRIVIALLY_COPYABLE(Value);
3042 
3043  public:
3044  template <typename... InterfaceArgs>
3045  WasmFullDecoder(Zone* zone, const WasmModule* module,
3046  WasmEnabledFeatures enabled, WasmDetectedFeatures* detected,
3047  const FunctionBody& body, InterfaceArgs&&... interface_args)
3048  : WasmDecoder<ValidationTag, decoding_mode>(
3049  zone, module, enabled, detected, body.sig, body.is_shared,
3050  body.start, body.end, body.offset),
3051  interface_(std::forward<InterfaceArgs>(interface_args)...),
3052  stack_(16, zone),
3053  control_(16, zone) {}
3054 
3055  ~WasmFullDecoder() {
3056  control_.Reset(this->zone_);
3057  stack_.Reset(this->zone_);
3058  locals_initializers_stack_.Reset(this->zone_);
3059  }
3060 
3061  Interface& interface() { return interface_; }
3062 
3063  void Decode() {
3064  DCHECK(stack_.empty());
3065  DCHECK(control_.empty());
3066  DCHECK_LE(this->pc_, this->end_);
3067  DCHECK_EQ(this->num_locals(), 0);
3068 
3069  locals_offset_ = this->pc_offset();
3070  uint32_t locals_length = this->DecodeLocals(this->pc());
3071  if (!VALIDATE(this->ok())) return TraceFailed();
3072  this->consume_bytes(locals_length);
3073  int non_defaultable = 0;
3074  uint32_t params_count =
3075  static_cast<uint32_t>(this->sig_->parameter_count());
3076  for (uint32_t index = params_count; index < this->num_locals(); index++) {
3077  if (!this->local_type(index).is_defaultable()) non_defaultable++;
3078  // We need this because reference locals are initialized with null, and
3079  // later we run a lowering step for null based on {detected_}.
3080  if (this->local_type(index).is_reference()) {
3081  this->detected_->add_reftypes();
3082  }
3083  }
3084  this->InitializeInitializedLocalsTracking(non_defaultable);
3085 
3086  // Cannot use CALL_INTERFACE_* macros because control is empty.
3087  interface().StartFunction(this);
3088  DecodeFunctionBody();
3089  // Decoding can fail even without validation, e.g. due to missing Liftoff
3090  // support.
3091  if (this->failed()) return TraceFailed();
3092 
3093  if (!VALIDATE(control_.empty())) {
3094  if (control_.size() > 1) {
3095  this->DecodeError(control_.back().pc(),
3096  "unterminated control structure");
3097  } else {
3098  this->DecodeError("function body must end with \"end\" opcode");
3099  }
3100  return TraceFailed();
3101  }
3102  // Cannot use CALL_INTERFACE_* macros because control is empty.
3103  interface().FinishFunction(this);
3104  if (this->failed()) return TraceFailed();
3105 
3106  DCHECK(stack_.empty());
3107  TRACE("wasm-decode ok\n\n");
3108  }
3109 
3110  void TraceFailed() {
3111  if (this->error_.offset()) {
3112  TRACE("wasm-error module+%-6d func+%d: %s\n\n", this->error_.offset(),
3113  this->GetBufferRelativeOffset(this->error_.offset()),
3114  this->error_.message().c_str());
3115  } else {
3116  TRACE("wasm-error: %s\n\n", this->error_.message().c_str());
3117  }
3118  }
3119 
3120  const char* SafeOpcodeNameAt(const uint8_t* pc) {
3121  if (!pc) return "<null>";
3122  if (pc >= this->end_) return "<end>";
3123  WasmOpcode opcode = static_cast<WasmOpcode>(*pc);
3124  if (!WasmOpcodes::IsPrefixOpcode(opcode)) {
3125  return WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(static_cast<WasmOpcode>(opcode));
3126  }
3127  opcode = this->template read_prefixed_opcode<Decoder::FullValidationTag>(pc)
3128  .first;
3129  return WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode);
3130  }
3131 
3132  WasmCodePosition position() const {
3133  int offset = static_cast<int>(this->pc_ - this->start_);
3134  DCHECK_EQ(this->pc_ - this->start_, offset); // overflows cannot happen
3135  return offset;
3136  }
3137 
3138  uint32_t control_depth() const {
3139  return static_cast<uint32_t>(control_.size());
3140  }
3141 
3142  Control* control_at(uint32_t depth) {
3143  DCHECK_GT(control_.size(), depth);
3144  return control_.end() - 1 - depth;
3145  }
3146 
3147  uint32_t stack_size() const { return stack_.size(); }
3148 
3149  Value* stack_value(uint32_t depth) const {
3150  DCHECK_LT(0, depth);
3151  DCHECK_GE(stack_.size(), depth);
3152  return stack_.end() - depth;
3153  }
3154 
3155  int32_t current_catch() const { return current_catch_; }
3156 
3157  uint32_t control_depth_of_current_catch() const {
3158  return control_depth() - 1 - current_catch();
3159  }
3160 
3161  uint32_t pc_relative_offset() const {
3162  return this->pc_offset() - locals_offset_;
3163  }
3164 
3165  bool is_local_initialized(uint32_t local_index) {
3166  DCHECK_GT(this->num_locals_, local_index);
3167  if (!has_nondefaultable_locals_) return true;
3168  return initialized_locals_[local_index];
3169  }
3170 
3171  void set_local_initialized(uint32_t local_index) {
3172  DCHECK_GT(this->num_locals_, local_index);
3173  if (!has_nondefaultable_locals_) return;
3174  // This implicitly covers defaultable locals too (which are always
3175  // initialized).
3176  if (is_local_initialized(local_index)) return;
3177  initialized_locals_[local_index] = true;
3178  locals_initializers_stack_.push(local_index);
3179  }
3180 
3181  uint32_t locals_initialization_stack_depth() const {
3182  return static_cast<uint32_t>(locals_initializers_stack_.size());
3183  }
3184 
3185  void RollbackLocalsInitialization(Control* c) {
3186  if (!has_nondefaultable_locals_) return;
3187  uint32_t previous_stack_height = c->init_stack_depth;
3188  while (locals_initializers_stack_.size() > previous_stack_height) {
3189  uint32_t local_index = locals_initializers_stack_.back();
3190  locals_initializers_stack_.pop();
3191  initialized_locals_[local_index] = false;
3192  }
3193  }
3194 
3195  void InitializeInitializedLocalsTracking(int non_defaultable_locals) {
3196  has_nondefaultable_locals_ = non_defaultable_locals > 0;
3197  if (!has_nondefaultable_locals_) return;
3198  initialized_locals_ =
3199  this->zone_->template AllocateArray<bool>(this->num_locals_);
3200  // Parameters are always initialized.
3201  const size_t num_params = this->sig_->parameter_count();
3202  std::fill_n(initialized_locals_, num_params, true);
3203  // Locals are initialized if they are defaultable.
3204  for (size_t i = num_params; i < this->num_locals_; i++) {
3205  initialized_locals_[i] = this->local_types_[i].is_defaultable();
3206  }
3207  DCHECK(locals_initializers_stack_.empty());
3208  locals_initializers_stack_.EnsureMoreCapacity(non_defaultable_locals,
3209  this->zone_);
3210  }
3211 
3212  void DecodeFunctionBody() {
3213  TRACE("wasm-decode %p...%p (module+%u, %d bytes)\n", this->start(),
3214  this->end(), this->pc_offset(),
3215  static_cast<int>(this->end() - this->start()));
3216 
3217  // Set up initial function block.
3218  {
3219  DCHECK(control_.empty());
3220  constexpr uint32_t kStackDepth = 0;
3221  constexpr uint32_t kInitStackDepth = 0;
3222  control_.EnsureMoreCapacity(1, this->zone_);
3223  control_.emplace_back(this->zone_, kControlBlock, kStackDepth,
3224  kInitStackDepth, this->pc_, kReachable);
3225  Control* c = &control_.back();
3226  if constexpr (decoding_mode == kFunctionBody) {
3227  InitMerge(&c->start_merge, 0, nullptr);
3228  InitMerge(&c->end_merge,
3229  static_cast<uint32_t>(this->sig_->return_count()),
3230  [this](uint32_t i) {
3231  return Value{this->pc_, this->sig_->GetReturn(i)};
3232  });
3233  } else {
3234  DCHECK_EQ(this->sig_->parameter_count(), 0);
3235  DCHECK_EQ(this->sig_->return_count(), 1);
3236  c->start_merge.arity = 0;
3237  c->end_merge.arity = 1;
3238  c->end_merge.vals.first = Value{this->pc_, this->sig_->GetReturn(0)};
3239  }
3240  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StartFunctionBody, c);
3241  }
3242 
3243  if (V8_LIKELY(this->current_inst_trace_->first == 0)) {
3244  // Decode the function body.
3245  while (this->pc_ < this->end_) {
3246  // Most operations only grow the stack by at least one element (unary
3247  // and binary operations, local.get, constants, ...). Thus check that
3248  // there is enough space for those operations centrally, and avoid any
3249  // bounds checks in those operations.
3250  stack_.EnsureMoreCapacity(1, this->zone_);
3251  uint8_t first_byte = *this->pc_;
3252  WasmOpcode opcode = static_cast<WasmOpcode>(first_byte);
3253  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(NextInstruction, opcode);
3254  int len;
3255  // Allowing two of the most common decoding functions to get inlined
3256  // appears to be the sweet spot.
3257  // Handling _all_ opcodes via a giant switch-statement has been tried
3258  // and found to be slower than calling through the handler table.
3259  if (opcode == kExprLocalGet) {
3260  len = WasmFullDecoder::DecodeLocalGet(this, opcode);
3261  } else if (opcode == kExprI32Const) {
3262  len = WasmFullDecoder::DecodeI32Const(this, opcode);
3263  } else {
3264  OpcodeHandler handler = GetOpcodeHandler(first_byte);
3265  len = (*handler)(this, opcode);
3266  }
3267  this->pc_ += len;
3268  }
3269 
3270  } else {
3271  // Decode the function body.
3272  while (this->pc_ < this->end_) {
3273  DCHECK(this->current_inst_trace_->first == 0 ||
3274  this->current_inst_trace_->first >= this->pc_offset());
3275  if (V8_UNLIKELY(this->current_inst_trace_->first ==
3276  this->pc_offset())) {
3277  TRACE("Emit trace at 0x%x with ID[0x%x]\n", this->pc_offset(),
3278  this->current_inst_trace_->second);
3279  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(TraceInstruction,
3280  this->current_inst_trace_->second);
3281  this->current_inst_trace_++;
3282  }
3283 
3284  // Most operations only grow the stack by at least one element (unary
3285  // and binary operations, local.get, constants, ...). Thus check that
3286  // there is enough space for those operations centrally, and avoid any
3287  // bounds checks in those operations.
3288  stack_.EnsureMoreCapacity(1, this->zone_);
3289  uint8_t first_byte = *this->pc_;
3290  WasmOpcode opcode = static_cast<WasmOpcode>(first_byte);
3291  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(NextInstruction, opcode);
3292  OpcodeHandler handler = GetOpcodeHandler(first_byte);
3293  int len = (*handler)(this, opcode);
3294  this->pc_ += len;
3295  }
3296  }
3297 
3298  // Even without validation, compilation could fail because of bailouts,
3299  // e.g., unsupported operations in Liftoff or the decoder for Wasm-in-JS
3300  // inlining. In those cases, {pc_} did not necessarily advance until {end_}.
3301  if (this->pc_ != this->end_) {
3302  // `DecodeError` is only available when validating, hence this guard.
3303  if constexpr (ValidationTag::validate) {
3304  this->DecodeError("Beyond end of code");
3305  }
3306  }
3307  }
3308 
3309  bool HasCatchAll(Control* block) const {
3310  DCHECK(block->is_try_table());
3311  return std::any_of(block->catch_cases.begin(), block->catch_cases.end(),
3312  [](const struct CatchCase& catch_case) {
3313  return catch_case.kind == kCatchAll ||
3314  catch_case.kind == kCatchAllRef;
3315  });
3316  }
3317 
3318  private:
3319  uint32_t locals_offset_ = 0;
3320  Interface interface_;
3321 
3322  // The value stack, stored as individual pointers for maximum performance.
3323  FastZoneVector<Value> stack_;
3324 
3325  // Indicates whether the local with the given index is currently initialized.
3326  // Entries for defaultable locals are meaningless; we have a byte for each
3327  // local because we expect that the effort required to densify this bit
3328  // vector would more than offset the memory savings.
3329  bool* initialized_locals_;
3330  // Keeps track of initializing assignments to non-defaultable locals that
3331  // happened, so they can be discarded at the end of the current block.
3332  // Contains no duplicates, so the size of this stack is bounded (and pre-
3333  // allocated) to the number of non-defaultable locals in the function.
3334  FastZoneVector<uint32_t> locals_initializers_stack_;
3335 
3336  // Control stack (blocks, loops, ifs, ...).
3337  FastZoneVector<Control> control_;
3338 
3339  // Controls whether code should be generated for the current block (basically
3340  // a cache for {ok() && control_.back().reachable()}).
3341  bool current_code_reachable_and_ok_ = true;
3342 
3343  // Performance optimization: bail out of any functions dealing with non-
3344  // defaultable locals early when there are no such locals anyway.
3345  bool has_nondefaultable_locals_ = true;
3346 
3347  // Depth of the current try block.
3348  int32_t current_catch_ = -1;
3349 
3350  static Value UnreachableValue(const uint8_t* pc) {
3351  return Value{pc, kWasmBottom};
3352  }
3353 
3354  void SetSucceedingCodeDynamicallyUnreachable() {
3355  Control* current = &control_.back();
3356  if (current->reachable()) {
3357  current->reachability = kSpecOnlyReachable;
3358  current_code_reachable_and_ok_ = false;
3359  }
3360  }
3361 
3362  // Mark that the current try-catch block might throw.
3363  // We only generate catch handlers for blocks that might throw.
3364  void MarkMightThrow() {
3365  if (!current_code_reachable_and_ok_ || current_catch() == -1) return;
3366  control_at(control_depth_of_current_catch())->might_throw = true;
3367  }

3369  V8_INLINE ValueType TableAddressType(const WasmTable* table) {
3370  return table->is_table64() ? kWasmI64 : kWasmI32;
3371  }
3372 
3373  V8_INLINE ValueType MemoryAddressType(const WasmMemory* memory) {
3374  return memory->is_memory64() ? kWasmI64 : kWasmI32;
3375  }

3377  V8_INLINE MemoryAccessImmediate
3378  MakeMemoryAccessImmediate(uint32_t pc_offset, uint32_t max_alignment) {
3379  return MemoryAccessImmediate(this, this->pc_ + pc_offset, max_alignment,
3380  validate);

3383 #ifdef DEBUG
3384  class TraceLine {
3385  public:
3386  explicit TraceLine(WasmFullDecoder* decoder) : decoder_(decoder) {
3387  WasmOpcode opcode = static_cast<WasmOpcode>(*decoder->pc());
3388  if (!WasmOpcodes::IsPrefixOpcode(opcode)) AppendOpcode(opcode);
3389  }
3390 
3391  void AppendOpcode(WasmOpcode opcode) {
3392  DCHECK(!WasmOpcodes::IsPrefixOpcode(opcode));
3393  Append(TRACE_INST_FORMAT, decoder_->startrel(decoder_->pc_),
3394  WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode));
3395  }
3396 
3397  ~TraceLine() {
3398  if (!v8_flags.trace_wasm_decoder) return;
3399  AppendStackState();
3400  PrintF("%.*s\n", len_, buffer_);
3401  }
3402 
3403  // Appends a formatted string.
3404  PRINTF_FORMAT(2, 3)
3405  void Append(const char* format, ...) {
3406  if (!v8_flags.trace_wasm_decoder) return;
3407  va_list va_args;
3408  va_start(va_args, format);
3409  size_t remaining_len = kMaxLen - len_;
3410  base::Vector<char> remaining_msg_space(buffer_ + len_, remaining_len);
3411  int len = base::VSNPrintF(remaining_msg_space, format, va_args);
3412  va_end(va_args);
3413  len_ += len < 0 ? remaining_len : len;
3414  }
3415 
3416  private:
3417  void AppendStackState() {
3418  DCHECK(v8_flags.trace_wasm_decoder);
3419  Append(" ");
3420  for (Control& c : decoder_->control_) {
3421  switch (c.kind) {
3422  case kControlIf:
3423  Append("I");
3424  break;
3425  case kControlBlock:
3426  Append("B");
3427  break;
3428  case kControlLoop:
3429  Append("L");
3430  break;
3431  case kControlTry:
3432  Append("T");
3433  break;
3434  case kControlTryTable:
3435  Append("T");
3436  break;
3437  case kControlIfElse:
3438  Append("E");
3439  break;
3440  case kControlTryCatch:
3441  Append("C");
3442  break;
3443  case kControlTryCatchAll:
3444  Append("A");
3445  break;
3446  }
3447  if (c.start_merge.arity) Append("%u-", c.start_merge.arity);
3448  Append("%u", c.end_merge.arity);
3449  if (!c.reachable()) Append("%c", c.unreachable() ? '*' : '#');
3450  }
3451  Append(" | ");
3452  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < decoder_->stack_.size(); ++i) {
3453  Value& val = decoder_->stack_[i];
3454  Append(" %c", val.type.short_name());
3455  }
3456  }

3458  static constexpr int kMaxLen = 512;
3459 
3460  char buffer_[kMaxLen];
3461  int len_ = 0;
3462  WasmFullDecoder* const decoder_;
3463  };
3464 #else
3465  class TraceLine {
3466  public:
3467  explicit TraceLine(WasmFullDecoder*) {}
3468 
3469  void AppendOpcode(WasmOpcode) {}
3470 
3471  PRINTF_FORMAT(2, 3)
3472  void Append(const char* format, ...) {}
3473  };
3474 #endif
3475 
3476 #define DECODE(name) \
3477  static int Decode##name(WasmFullDecoder* decoder, WasmOpcode opcode) { \
3478  TraceLine trace_msg(decoder); \
3479  return decoder->Decode##name##Impl(&trace_msg, opcode); \
3480  } \
3481  V8_INLINE int Decode##name##Impl(TraceLine* trace_msg, WasmOpcode opcode)
3482 
3483  DECODE(Nop) { return 1; }
3484 
3485  DECODE(NopForTestingUnsupportedInLiftoff) {
3486  if (!VALIDATE(v8_flags.enable_testing_opcode_in_wasm)) {
3487  this->DecodeError("Invalid opcode 0x%x", opcode);
3488  return 0;
3489  }
3490  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(NopForTestingUnsupportedInLiftoff);
3491  // Return {0} if we failed, to not advance the pc past the end.
3492  if (this->failed()) {
3493  DCHECK_EQ(this->pc_, this->end_);
3494  return 0;
3495  }
3496  return 1;
3497  }
3498 
3499 #define BUILD_SIMPLE_OPCODE(op, _, sig, ...) \
3500  DECODE(op) { return BuildSimpleOperator_##sig(kExpr##op); }
3501  FOREACH_SIMPLE_NON_CONST_OPCODE(BUILD_SIMPLE_OPCODE)
3502 #undef BUILD_SIMPLE_OPCODE
3503 
3504 #define BUILD_SIMPLE_OPCODE(op, _, sig, ...) \
3505  DECODE(op) { \
3506  if constexpr (decoding_mode == kConstantExpression) { \
3507  this->detected_->add_extended_const(); \
3508  } \
3509  return BuildSimpleOperator_##sig(kExpr##op); \
3510  }
3511  FOREACH_SIMPLE_EXTENDED_CONST_OPCODE(BUILD_SIMPLE_OPCODE)
3512 #undef BUILD_SIMPLE_OPCODE
3513 
3514  DECODE(Block) {
3515  BlockTypeImmediate imm(this->enabled_, this->detected_, this, this->pc_ + 1,
3516  validate);
3517  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm)) return 0;
3518  Control* block = PushControl(kControlBlock, imm);
3519  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(Block, block);
3520  return 1 + imm.length;
3521  }
3522 
3523  DECODE(Rethrow) {
3524  CHECK_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(legacy_eh);
3525  BranchDepthImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
3526  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm, control_.size())) return 0;
3527  Control* c = control_at(imm.depth);
3528  if (!VALIDATE(c->is_try_catchall() || c->is_try_catch())) {
3529  this->error("rethrow not targeting catch or catch-all");
3530  return 0;
3531  }
3532  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(Rethrow, c);
3533  MarkMightThrow();
3534  EndControl();
3535  return 1 + imm.length;
3536  }
3537 
3538  DECODE(Throw) {
3539  // Do not update the detected feature set. This instruction is used by both
3540  // the legacy and new EH proposals, so there is no way to know which
3541  // one the module is using from this instruction alone.
3542  TagIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
3543  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm)) return 0;
3544  if (imm.tag->sig->return_count() != 0) {
3545  this->DecodeError("tag signature %u has non-void return", imm.index);
3546  return 0;
3547  }
3548  PoppedArgVector args = PopArgs(imm.tag->ToFunctionSig());
3549  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(Throw, imm, args.data());
3550  MarkMightThrow();
3551  EndControl();
3552  return 1 + imm.length;
3553  }
3554 
3555  DECODE(Try) {
3556  CHECK_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(legacy_eh);
3557  if (!VALIDATE(!this->detected_->has_exnref() ||
3558  v8_flags.wasm_allow_mixed_eh_for_testing)) {
3559  this->DecodeError(
3560  "module uses a mix of legacy and new exception handling "
3561  "instructions");
3562  return 0;
3563  }
3564  BlockTypeImmediate imm(this->enabled_, this->detected_, this, this->pc_ + 1,
3565  validate);
3566  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm)) return 0;
3567  Control* try_block = PushControl(kControlTry, imm);
3568  try_block->previous_catch = current_catch_;
3569  current_catch_ = static_cast<int>(control_depth() - 1);
3570  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(Try, try_block);
3571  return 1 + imm.length;
3572  }
3573 
3574  DECODE(Catch) {
3575  CHECK_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(legacy_eh);
3576  // We must have already seen a "try" opcode, so we don't need to check for
3577  // mixed legacy / new EH instructions again.
3578  TagIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
3579  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm)) return 0;
3580  DCHECK(!control_.empty());
3581  Control* c = &control_.back();
3582  if (!VALIDATE(c->is_try())) {
3583  this->DecodeError("catch does not match a try");
3584  return 0;
3585  }
3586  if (!VALIDATE(!c->is_try_catchall())) {
3587  this->DecodeError("catch after catch-all for try");
3588  return 0;
3589  }
3590  FallThrough();
3591  c->kind = kControlTryCatch;
3592  stack_.shrink_to(c->stack_depth);
3593  c->reachability = control_at(1)->innerReachability();
3594  current_code_reachable_and_ok_ = VALIDATE(this->ok()) && c->reachable();
3595  RollbackLocalsInitialization(c);
3596  const WasmTagSig* sig = imm.tag->sig;
3597 
3598  // tags can have return values, so we have to check.
3599  if (sig->return_count() != 0) {
3600  this->DecodeError("tag signature %u has non-void return", imm.index);
3601  return 0;
3602  }
3603 
3604  stack_.EnsureMoreCapacity(static_cast<int>(sig->parameter_count()),
3605  this->zone_);
3606  for (ValueType type : sig->parameters()) Push(type);
3607  base::Vector<Value> values(stack_.begin() + c->stack_depth,
3608  sig->parameter_count());
3609  current_catch_ = c->previous_catch; // Pop try scope.
3610  // If there is a throwing instruction in `c`, generate the header for a
3611  // catch block. Otherwise, the catch block is unreachable.
3612  if (c->might_throw) {
3613  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_PARENT_REACHABLE(CatchException, imm, c, values);
3614  } else {
3615  SetSucceedingCodeDynamicallyUnreachable();
3616  }
3617  return 1 + imm.length;
3618  }
3619 
3620  DECODE(Delegate) {
3621  CHECK_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(legacy_eh);
3622  // We must have already seen a "try" opcode, so we don't need to check for
3623  // mixed legacy / new EH instructions again.
3624  BranchDepthImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
3625  // -1 because the current try block is not included in the count.
3626  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm, control_depth() - 1)) return 0;
3627  Control* c = &control_.back();
3628  if (!VALIDATE(c->is_incomplete_try())) {
3629  this->DecodeError("delegate does not match a try");
3630  return 0;
3631  }
3632  // +1 because the current try block is not included in the count.
3633  uint32_t target_depth = imm.depth + 1;
3634  while (target_depth < control_depth() - 1 &&
3635  (!control_at(target_depth)->is_try() ||
3636  control_at(target_depth)->is_try_catch() ||
3637  control_at(target_depth)->is_try_catchall())) {
3638  target_depth++;
3639  }
3640  FallThrough();
3641  if (c->might_throw) {
3642  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_PARENT_REACHABLE(Delegate, target_depth, c);
3643  // Delegate propagates the `might_throw` status to the delegated-to block.
3644  if (control_at(1)->reachable() && target_depth != control_depth() - 1) {
3645  control_at(target_depth)->might_throw = true;
3646  }
3647  }
3648  current_catch_ = c->previous_catch;
3649  EndControl();
3650  PopControl();
3651  return 1 + imm.length;
3652  }
3653 
3654  DECODE(CatchAll) {
3655  CHECK_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(legacy_eh);
3656  // We must have already seen a "try" opcode, so we don't need to check for
3657  // mixed legacy / new EH instructions again.
3658  DCHECK(!control_.empty());
3659  Control* c = &control_.back();
3660  if (!VALIDATE(c->is_try())) {
3661  this->DecodeError("catch-all does not match a try");
3662  return 0;
3663  }
3664  if (!VALIDATE(!c->is_try_catchall())) {
3665  this->error("catch-all already present for try");
3666  return 0;
3667  }
3668  FallThrough();
3669  c->kind = kControlTryCatchAll;
3670  c->reachability = control_at(1)->innerReachability();
3671  current_code_reachable_and_ok_ = VALIDATE(this->ok()) && c->reachable();
3672  RollbackLocalsInitialization(c);
3673  current_catch_ = c->previous_catch; // Pop try scope.
3674  // If there is a throwing instruction in `c`, generate the header for a
3675  // catch block. Otherwise, the catch block is unreachable.
3676  if (c->might_throw) {
3677  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_PARENT_REACHABLE(CatchAll, c);
3678  } else {
3679  SetSucceedingCodeDynamicallyUnreachable();
3680  }
3681  stack_.shrink_to(c->stack_depth);
3682  return 1;
3683  }
3684 
3685  DECODE(TryTable) {
3686  CHECK_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(exnref);
3687  if (!VALIDATE(!this->detected_->has_legacy_eh() ||
3688  v8_flags.wasm_allow_mixed_eh_for_testing)) {
3689  this->DecodeError(
3690  "module uses a mix of legacy and new exception handling "
3691  "instructions");
3692  return 0;
3693  }
3694  BlockTypeImmediate block_imm(this->enabled_, this->detected_, this,
3695  this->pc_ + 1, validate);
3696  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, block_imm)) return 0;
3697  Control* try_block = PushControl(kControlTryTable, block_imm);
3698  TryTableImmediate try_table_imm(this, this->pc_ + 1 + block_imm.length,
3699  validate);
3700  if (try_table_imm.table_count > 0) {
3701  try_block->previous_catch = current_catch_;
3702  current_catch_ = static_cast<int>(control_depth() - 1);
3703  }
3704  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 2, try_table_imm)) return 0;
3705  TryTableIterator<ValidationTag> try_table_iterator(this, try_table_imm);
3706  try_block->catch_cases = this->zone_->template AllocateVector<CatchCase>(
3707  try_table_imm.table_count);
3708  int i = 0;
3709  while (try_table_iterator.has_next()) {
3710  CatchCase catch_case = try_table_iterator.next();
3711  if (!VALIDATE(catch_case.kind <= kLastCatchKind)) {
3712  this->DecodeError("invalid catch kind in try table");
3713  return 0;
3714  }
3715  if ((catch_case.kind == kCatch || catch_case.kind == kCatchRef)) {
3716  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_, catch_case.maybe_tag.tag_imm)) {
3717  return 0;
3718  }
3719  const WasmTagSig* sig = catch_case.maybe_tag.tag_imm.tag->sig;
3720  if (sig->return_count() != 0) {
3721  // tags can have return values, so we have to check.
3722  this->DecodeError("tag signature %u has non-void return",
3723  catch_case.maybe_tag.tag_imm.index);
3724  return 0;
3725  }
3726  }
3727  catch_case.br_imm.depth += 1;
3728  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_, catch_case.br_imm, control_.size())) {
3729  return 0;
3730  }
3731 
3732  uint32_t stack_size = stack_.size();
3733  uint32_t push_count = 0;
3734  if (catch_case.kind == kCatch || catch_case.kind == kCatchRef) {
3735  const WasmTagSig* sig = catch_case.maybe_tag.tag_imm.tag->sig;
3736  stack_.EnsureMoreCapacity(static_cast<int>(sig->parameter_count()),
3737  this->zone_);
3738  for (ValueType type : sig->parameters()) Push(type);
3739  push_count += sig->parameter_count();
3740  }
3741  if (catch_case.kind == kCatchRef || catch_case.kind == kCatchAllRef) {
3742  stack_.EnsureMoreCapacity(1, this->zone_);
3743  Push(ValueType::Ref(kWasmExnRef));
3744  push_count += 1;
3745  }
3746  Control* target = control_at(catch_case.br_imm.depth);
3747  if (!VALIDATE(push_count == target->br_merge()->arity)) {
3748  this->DecodeError(
3749  "catch kind generates %d operand%s, target block expects %d",
3750  push_count, push_count != 1 ? "s" : "", target->br_merge()->arity);
3751  return 0;
3752  }
3753  if (!VALIDATE(
3754  (TypeCheckBranch<PushBranchValues::kYes, RewriteStackTypes::kNo>(
3755  target)))) {
3756  return 0;
3757  }
3758  stack_.shrink_to(stack_size);
3759  DCHECK_LT(i, try_table_imm.table_count);
3760  try_block->catch_cases[i] = catch_case;
3761  ++i;
3762  }
3763  uint32_t try_table_length = try_table_iterator.length();
3764  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(TryTable, try_block);
3765  return 1 + block_imm.length + try_table_length;
3766  }
3767 
3768  DECODE(ThrowRef) {
3769  CHECK_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(exnref);
3770  if (!VALIDATE(!this->detected_->has_legacy_eh() ||
3771  v8_flags.wasm_allow_mixed_eh_for_testing)) {
3772  this->DecodeError(
3773  "module uses a mix of legacy and new exception handling "
3774  "instructions");
3775  return 0;
3776  }
3777  Value value = Pop(kWasmExnRef);
3778  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ThrowRef, &value);
3779  MarkMightThrow();
3780  EndControl();
3781  return 1;
3782  }
3783 
3784  DECODE(BrOnNull) {
3785  this->detected_->add_typed_funcref();
3786  BranchDepthImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
3787  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm, control_.size())) return 0;
3788  Value ref_object = Pop();
3789  Control* c = control_at(imm.depth);
3790  if (!VALIDATE(
3791  (TypeCheckBranch<PushBranchValues::kYes, RewriteStackTypes::kYes>(
3792  c)))) {
3793  return 0;
3794  }
3795  switch (ref_object.type.kind()) {
3796  case kBottom:
3797  // We are in a polymorphic stack. Leave the stack as it is.
3798  DCHECK(!current_code_reachable_and_ok_);
3799  [[fallthrough]];
3800  case kRef:
3801  // For a non-nullable value, we won't take the branch, and can leave
3802  // the stack as it is.
3803  Push(ref_object);
3804  break;
3805  case kRefNull: {
3806  Value* result = Push(ValueType::Ref(ref_object.type.heap_type()));
3807  // The result of br_on_null has the same value as the argument (but a
3808  // non-nullable type).
3809  if (V8_LIKELY(current_code_reachable_and_ok_)) {
3810  CALL_INTERFACE(BrOnNull, ref_object, imm.depth, false, result);
3811  c->br_merge()->reached = true;
3812  }
3813  break;
3814  }
3815  default:
3816  PopTypeError(0, ref_object, "object reference");
3817  return 0;
3818  }
3819  return 1 + imm.length;
3820  }
3821 
3822  DECODE(BrOnNonNull) {
3823  this->detected_->add_typed_funcref();
3824  BranchDepthImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
3825  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm, control_.size())) return 0;
3826  Value ref_object = Pop();
3827  if (!VALIDATE(ref_object.type.is_object_reference() ||
3828  ref_object.type.is_bottom())) {
3829  PopTypeError(
3830  0, ref_object,
3831  "subtype of ((ref null any), (ref null extern) or (ref null func))");
3832  return 0;
3833  }
3834  // Typechecking the branch and creating the branch merges requires the
3835  // non-null value on the stack, so we push it temporarily.
3836  Value* value_on_branch = Push(ref_object.type.AsNonNull());
3837  Control* c = control_at(imm.depth);
3838  if (!VALIDATE(
3839  (TypeCheckBranch<PushBranchValues::kYes, RewriteStackTypes::kYes>(
3840  c)))) {
3841  return 0;
3842  }
3843  switch (ref_object.type.kind()) {
3844  case kBottom:
3845  // We are in unreachable code. Do nothing.
3846  DCHECK(!current_code_reachable_and_ok_);
3847  break;
3848  case kRef:
3849  // For a non-nullable value, we always take the branch.
3850  if (V8_LIKELY(current_code_reachable_and_ok_)) {
3851  CALL_INTERFACE(Forward, ref_object, value_on_branch);
3852  CALL_INTERFACE(BrOrRet, imm.depth);
3853  // We know that the following code is not reachable, but according
3854  // to the spec it technically is. Set it to spec-only reachable.
3855  SetSucceedingCodeDynamicallyUnreachable();
3856  c->br_merge()->reached = true;
3857  }
3858  break;
3859  case kRefNull: {
3860  if (V8_LIKELY(current_code_reachable_and_ok_)) {
3861  CALL_INTERFACE(BrOnNonNull, ref_object, value_on_branch, imm.depth,
3862  true);
3863  c->br_merge()->reached = true;
3864  }
3865  break;
3866  }
3867  default:
3868  PopTypeError(0, ref_object, "object reference");
3869  return 0;
3870  }
3871  Drop(*value_on_branch);
3872  return 1 + imm.length;
3873  }
3874 
3875  DECODE(Loop) {
3876  BlockTypeImmediate imm(this->enabled_, this->detected_, this, this->pc_ + 1,
3877  validate);
3878  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm)) return 0;
3879  Control* block = PushControl(kControlLoop, imm);
3880  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(Loop, block);
3881  // Loops have a merge point at block entry, hence push the merge values
3882  // (Phis in case of TurboFan) after calling the interface.
3883  // TODO(clemensb): Can we skip this (and the related PushMergeValues in
3884  // PopControl) for Liftoff?
3885  PushMergeValues(block, &block->start_merge);
3886  return 1 + imm.length;
3887  }
3888 
3889  DECODE(If) {
3890  BlockTypeImmediate imm(this->enabled_, this->detected_, this, this->pc_ + 1,
3891  validate);
3892  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm)) return 0;
3893  Value cond = Pop(kWasmI32);
3894  Control* if_block = PushControl(kControlIf, imm);
3895  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(If, cond, if_block);
3896  return 1 + imm.length;
3897  }
3898 
3899  DECODE(Else) {
3900  DCHECK(!control_.empty());
3901  Control* c = &control_.back();
3902  if (!VALIDATE(c->is_if())) {
3903  this->DecodeError("else does not match an if");
3904  return 0;
3905  }
3906  if (!VALIDATE(c->is_onearmed_if())) {
3907  this->DecodeError("else already present for if");
3908  return 0;
3909  }
3910  if (!VALIDATE(TypeCheckFallThru())) return 0;
3911  c->kind = kControlIfElse;
3912  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_PARENT_REACHABLE(Else, c);
3913  if (c->reachable()) c->end_merge.reached = true;
3914  RollbackLocalsInitialization(c);
3915  PushMergeValues(c, &c->start_merge);
3916  c->reachability = control_at(1)->innerReachability();
3917  current_code_reachable_and_ok_ = VALIDATE(this->ok()) && c->reachable();
3918  return 1;
3919  }
3920 
3921  DECODE(End) {
3922  DCHECK(!control_.empty());
3923  if constexpr (decoding_mode == kFunctionBody) {
3924  Control* c = &control_.back();
3925  if (c->is_incomplete_try()) {
3926  // Catch-less try, fall through to the implicit catch-all.
3927  c->kind = kControlTryCatch;
3928  current_catch_ = c->previous_catch; // Pop try scope.
3929  }
3930  if (c->is_try_catch()) {
3931  // Emulate catch-all + re-throw.
3932  FallThrough();
3933  c->reachability = control_at(1)->innerReachability();
3934  current_code_reachable_and_ok_ = VALIDATE(this->ok()) && c->reachable();
3935  // Cache `c->might_throw` so we can access it safely after `c`'s
3936  // destructor is called in `PopContol()`.
3937  bool might_throw = c->might_throw;
3938  if (might_throw) {
3939  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_PARENT_REACHABLE(CatchAll, c);
3940  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(Rethrow, c);
3941  }
3942  EndControl();
3943  PopControl();
3944  // We must mark the parent catch block as `might_throw`, since this
3945  // conceptually rethrows. Note that we do this regardless of whether
3946  // the code at this point is reachable.
3947  if (might_throw && current_catch() != -1) {
3948  control_at(control_depth_of_current_catch())->might_throw = true;
3949  }
3950  return 1;
3951  }
3952  if (c->is_onearmed_if()) {
3953  if (!VALIDATE(TypeCheckOneArmedIf(c))) return 0;
3954  }
3955  if (c->is_try_table()) {
3956  // "Pop" the {current_catch_} index. We did not push it if the block has
3957  // no handler, so also skip it here in this case.
3958  if (c->catch_cases.size() > 0) {
3959  current_catch_ = c->previous_catch;
3960  }
3961  FallThrough();
3962  // Temporarily set the reachability for the catch handlers, and restore
3963  // it before we actually exit the try block.
3964  Reachability reachability_at_end = c->reachability;
3965  c->reachability = control_at(1)->innerReachability();
3966  current_code_reachable_and_ok_ = VALIDATE(this->ok()) && c->reachable();
3967  for (CatchCase& catch_case : c->catch_cases) {
3968  uint32_t stack_size = stack_.size();
3969  size_t push_count = 0;
3970  if (catch_case.kind == kCatch || catch_case.kind == kCatchRef) {
3971  const WasmTagSig* sig = catch_case.maybe_tag.tag_imm.tag->sig;
3972  stack_.EnsureMoreCapacity(static_cast<int>(sig->parameter_count()),
3973  this->zone_);
3974  for (ValueType type : sig->parameters()) Push(type);
3975  push_count = sig->parameter_count();
3976  }
3977  if (catch_case.kind == kCatchRef || catch_case.kind == kCatchAllRef) {
3978  stack_.EnsureMoreCapacity(1, this->zone_);
3979  Push(ValueType::Ref(kWasmExnRef));
3980  push_count += 1;
3981  }
3982  base::Vector<Value> values(
3983  stack_.begin() + stack_.size() - push_count, push_count);
3984  if (c->might_throw) {
3985  // Already type checked on block entry.
3986  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_PARENT_REACHABLE(CatchCase, c, catch_case,
3987  values);
3988  if (current_code_reachable_and_ok_) {
3989  Control* target = control_at(catch_case.br_imm.depth);
3990  target->br_merge()->reached = true;
3991  }
3992  }
3993  stack_.shrink_to(stack_size);
3994  if (catch_case.kind == kCatchAll || catch_case.kind == kCatchAllRef) {
3995  break;
3996  }
3997  }
3998  c->reachability = reachability_at_end;
3999  // If there is no catch-all case, we must mark the parent catch block as
4000  // `might_throw`, since this conceptually rethrows. Note that we do this
4001  // regardless of whether the code at this point is reachable.
4002  if (c->might_throw && !HasCatchAll(c) && current_catch() != -1) {
4003  control_at(control_depth_of_current_catch())->might_throw = true;
4004  }
4005  EndControl();
4006  PopControl();
4007  return 1;
4008  }
4009  }
4010 
4011  if (control_.size() == 1) {
4012  // We need to call this first because the interface might set
4013  // {this->end_}, making the next check pass.
4014  DoReturn<kStrictCounting, decoding_mode == kFunctionBody
4015  ? kFallthroughMerge
4016  : kInitExprMerge>();
4017  // If at the last (implicit) control, check we are at end.
4018  if (!VALIDATE(this->pc_ + 1 == this->end_)) {
4019  this->DecodeError(this->pc_ + 1, "trailing code after function end");
4020  return 0;
4021  }
4022  // The result of the block is the return value.
4023  trace_msg->Append("\n" TRACE_INST_FORMAT, startrel(this->pc_),
4024  "(implicit) return");
4025  control_.pop();
4026  return 1;
4027  }
4028 
4029  if (!VALIDATE(TypeCheckFallThru())) return 0;
4030  PopControl();
4031  return 1;
4032  }
4033 
4034  DECODE(Select) {
4035  auto [tval, fval, cond] = Pop(kWasmBottom, kWasmBottom, kWasmI32);
4036  ValueType result_type = tval.type;
4037  if (result_type == kWasmBottom) {
4038  result_type = fval.type;
4039  } else {
4040  ValidateStackValue(1, fval, result_type);
4041  }
4042  if (!VALIDATE(!result_type.is_reference())) {
4043  this->DecodeError(
4044  "select without type is only valid for value type inputs");
4045  return 0;
4046  }
4047  Value* result = Push(result_type);
4048  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(Select, cond, fval, tval, result);
4049  return 1;
4050  }
4051 
4052  DECODE(SelectWithType) {
4053  this->detected_->add_reftypes();
4054  SelectTypeImmediate imm(this->enabled_, this->detected_, this,
4055  this->pc_ + 1, validate);
4056  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm)) return 0;
4057  auto [tval, fval, cond] = Pop(imm.type, imm.type, kWasmI32);
4058  Value* result = Push(imm.type);
4059  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(Select, cond, fval, tval, result);
4060  return 1 + imm.length;
4061  }
4062 
4063  DECODE(Br) {
4064  BranchDepthImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
4065  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm, control_.size())) return 0;
4066  Control* c = control_at(imm.depth);
4067  if (!VALIDATE(
4068  (TypeCheckBranch<PushBranchValues::kNo, RewriteStackTypes::kNo>(
4069  c)))) {
4070  return 0;
4071  }
4072  if (V8_LIKELY(current_code_reachable_and_ok_)) {
4073  CALL_INTERFACE(BrOrRet, imm.depth);
4074  c->br_merge()->reached = true;
4075  }
4076  EndControl();
4077  return 1 + imm.length;
4078  }
4079 
4080  DECODE(BrIf) {
4081  BranchDepthImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
4082  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm, control_.size())) return 0;
4083  Value cond = Pop(kWasmI32);
4084  Control* c = control_at(imm.depth);
4085  if (!VALIDATE(
4086  (TypeCheckBranch<PushBranchValues::kYes, RewriteStackTypes::kYes>(
4087  c)))) {
4088  return 0;
4089  }
4090  if (V8_LIKELY(current_code_reachable_and_ok_)) {
4091  CALL_INTERFACE(BrIf, cond, imm.depth);
4092  c->br_merge()->reached = true;
4093  }
4094  return 1 + imm.length;
4095  }
4096 
4097  DECODE(BrTable) {
4098  BranchTableImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
4099  BranchTableIterator<ValidationTag> iterator(this, imm);
4100  Value key = Pop(kWasmI32);
4101  if (!VALIDATE(this->ok())) return 0;
4102  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm)) return 0;
4103 
4104  // Cache the branch targets during the iteration, so that we can set
4105  // all branch targets as reachable after the {CALL_INTERFACE} call.
4106  SmallZoneVector<bool, 32> br_targets(control_.size(), this->zone());
4107  std::uninitialized_fill(br_targets.begin(), br_targets.end(), false);
4108 
4109  uint32_t arity = 0;
4110 
4111  while (iterator.has_next()) {
4112  const uint32_t index = iterator.cur_index();
4113  const uint8_t* pos = iterator.pc();
4114  const uint32_t target = iterator.next();
4115  if (!VALIDATE(target < control_depth())) {
4116  this->DecodeError(pos, "invalid branch depth: %u", target);
4117  return 0;
4118  }
4119  // Avoid redundant branch target checks.
4120  if (br_targets[target]) continue;
4121  br_targets[target] = true;
4122 
4123  if (ValidationTag::validate) {
4124  if (index == 0) {
4125  arity = control_at(target)->br_merge()->arity;
4126  } else if (!VALIDATE(control_at(target)->br_merge()->arity == arity)) {
4127  this->DecodeError(
4128  pos, "br_table: label arity inconsistent with previous arity %d",
4129  arity);
4130  return 0;
4131  }
4132  if (!VALIDATE(
4133  (TypeCheckBranch<PushBranchValues::kNo, RewriteStackTypes::kNo>(
4134  control_at(target))))) {
4135  return 0;
4136  }
4137  }
4138  }
4139 
4140  if (V8_LIKELY(current_code_reachable_and_ok_)) {
4141  CALL_INTERFACE(BrTable, imm, key);
4142 
4143  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < control_depth(); ++i) {
4144  control_at(i)->br_merge()->reached |= br_targets[i];
4145  }
4146  }
4147  EndControl();
4148  return 1 + iterator.length();
4149  }
4150 
4151  DECODE(Return) {
4152  return DoReturn<kNonStrictCounting, kReturnMerge>() ? 1 : 0;
4153  }
4154 
4155  DECODE(Unreachable) {
4156  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(Trap, TrapReason::kTrapUnreachable);
4157  EndControl();
4158  return 1;
4159  }

4189  DECODE(RefNull) {
4190  this->detected_->add_reftypes();
4191  HeapTypeImmediate imm(this->enabled_, this->detected_, this, this->pc_ + 1,
4192  validate);
4193  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm)) return 0;
4194  if (!VALIDATE(!this->enabled_.has_stringref() ||
4195  !imm.type.is_string_view())) {
4196  this->DecodeError(this->pc_ + 1, "cannot create null string view");
4197  return 0;
4198  }
4199  ValueType type = ValueType::RefNull(imm.type);
4200  if (type.has_index()) type = type.AsExactIfEnabled(this->enabled_);
4201  Value* value = Push(type);
4202  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(RefNull, type, value);
4203  return 1 + imm.length;

4206  DECODE(RefIsNull) {
4207  this->detected_->add_reftypes();
4208  Value value = Pop();
4209  Value* result = Push(kWasmI32);
4210  switch (value.type.kind()) {
4211  case kRefNull:
4212  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(UnOp, kExprRefIsNull, value, result);
4213  return 1;
4214  case kBottom:
4215  // We are in unreachable code, the return value does not matter.
4216  case kRef:
4217  // For non-nullable references, the result is always false.
4218  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(Drop);
4219  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(I32Const, result, 0);
4220  return 1;
4221  default:
4222  if constexpr (!ValidationTag::validate) UNREACHABLE();
4223  PopTypeError(0, value, "reference type");
4224  return 0;
4225  }
4226  }

4228  DECODE(RefFunc) {
4229  this->detected_->add_reftypes();
4230  IndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, "function index", validate);
4231  if (!this->ValidateFunction(this->pc_ + 1, imm)) return 0;
4232  ModuleTypeIndex index = this->module_->functions[imm.index].sig_index;
4233  const TypeDefinition& type_def = this->module_->type(index);
4234  Value* value =
4235  Push(ValueType::Ref(index, type_def.is_shared, RefTypeKind::kFunction)
4236  .AsExactIfEnabled(this->enabled_));
4237  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(RefFunc, imm.index, value);
4238  return 1 + imm.length;
4239  }

4241  DECODE(RefAsNonNull) {
4242  this->detected_->add_typed_funcref();
4243  Value value = Pop();
4244  switch (value.type.kind()) {
4245  case kBottom:
4246  // We are in unreachable code. Forward the bottom value.
4247  case kRef:
4248  // A non-nullable value can remain as-is.
4249  Push(value);
4250  return 1;
4251  case kRefNull: {
4252  Value* result = Push(ValueType::Ref(value.type.heap_type()));
4253  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(RefAsNonNull, value, result);
4254  return 1;
4255  }
4256  default:
4257  if constexpr (!ValidationTag::validate) UNREACHABLE();
4258  PopTypeError(0, value, "reference type");
4259  return 0;
4260  }
4261  }

4461  DECODE(RefEq) {
4462  this->detected_->add_gc();
4463  Value rhs = Pop();
4464  Value lhs = Pop();
4465  if (!VALIDATE(
4466  IsSubtypeOf(lhs.type.AsNonShared(), kWasmEqRef, this->module_) ||
4467  control_.back().unreachable())) {
4468  this->DecodeError(this->pc_,
4469  "ref.eq[0] expected either eqref or (ref null shared "
4470  "eq), found %s of type %s",
4471  SafeOpcodeNameAt(lhs.pc()), lhs.type.name().c_str());
4472  return 0;
4473  }
4474  if (!VALIDATE(
4475  IsSubtypeOf(rhs.type.AsNonShared(), kWasmEqRef, this->module_) ||
4476  control_.back().unreachable())) {
4477  this->DecodeError(this->pc_,
4478  "ref.eq[1] expected either eqref or (ref null shared "
4479  "eq), found %s of type %s",
4480  SafeOpcodeNameAt(rhs.pc()), rhs.type.name().c_str());
4481  return 0;
4482  }
4483  if (!VALIDATE(lhs.type.is_shared() == rhs.type.is_shared() ||
4484  control_.back().unreachable())) {
4485  this->DecodeError(this->pc_,
4486  "ref.eq: sharedness of both operands must match");
4487  return 0;
4488  }
4489  Value* result = Push(kWasmI32);
4490  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(BinOp, kExprRefEq, lhs, rhs, result);
4491  return 1;
4492  }
4493 
4494  bool IsSubtypeVec(base::Vector<const ValueType> subtypes,
4495  base::Vector<const ValueType> supertypes) {
4496  if (subtypes.size() != supertypes.size()) return false;
4497 
4498  auto super_it = supertypes.begin();
4499  for (ValueType subtype : subtypes) {
4500  if (!IsSubtypeOf(subtype, *super_it++, this->module_)) return false;
4501  }
4502  return true;
4503  }

4505  DECODE(ContNew) {
4506  CHECK_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(wasmfx);
4507  ContIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
4508  if (!this->ValidateCont(this->pc_ + 1, imm)) return 0;
4509 
4510  // Pop a function type.
4511  Value func_ref =
4512  Pop(ValueType::RefNull(imm.cont_type->contfun_typeindex(), imm.shared,
4513  RefTypeKind::kFunction));
4514 
4515  // Push a continuation type.
4516  Value* value = Push(ValueType::Ref(imm.heap_type()));
4517  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ContNew, imm, func_ref, value);
4518  return 1 + imm.length;
4519  }

4521  DECODE(ContBind) {
4522  CHECK_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(wasmfx);
4523 
4524  ContIndexImmediate orig_cont_imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
4525  if (!this->ValidateCont(this->pc_ + 1, orig_cont_imm)) return 0;
4526  ContIndexImmediate new_cont_imm(this, this->pc_ + orig_cont_imm.length + 1,
4527  validate);
4528  if (!this->ValidateCont(this->pc_ + 1, new_cont_imm)) return 0;
4529 
4530  const FunctionSig* orig_cont_sig =
4531  this->module_->signature(orig_cont_imm.cont_type->contfun_typeindex());
4532  const FunctionSig* new_cont_sig =
4533  this->module_->signature(new_cont_imm.cont_type->contfun_typeindex());
4534 
4535  if (!VALIDATE(
4536  IsSubtypeVec(orig_cont_sig->returns(), new_cont_sig->returns()))) {
4537  this->DecodeError("expecting returns of %d to match returns of %d",
4538  orig_cont_imm.index.index, new_cont_imm.index.index);
4539  return 0;
4540  }
4541 
4542  int delta = static_cast<int>(orig_cont_sig->parameters().size()) -
4543  static_cast<int>(new_cont_sig->parameters().size());
4544  if (!VALIDATE(delta >= 0)) {
4545  this->DecodeError(
4546  "source cont type %d has fewer parameters than target %d",
4547  orig_cont_imm.index.index, new_cont_imm.index.index);
4548  return 0;
4549  }
4550 
4551  const base::Vector<const ValueType> sig_parameters =
4552  orig_cont_sig->parameters();
4553  const base::Vector<const ValueType> new_sig_parameters =
4554  new_cont_sig->parameters();
4555 
4556  if (!VALIDATE(IsSubtypeVec(new_sig_parameters,
4557  sig_parameters + static_cast<size_t>(delta)))) {
4558  this->DecodeError(
4559  "parameters of new continuation %d should be subtypes of parameters "
4560  "of input continuation %d",
4561  new_cont_imm.index.index, orig_cont_imm.index.index);
4562  }
4563 
4564  Value orig_cont = Pop(ValueType::RefNull(orig_cont_imm.heap_type()));
4565  PoppedArgVector args = PopSomeArgs(orig_cont_sig, delta);
4566  Value* new_cont = Push(ValueType::Ref(new_cont_imm.heap_type()));
4567  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ContBind, orig_cont_imm, orig_cont,
4568  args.data(), new_cont_imm, new_cont);
4569  return 1 + orig_cont_imm.length + new_cont_imm.length;
4570  }
4571 
4572  V8_INLINE int DecodeEffectHandlerTable(
4573  EffectHandlerTableImmediate& handler_table_imm,
4574  base::Vector<HandlerCase>& handlers) {
4575  EffectHandlerTableIterator<ValidationTag> handle_iterator(
4576  this, handler_table_imm);
4577  int i = 0;
4578  while (handle_iterator.has_next()) {
4579  HandlerCase handler = handle_iterator.next();
4580 
4581  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_, handler.tag)) {
4582  return -1;
4583  }
4584  handlers[i] = handler;
4585 
4586  uint32_t stack_size = stack_.size();
4587  uint32_t push_count = 0;
4588  if (handler.kind == kOnSuspend) {
4589  const WasmTagSig* sig = handler.tag.tag->sig;
4590  stack_.EnsureMoreCapacity(static_cast<int>(sig->parameter_count()),
4591  this->zone_);
4592  for (ValueType type : sig->parameters()) Push(type);
4593  push_count += sig->parameter_count();
4594 
4595  if (!VALIDATE((this->Validate(this->pc_, handler.maybe_depth.br,
4596  control_depth())))) {
4597  return -1;
4598  }
4599  Control* target = control_at(handler.maybe_depth.br.depth);
4600  if (!VALIDATE(push_count == target->br_merge()->arity)) {
4601  this->DecodeError(
4602  "handler generates %d operand%s, target block returns %d",
4603  push_count, push_count != 1 ? "s" : "",
4604  target->br_merge()->arity);
4605  return -1;
4606  }
4607  if (!VALIDATE((
4608  TypeCheckBranch<PushBranchValues::kYes, RewriteStackTypes::kNo>(
4609  target)))) {
4610  return -1;
4611  }
4612  stack_.shrink_to(stack_size);
4613  DCHECK_LT(i, handler_table_imm.table_count);
4614  } else if (handler.kind != kSwitch) {
4615  this->DecodeError("invalid handler kind %d", handler.kind);
4616  return -1;
4617  }
4618  i++;
4619  }
4620  return handle_iterator.length();
4621  }
4622 
4623  DECODE(Resume) {
4624  CHECK_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(wasmfx);
4625  ContIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
4626  if (!this->ValidateCont(this->pc_ + 1, imm)) return 0;
4627 
4628  Pop(ValueType::RefNull(imm.heap_type()));
4629 
4630  EffectHandlerTableImmediate handler_table_imm(
4631  this, this->pc_ + 1 + imm.length, validate);
4632  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + imm.length + 1, handler_table_imm))
4633  return 0;
4634 
4635  base::Vector<HandlerCase> handlers =
4636  this->zone_->template AllocateVector<HandlerCase>(
4637  handler_table_imm.table_count);
4638 
4639  int table_length = DecodeEffectHandlerTable(handler_table_imm, handlers);
4640  if (table_length < 0) return 0;
4641 
4642  // Continuations are function-like values; check the args and returns.
4643  const FunctionSig* contFunSig =
4644  this->module_->signature(imm.cont_type->contfun_typeindex());
4645  PoppedArgVector args = PopArgs(contFunSig);
4646  Value* returns = PushReturns(contFunSig);
4647 
4648  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(Resume, imm, handlers, args.data(),
4649  returns);
4650  return 1 + imm.length + table_length;
4651  }
4652 
4653  DECODE(ResumeThrow) {
4654  CHECK_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(wasmfx);
4655  ContIndexImmediate cont_imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
4656  if (!this->ValidateCont(this->pc_ + 1, cont_imm)) return 0;
4657 
4658  Pop(ValueType::RefNull(cont_imm.heap_type()));
4659 
4660  TagIndexImmediate exc_imm(this, this->pc_ + cont_imm.length + 1, validate);
4661  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + cont_imm.length + 1, exc_imm)) return 0;
4662  if (exc_imm.tag->sig->return_count() != 0) {
4663  this->DecodeError("tag signature %u has non-void return", exc_imm.index);
4664  return 0;
4665  }
4666  PoppedArgVector args = PopArgs(exc_imm.tag->ToFunctionSig());
4667 
4668  EffectHandlerTableImmediate handler_table_imm(
4669  this, this->pc_ + cont_imm.length + exc_imm.length + 1, validate);
4670  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + cont_imm.length + exc_imm.length + 1,
4671  handler_table_imm))
4672  return 0;
4673 
4674  base::Vector<HandlerCase> handlers =
4675  this->zone_->template AllocateVector<HandlerCase>(
4676  handler_table_imm.table_count);
4677 
4678  int table_length = DecodeEffectHandlerTable(handler_table_imm, handlers);
4679  if (table_length < 0) return 0;
4680 
4681  // The continuation might return, check the return type.
4682  const FunctionSig* contFunSig =
4683  this->module_->signature(cont_imm.cont_type->contfun_typeindex());
4684  Value* returns = PushReturns(contFunSig);
4685 
4686  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ResumeThrow, cont_imm, exc_imm, handlers,
4687  args.data(), returns);
4688  return 1 + exc_imm.length + cont_imm.length + table_length;
4689  }
4690 
4691  DECODE(Suspend) {
4692  CHECK_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(wasmfx);
4693  TagIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
4694  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + 1, imm)) return 0;
4695 
4696  const FunctionSig* sig = imm.tag->ToFunctionSig();
4697 
4698  PoppedArgVector args = PopArgs(sig);
4699 
4700  Value* returns = PushReturns(sig);
4701 
4702  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(Suspend, imm, args.data(), returns);
4703 
4704  return 1 + imm.length;
4705  }
4706 
4707  DECODE(Switch) {
4708  CHECK_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(wasmfx);
4709  ContIndexImmediate contimm(this, this->pc_ + 1, validate);
4710  if (!this->ValidateCont(this->pc_ + 1, contimm)) return 0;
4711 
4712  TagIndexImmediate tagimm(this, this->pc_ + contimm.length + 1, validate);
4713  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + contimm.length + 1, tagimm)) return 0;
4714 
4715  const FunctionSig* tag_sig = tagimm.tag->ToFunctionSig();
4716  const FunctionSig* cont_sig =
4717  this->module_->signature(contimm.cont_type->contfun_typeindex());
4718 
4719  if (!VALIDATE(IsSubtypeVec(cont_sig->returns(), tag_sig->returns()))) {
4720  this->DecodeError("return(s) from continuation %d do not match tag %d",
4721  contimm.index.index, tagimm.index);
4722  return 0;
4723  }
4724 
4725  const base::Vector<const ValueType> cont_args = cont_sig->parameters();
4726 
4727  if (!VALIDATE(cont_args.size() >= 1 &&
4728  IsSubtypeOf(cont_args.last(), kWasmContRef, this->module_))) {
4729  this->DecodeError(
4730  "expecting a (ref null? cont) as last parameter of type %d",
4731  contimm.index.index);
4732  return 0;
4733  }
4734 
4735  const ValueType return_type = cont_args.last();
4736 
4737  if (!VALIDATE(return_type.has_index() &&
4738  this->module_->has_cont_type(return_type.ref_index()))) {
4739  this->DecodeError(
4740  "expecting a defined cont type as last parameter of type %d",
4741  contimm.index.index);
4742  return 0;
4743  }
4744  const ContType* return_cont =
4745  this->module_->cont_type(return_type.ref_index());
4746  const FunctionSig* return_sig =
4747  this->module_->signature(return_cont->contfun_typeindex());
4748 
4749  if (!VALIDATE(IsSubtypeVec(tag_sig->returns(), return_sig->returns()))) {
4750  this->DecodeError(
4751  "tag %d's return types should be a subtype of return continuation "
4752  "%d's return types",
4753  tagimm.index, cont_args.last().ref_index().index);
4754  return 0;
4755  }
4756 
4757  Value cont_ref = Pop(ValueType::RefNull(contimm.heap_type()));
4758  PoppedArgVector args =
4759  PopSomeArgs(cont_sig, static_cast<int>(cont_args.size()) - 1);
4760 
4761  Value* returns = PushParameters(return_sig);
4762 
4763  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(Switch, tagimm, contimm, cont_ref,
4764  args.data(), returns);
4765 
4766  return 1 + contimm.length + tagimm.length;
4767  }
4768 
4769  DECODE(Numeric) {
4770  auto [full_opcode, opcode_length] =
4771  this->template read_prefixed_opcode<ValidationTag>(this->pc_,
4772  "numeric index");
4773  if (full_opcode == kExprTableGrow || full_opcode == kExprTableSize ||
4774  full_opcode == kExprTableFill) {
4775  this->detected_->add_reftypes();
4776  }
4777  trace_msg->AppendOpcode(full_opcode);
4778  return DecodeNumericOpcode(full_opcode, opcode_length);
4779  }

4781  DECODE(AsmJs) {
4782  auto [full_opcode, opcode_length] =
4783  this->template read_prefixed_opcode<ValidationTag>(this->pc_,
4784  "asmjs index");
4785  trace_msg->AppendOpcode(full_opcode);
4786  return DecodeAsmJsOpcode(full_opcode, opcode_length);
4787  }

4789  DECODE(Simd) {
4790  this->detected_->add_simd();
4791  if (!CheckHardwareSupportsSimd()) {
4792  if (v8_flags.correctness_fuzzer_suppressions) {
4793  FATAL("Aborting on missing Wasm SIMD support");
4794  }
4795  this->DecodeError("Wasm SIMD unsupported");
4796  return 0;
4797  }
4798  auto [full_opcode, opcode_length] =
4799  this->template read_prefixed_opcode<ValidationTag>(this->pc_);
4800  if (!VALIDATE(this->ok())) return 0;
4801  trace_msg->AppendOpcode(full_opcode);
4802  if (WasmOpcodes::IsFP16SimdOpcode(full_opcode)) {
4803  this->detected_->add_fp16();
4804  } else if (WasmOpcodes::IsRelaxedSimdOpcode(full_opcode)) {
4805  this->detected_->add_relaxed_simd();
4806  }
4807  return DecodeSimdOpcode(full_opcode, opcode_length);
4808  }
4809 
4810  DECODE(Atomic) {

4812  this->template read_prefixed_opcode<ValidationTag>(this->pc_,
4813  "atomic index");
4814  trace_msg->AppendOpcode(full_opcode);
4815  return DecodeAtomicOpcode(full_opcode, opcode_length);
4816  }
4817 
4818  DECODE(GC) {
4819  auto [full_opcode, opcode_length] =
4820  this->template read_prefixed_opcode<ValidationTag>(this->pc_,
4821  "gc index");
4822  trace_msg->AppendOpcode(full_opcode);
4823  // If we are validating we could have read an illegal opcode. Handle that
4824  // separately.
4825  if (!VALIDATE(full_opcode != 0)) {
4826  DCHECK(this->failed());
4827  return 0;
4828  } else if (full_opcode >= kExprStringNewUtf8) {
4829  CHECK_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(stringref);
4830  return DecodeStringRefOpcode(full_opcode, opcode_length);
4831  } else {
4832  this->detected_->add_gc();
4833  return DecodeGCOpcode(full_opcode, opcode_length);
4834  }
4835  }

4850  static int UnknownOpcodeError(WasmFullDecoder* decoder, WasmOpcode opcode) {
4851  decoder->DecodeError("Invalid opcode 0x%x", opcode);
4852  return 0;
4853  }
4854 
4855  using OpcodeHandler = int (*)(WasmFullDecoder*, WasmOpcode);
4856 
4857  // Ideally we would use template specialization for the different opcodes, but
4858  // GCC does not allow to specialize templates in class scope
4859  // (https://gcc.gnu.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=85282), and specializing
4860  // outside the class is not allowed for non-specialized classes.
4861  // Hence just list all implementations explicitly here, which also gives more
4862  // freedom to use the same implementation for different opcodes.
4863 #define DECODE_IMPL(opcode) DECODE_IMPL2(kExpr##opcode, opcode)
4864 #define DECODE_IMPL2(opcode, name) \
4865  if (idx == opcode) { \
4866  if constexpr (decoding_mode == kConstantExpression) { \
4867  return &WasmFullDecoder::NonConstError; \
4868  } else { \
4869  return &WasmFullDecoder::Decode##name; \
4870  } \
4871  }
4872 #define DECODE_IMPL_CONST(opcode) DECODE_IMPL_CONST2(kExpr##opcode, opcode)
4873 #define DECODE_IMPL_CONST2(opcode, name) \
4874  if (idx == opcode) return &WasmFullDecoder::Decode##name
4875

4877  DECODE_IMPL(Nop);

4879  FOREACH_SIMPLE_NON_CONST_OPCODE(BUILD_SIMPLE_OPCODE)
4880 #undef BUILD_SIMPLE_OPCODE
4881 #define BUILD_SIMPLE_EXTENDED_CONST_OPCODE(op, ...) DECODE_IMPL_CONST(op);
4882  FOREACH_SIMPLE_EXTENDED_CONST_OPCODE(BUILD_SIMPLE_EXTENDED_CONST_OPCODE)
4883 #undef BUILD_SIMPLE_EXTENDED_CONST_OPCODE
4884  DECODE_IMPL(Block);
4885  DECODE_IMPL(Rethrow);
4886  DECODE_IMPL(Throw);
4887  DECODE_IMPL(Try);
4888  DECODE_IMPL(TryTable);
4889  DECODE_IMPL(ThrowRef);
4890  DECODE_IMPL(Catch);
4891  DECODE_IMPL(Delegate);
4892  DECODE_IMPL(CatchAll);
4893  DECODE_IMPL(ContNew);
4894  DECODE_IMPL(ContBind);
4895  DECODE_IMPL(Resume);

4914  DECODE_IMPL_CONST(I64Const);
4915  DECODE_IMPL_CONST(F32Const);
4916  DECODE_IMPL_CONST(F64Const);

4958  OpcodeHandler GetOpcodeHandler(uint8_t opcode) {
4959  static constexpr std::array<OpcodeHandler, 256> kOpcodeHandlers =
4960  base::make_array<256>(GetOpcodeHandlerTableEntry);

4963 
4964  void EndControl() {
4965  DCHECK(!control_.empty());
4966  Control* current = &control_.back();
4967  stack_.shrink_to(current->stack_depth);
4968  current->reachability = kUnreachable;
4969  current_code_reachable_and_ok_ = false;
4970  }
4971 
4972  template <typename func>
4973  V8_INLINE void InitMerge(Merge<Value>* merge, uint32_t arity, func get_val) {
4974  merge->arity = arity;
4975  if constexpr (std::is_null_pointer_v<func>) {
4976  DCHECK_EQ(0, arity);
4977  } else if (arity == 1) {
4978  merge->vals.first = get_val(0);
4979  } else if (arity > 1) {
4980  merge->vals.array = this->zone()->template AllocateArray<Value>(arity);
4981  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < arity; i++) {
4982  merge->vals.array[i] = get_val(i);
4983  }
4984  }
4985  }
4986 
4987  // In reachable code, check if there are at least {count} values on the stack.
4988  // In unreachable code, if there are less than {count} values on the stack,
4989  // insert a number of unreachable values underneath the current values equal
4990  // to the difference, and return that number.
4991  V8_INLINE int EnsureStackArguments(int count) {
4992  uint32_t limit = control_.back().stack_depth;
4993  if (V8_LIKELY(stack_.size() >= count + limit)) return 0;
4994  return EnsureStackArguments_Slow(count);
4995  }
4996 
4997  V8_NOINLINE V8_PRESERVE_MOST int EnsureStackArguments_Slow(int count) {
4998  uint32_t limit = control_.back().stack_depth;
4999  if (!VALIDATE(control_.back().unreachable())) {
5000  NotEnoughArgumentsError(count, stack_.size() - limit);
5001  }
5002  // Silently create unreachable values out of thin air underneath the
5003  // existing stack values. To do so, we have to move existing stack values
5004  // upwards in the stack, then instantiate the new Values as
5005  // {UnreachableValue}.
5006  int current_values = stack_.size() - limit;
5007  int additional_values = count - current_values;
5008  DCHECK_GT(additional_values, 0);
5009  // Ensure that after this operation there is still room for one more value.
5010  // Callers might not expect this operation to push values on the stack
5011  // (because it only does so in exceptional cases).
5012  stack_.EnsureMoreCapacity(additional_values + 1, this->zone_);
5013  Value unreachable_value = UnreachableValue(this->pc_);
5014  for (int i = 0; i < additional_values; ++i) stack_.push(unreachable_value);
5015  if (current_values > 0) {
5016  // Move the current values up to the end of the stack, and create
5017  // unreachable values below.
5018  Value* stack_base = stack_value(current_values + additional_values);
5019  for (int i = current_values - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
5020  stack_base[additional_values + i] = stack_base[i];
5021  }
5022  for (int i = 0; i < additional_values; i++) {
5023  stack_base[i] = UnreachableValue(this->pc_);
5024  }
5025  }
5026  return additional_values;
5027  }
5028 
5029  V8_INLINE void ValidateParameters(const FunctionSig* sig) {
5030  int num_params = static_cast<int>(sig->parameter_count());
5031  EnsureStackArguments(num_params);
5032  Value* param_base = stack_.end() - num_params;
5033  for (int i = 0; i < num_params; i++) {
5034  ValidateStackValue(i, param_base[i], sig->GetParam(i));
5035  }
5036  }
5037 
5038  // Drops a number of stack elements equal to the {sig}'s parameter count (0 if
5039  // {sig} is null), or all of them if less are present.
5040  V8_INLINE void DropArgs(const FunctionSig* sig) {
5041  int count = static_cast<int>(sig->parameter_count());
5042  Drop(count);
5043  }
5044 
5045  V8_INLINE PoppedArgVector PopArgs(const StructType* type) {
5046  int count = static_cast<int>(type->field_count());
5047  EnsureStackArguments(count);
5048  DCHECK_LE(control_.back().stack_depth, stack_size());
5049  DCHECK_GE(stack_size() - control_.back().stack_depth, count);
5050  Value* args_base = stack_.end() - count;
5051  for (int i = 0; i < count; i++) {
5052  ValidateStackValue(i, args_base[i], type->field(i).Unpacked());
5053  }
5054  // Note: Popping from the {FastZoneVector} does not invalidate the old (now
5055  // out-of-range) elements.
5056  stack_.pop(count);
5057  return PoppedArgVector{base::VectorOf(args_base, count)};
5058  }
5059  // Drops a number of stack elements equal to the struct's field count, or all
5060  // of them if less are present.
5061  V8_INLINE void DropArgs(const StructType* type) {
5062  Drop(static_cast<int>(type->field_count()));
5063  }
5064 
5065  // Pops some of the arguments as required by signature and count.
5066  V8_INLINE PoppedArgVector PopSomeArgs(const FunctionSig* sig, int count) {
5067  DCHECK_LE(count, static_cast<int>(sig->parameter_count()));
5068 
5069  EnsureStackArguments(count);
5070  DCHECK_LE(control_.back().stack_depth, stack_size());
5071  DCHECK_GE(stack_size() - control_.back().stack_depth, count);
5072  Value* args_base = stack_.end() - count;
5073  for (int i = 0; i < count; ++i) {
5074  ValidateStackValue(i, args_base[i], sig->GetParam(i));
5075  }
5076  // Note: Popping from the {FastZoneVector} does not invalidate the old (now
5077  // out-of-range) elements.
5078  stack_.pop(count);
5079  return PoppedArgVector{base::VectorOf(args_base, count)};
5080  }
5081 
5082  // Pops all the arguments as required by signature.
5083  V8_INLINE PoppedArgVector PopArgs(const FunctionSig* sig) {
5084  return PopSomeArgs(sig, static_cast<int>(sig->parameter_count()));
5085  }
5086 
5087  Control* PushControl(ControlKind kind, const BlockTypeImmediate& imm) {
5088  DCHECK(!control_.empty());
5089  ValidateParameters(&imm.sig);
5090  uint32_t consumed_values = static_cast<uint32_t>(imm.sig.parameter_count());
5091  uint32_t stack_depth = stack_.size();
5092  DCHECK_LE(consumed_values, stack_depth);
5093  uint32_t inner_stack_depth = stack_depth - consumed_values;
5094  DCHECK_LE(control_.back().stack_depth, inner_stack_depth);
5095 
5096  uint32_t init_stack_depth = this->locals_initialization_stack_depth();
5097  Reachability reachability = control_.back().innerReachability();
5098  control_.EnsureMoreCapacity(1, this->zone_);
5099  control_.emplace_back(this->zone_, kind, inner_stack_depth,
5100  init_stack_depth, this->pc_, reachability);
5101  Control* new_block = &control_.back();
5102 
5103  Value* arg_base = stack_.end() - consumed_values;
5104  // Update the type of input nodes to the more general types expected by the
5105  // block. In particular, in unreachable code, the input would have bottom
5106  // type otherwise.
5107  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < consumed_values; ++i) {
5108  DCHECK_IMPLIES(this->ok(), IsSubtypeOf(arg_base[i].type, imm.in_type(i),
5109  this->module_) ||
5110  arg_base[i].type == kWasmBottom);
5111  arg_base[i].type = imm.in_type(i);
5112  }
5113 
5114  // Initialize start- and end-merges of {c} with values according to the
5115  // in- and out-types of {c} respectively.
5116  const uint8_t* pc = this->pc_;
5117  InitMerge(&new_block->end_merge, imm.out_arity(), [pc, &imm](uint32_t i) {
5118  return Value{pc, imm.out_type(i)};
5119  });
5120  InitMerge(&new_block->start_merge, imm.in_arity(),
5121  [arg_base](uint32_t i) { return arg_base[i]; });
5122  return new_block;
5123  }
5124 
5125  void PopControl() {
5126  // This cannot be the outermost control block.
5127  DCHECK_LT(1, control_.size());
5128  Control* c = &control_.back();
5129  DCHECK_LE(c->stack_depth, stack_.size());
5130 
5131  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_PARENT_REACHABLE(PopControl, c);
5132 
5133  // - In non-unreachable code, a loop just leaves the values on the stack.
5134  // - In unreachable code, it is not guaranteed that we have Values of the
5135  // correct types on the stack, so we have to make sure we do. Their values
5136  // do not matter, so we might as well push the (uninitialized) values of
5137  // the loop's end merge.
5138  if (!c->is_loop() || c->unreachable()) {
5139  PushMergeValues(c, &c->end_merge);
5140  }
5141  RollbackLocalsInitialization(c);
5142 
5143  bool parent_reached =
5144  c->reachable() || c->end_merge.reached || c->is_onearmed_if();
5145  control_.pop();
5146  // If the parent block was reachable before, but the popped control does not
5147  // return to here, this block becomes "spec only reachable".
5148  if (!parent_reached) SetSucceedingCodeDynamicallyUnreachable();
5149  current_code_reachable_and_ok_ =
5150  VALIDATE(this->ok()) && control_.back().reachable();
5151  }
5152 
5153  int DecodeLoadMem(LoadType type, int prefix_len = 1) {
5154  MemoryAccessImmediate imm =
5155  MakeMemoryAccessImmediate(prefix_len, type.size_log_2());
5156  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + prefix_len, imm)) return 0;
5157  ValueType address_type = MemoryAddressType(imm.memory);
5158  Value index = Pop(address_type);
5159  Value* result = Push(type.value_type());
5160  if (V8_LIKELY(
5161  !CheckStaticallyOutOfBounds(imm.memory, type.size(), imm.offset))) {
5162  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(LoadMem, type, imm, index, result);
5163  }
5164  return prefix_len + imm.length;
5165  }
5166 
5167  int DecodeLoadTransformMem(LoadType type, LoadTransformationKind transform,
5168  uint32_t opcode_length) {
5169  // Load extends always load 64-bits.
5170  uint32_t max_alignment =
5171  transform == LoadTransformationKind::kExtend ? 3 : type.size_log_2();
5172  MemoryAccessImmediate imm =
5173  MakeMemoryAccessImmediate(opcode_length, max_alignment);
5174  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
5175  ValueType address_type = MemoryAddressType(imm.memory);
5176  Value index = Pop(address_type);
5177  Value* result = Push(kWasmS128);
5178  uintptr_t op_size =
5179  transform == LoadTransformationKind::kExtend ? 8 : type.size();
5180  if (V8_LIKELY(
5181  !CheckStaticallyOutOfBounds(imm.memory, op_size, imm.offset))) {
5182  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(LoadTransform, type, transform, imm,
5183  index, result);
5184  }
5185  return opcode_length + imm.length;
5186  }
5187 
5188  int DecodeLoadLane(WasmOpcode opcode, LoadType type, uint32_t opcode_length) {
5189  MemoryAccessImmediate mem_imm =
5190  MakeMemoryAccessImmediate(opcode_length, type.size_log_2());
5191  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, mem_imm)) return 0;
5192  SimdLaneImmediate lane_imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length + mem_imm.length,
5193  validate);
5194  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, opcode, lane_imm)) return 0;
5195  ValueType address_type = MemoryAddressType(mem_imm.memory);
5196  auto [index, v128] = Pop(address_type, kWasmS128);
5197 
5198  Value* result = Push(kWasmS128);
5199  if (V8_LIKELY(!CheckStaticallyOutOfBounds(mem_imm.memory, type.size(),
5200  mem_imm.offset))) {
5201  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(LoadLane, type, v128, index, mem_imm,
5202  lane_imm.lane, result);
5203  }
5204  return opcode_length + mem_imm.length + lane_imm.length;
5205  }
5206 
5207  int DecodeStoreLane(WasmOpcode opcode, StoreType type,
5208  uint32_t opcode_length) {
5209  MemoryAccessImmediate mem_imm =
5210  MakeMemoryAccessImmediate(opcode_length, type.size_log_2());
5211  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, mem_imm)) return 0;
5212  SimdLaneImmediate lane_imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length + mem_imm.length,
5213  validate);
5214  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, opcode, lane_imm)) return 0;
5215  ValueType address_type = MemoryAddressType(mem_imm.memory);
5216  auto [index, v128] = Pop(address_type, kWasmS128);
5217 
5218  if (V8_LIKELY(!CheckStaticallyOutOfBounds(mem_imm.memory, type.size(),
5219  mem_imm.offset))) {
5220  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StoreLane, type, mem_imm, index, v128,
5221  lane_imm.lane);
5222  }
5223  return opcode_length + mem_imm.length + lane_imm.length;
5224  }
5225 
5226  bool CheckStaticallyOutOfBounds(const WasmMemory* memory, uint64_t size,
5227  uint64_t offset) {
5228  const bool statically_oob =
5229  !base::IsInBounds<uint64_t>(offset, size, memory->max_memory_size);
5230  if (V8_UNLIKELY(statically_oob)) {
5231  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(Trap, TrapReason::kTrapMemOutOfBounds);
5232  SetSucceedingCodeDynamicallyUnreachable();
5233  }
5234  return statically_oob;
5235  }
5236 
5237  int DecodeStoreMem(StoreType store, int prefix_len = 1) {
5238  MemoryAccessImmediate imm =
5239  MakeMemoryAccessImmediate(prefix_len, store.size_log_2());
5240  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + prefix_len, imm)) return 0;
5241  ValueType address_type = MemoryAddressType(imm.memory);
5242  auto [index, value] = Pop(address_type, store.value_type());
5243  if (V8_LIKELY(!CheckStaticallyOutOfBounds(imm.memory, store.size(),
5244  imm.offset))) {
5245  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StoreMem, store, imm, index, value);
5246  }
5247  return prefix_len + imm.length;
5248  }

5250  uint32_t SimdConstOp(uint32_t opcode_length) {
5251  Simd128Immediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
5252  Value* result = Push(kWasmS128);
5253  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(S128Const, imm, result);
5254  return opcode_length + kSimd128Size;
5255  }
5256 
5257  uint32_t SimdExtractLane(WasmOpcode opcode, ValueType type,
5258  uint32_t opcode_length) {
5259  SimdLaneImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
5260  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, opcode, imm)) return 0;
5261  Value input = Pop(kWasmS128);
5262  Value* result = Push(type);
5263  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(SimdLaneOp, opcode, imm,
5264  base::VectorOf({input}), result);
5265  return opcode_length + imm.length;
5266  }
5267 
5268  uint32_t SimdReplaceLane(WasmOpcode opcode, ValueType type,
5269  uint32_t opcode_length) {
5270  SimdLaneImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
5271  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, opcode, imm)) return 0;
5272  auto [v128, lane_val] = Pop(kWasmS128, type);
5273  Value* result = Push(kWasmS128);
5274  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(
5275  SimdLaneOp, opcode, imm, base::VectorOf({v128, lane_val}), result);
5276  return opcode_length + imm.length;
5277  }
5278 
5279  uint32_t Simd8x16ShuffleOp(uint32_t opcode_length) {
5280  Simd128Immediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
5281  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
5282  auto [input0, input1] = Pop(kWasmS128, kWasmS128);
5283  Value* result = Push(kWasmS128);
5284  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(Simd8x16ShuffleOp, imm, input0, input1,
5285  result);
5286  return opcode_length + 16;
5287  }
