5289  uint32_t DecodeSimdOpcode(WasmOpcode opcode, uint32_t opcode_length) {
5290  if constexpr (decoding_mode == kConstantExpression) {
5291  // Currently, only s128.const is allowed in constant expressions.
5292  if (opcode != kExprS128Const) {
5293  this->DecodeError("opcode %s is not allowed in constant expressions",
5294  this->SafeOpcodeNameAt(this->pc()));
5295  return 0;
5296  }
5297  return SimdConstOp(opcode_length);
5298  }
5299  // opcode_length is the number of bytes that this SIMD-specific opcode takes
5300  // up in the LEB128 encoded form.
5301  switch (opcode) {
5302  case kExprF64x2ExtractLane:
5303  return SimdExtractLane(opcode, kWasmF64, opcode_length);
5304  case kExprF16x8ExtractLane: {
5305  if (!this->enabled_.has_fp16()) {
5306  this->DecodeError(
5307  "invalid simd opcode: 0x%x, "
5308  "enable with --experimental-wasm-fp16",
5309  opcode);
5310  return 0;
5311  }
5312  [[fallthrough]];
5313  }
5314  case kExprF32x4ExtractLane:
5315  return SimdExtractLane(opcode, kWasmF32, opcode_length);
5316  case kExprI64x2ExtractLane:
5317  return SimdExtractLane(opcode, kWasmI64, opcode_length);
5318  case kExprI32x4ExtractLane:
5319  case kExprI16x8ExtractLaneS:
5320  case kExprI16x8ExtractLaneU:
5321  case kExprI8x16ExtractLaneS:
5322  case kExprI8x16ExtractLaneU:
5323  return SimdExtractLane(opcode, kWasmI32, opcode_length);
5324  case kExprF64x2ReplaceLane:
5325  return SimdReplaceLane(opcode, kWasmF64, opcode_length);
5326  case kExprF16x8ReplaceLane: {
5327  if (!this->enabled_.has_fp16()) {
5328  this->DecodeError(
5329  "invalid simd opcode: 0x%x, "
5330  "enable with --experimental-wasm-fp16",
5331  opcode);
5332  return 0;
5333  }
5334  [[fallthrough]];
5335  }
5336  case kExprF32x4ReplaceLane:
5337  return SimdReplaceLane(opcode, kWasmF32, opcode_length);
5338  case kExprI64x2ReplaceLane:
5339  return SimdReplaceLane(opcode, kWasmI64, opcode_length);
5340  case kExprI32x4ReplaceLane:
5341  case kExprI16x8ReplaceLane:
5342  case kExprI8x16ReplaceLane:
5343  return SimdReplaceLane(opcode, kWasmI32, opcode_length);
5344  case kExprI8x16Shuffle:
5345  return Simd8x16ShuffleOp(opcode_length);
5346  case kExprS128LoadMem:
5347  return DecodeLoadMem(LoadType::kS128Load, opcode_length);
5348  case kExprS128StoreMem:
5349  return DecodeStoreMem(StoreType::kS128Store, opcode_length);
5350  case kExprS128Load32Zero:
5351  return DecodeLoadTransformMem(LoadType::kI32Load,
5352  LoadTransformationKind::kZeroExtend,
5353  opcode_length);
5354  case kExprS128Load64Zero:
5355  return DecodeLoadTransformMem(LoadType::kI64Load,
5356  LoadTransformationKind::kZeroExtend,
5357  opcode_length);
5358  case kExprS128Load8Splat:
5359  return DecodeLoadTransformMem(LoadType::kI32Load8S,
5360  LoadTransformationKind::kSplat,
5361  opcode_length);
5362  case kExprS128Load16Splat:
5363  return DecodeLoadTransformMem(LoadType::kI32Load16S,
5364  LoadTransformationKind::kSplat,
5365  opcode_length);
5366  case kExprS128Load32Splat:
5367  return DecodeLoadTransformMem(
5368  LoadType::kI32Load, LoadTransformationKind::kSplat, opcode_length);
5369  case kExprS128Load64Splat:
5370  return DecodeLoadTransformMem(
5371  LoadType::kI64Load, LoadTransformationKind::kSplat, opcode_length);
5372  case kExprS128Load8x8S:
5373  return DecodeLoadTransformMem(LoadType::kI32Load8S,
5374  LoadTransformationKind::kExtend,
5375  opcode_length);
5376  case kExprS128Load8x8U:
5377  return DecodeLoadTransformMem(LoadType::kI32Load8U,
5378  LoadTransformationKind::kExtend,
5379  opcode_length);
5380  case kExprS128Load16x4S:
5381  return DecodeLoadTransformMem(LoadType::kI32Load16S,
5382  LoadTransformationKind::kExtend,
5383  opcode_length);
5384  case kExprS128Load16x4U:
5385  return DecodeLoadTransformMem(LoadType::kI32Load16U,
5386  LoadTransformationKind::kExtend,
5387  opcode_length);
5388  case kExprS128Load32x2S:
5389  return DecodeLoadTransformMem(LoadType::kI64Load32S,
5390  LoadTransformationKind::kExtend,
5391  opcode_length);
5392  case kExprS128Load32x2U:
5393  return DecodeLoadTransformMem(LoadType::kI64Load32U,
5394  LoadTransformationKind::kExtend,
5395  opcode_length);
5396  case kExprS128Load8Lane: {
5397  return DecodeLoadLane(opcode, LoadType::kI32Load8S, opcode_length);
5398  }
5399  case kExprS128Load16Lane: {
5400  return DecodeLoadLane(opcode, LoadType::kI32Load16S, opcode_length);
5401  }
5402  case kExprS128Load32Lane: {
5403  return DecodeLoadLane(opcode, LoadType::kI32Load, opcode_length);
5404  }
5405  case kExprS128Load64Lane: {
5406  return DecodeLoadLane(opcode, LoadType::kI64Load, opcode_length);
5407  }
5408  case kExprS128Store8Lane: {
5409  return DecodeStoreLane(opcode, StoreType::kI32Store8, opcode_length);
5410  }
5411  case kExprS128Store16Lane: {
5412  return DecodeStoreLane(opcode, StoreType::kI32Store16, opcode_length);
5413  }
5414  case kExprS128Store32Lane: {
5415  return DecodeStoreLane(opcode, StoreType::kI32Store, opcode_length);
5416  }
5417  case kExprS128Store64Lane: {
5418  return DecodeStoreLane(opcode, StoreType::kI64Store, opcode_length);
5419  }
5420  case kExprS128Const:
5421  return SimdConstOp(opcode_length);
5422  case kExprF16x8Splat:
5423  case kExprF16x8Abs:
5424  case kExprF16x8Neg:
5425  case kExprF16x8Sqrt:
5426  case kExprF16x8Ceil:
5427  case kExprF16x8Floor:
5428  case kExprF16x8Trunc:
5429  case kExprF16x8NearestInt:
5430  case kExprF16x8Eq:
5431  case kExprF16x8Ne:
5432  case kExprF16x8Lt:
5433  case kExprF16x8Gt:
5434  case kExprF16x8Le:
5435  case kExprF16x8Ge:
5436  case kExprF16x8Add:
5437  case kExprF16x8Sub:
5438  case kExprF16x8Mul:
5439  case kExprF16x8Div:
5440  case kExprF16x8Min:
5441  case kExprF16x8Max:
5442  case kExprF16x8Pmin:
5443  case kExprF16x8Pmax:
5444  case kExprI16x8SConvertF16x8:
5445  case kExprI16x8UConvertF16x8:
5446  case kExprF16x8SConvertI16x8:
5447  case kExprF16x8UConvertI16x8:
5448  case kExprF16x8DemoteF32x4Zero:
5449  case kExprF16x8DemoteF64x2Zero:
5450  case kExprF32x4PromoteLowF16x8:
5451  case kExprF16x8Qfma:
5452  case kExprF16x8Qfms: {
5453  if (!this->enabled_.has_fp16()) {
5454  this->DecodeError(
5455  "invalid simd opcode: 0x%x, "
5456  "enable with --experimental-wasm-fp16",
5457  opcode);
5458  return 0;
5459  }
5460  [[fallthrough]];
5461  }
5462  default: {
5463  const FunctionSig* sig = WasmOpcodes::Signature(opcode);
5464  if (!VALIDATE(sig != nullptr)) {
5465  this->DecodeError("invalid simd opcode");
5466  return 0;
5467  }
5468  PoppedArgVector args = PopArgs(sig);
5469  Value* results = sig->return_count() == 0 ? nullptr : PushReturns(sig);
5470  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(SimdOp, opcode, args.data(),
5471  results);
5472  return opcode_length;
5473  }
5474  }
5475  }
5476 
5477  // Returns true if type checking will always fail, either because the types
5478  // are unrelated or because the target_type is one of the null sentinels and
5479  // conversion to null does not succeed.
5480  bool TypeCheckAlwaysFails(Value obj, HeapType expected_type,
5481  bool null_succeeds) {
5482  bool types_unrelated =
5483  !IsSubtypeOf(ValueType::Ref(expected_type), obj.type, this->module_) &&
5484  !IsSubtypeOf(obj.type, ValueType::RefNull(expected_type),
5485  this->module_);
5486  // For "unrelated" types the check can still succeed for the null value on
5487  // instructions treating null as a successful check.
5488  // TODO(12868): For string views, this implementation anticipates that
5489  // https://github.com/WebAssembly/stringref/issues/40 will be resolved
5490  // by making the views standalone types.
5491  return (types_unrelated &&
5492  (!null_succeeds || !obj.type.is_nullable() ||
5493  obj.type.is_string_view() || expected_type.is_string_view())) ||
5494  ((!null_succeeds || !obj.type.is_nullable()) &&
5495  (expected_type.representation() == HeapType::kNone ||
5496  expected_type.representation() == HeapType::kNoFunc ||
5497  expected_type.representation() == HeapType::kNoExtern ||
5498  expected_type.representation() == HeapType::kNoExn ||
5499  expected_type.representation() == HeapType::kNoneShared ||
5500  expected_type.representation() == HeapType::kNoFuncShared ||
5501  expected_type.representation() == HeapType::kNoExternShared ||
5502  expected_type.representation() == HeapType::kNoExnShared));
5503  }
5504 
5505  // Checks if {obj} is a subtype of type, thus checking will always
5506  // succeed.
5507  bool TypeCheckAlwaysSucceeds(Value obj, HeapType type) {
5508  return IsSubtypeOf(obj.type, ValueType::RefNull(type), this->module_);
5509  }

5511 #define NON_CONST_ONLY \
5512  if constexpr (decoding_mode == kConstantExpression) { \
5513  this->DecodeError("opcode %s is not allowed in constant expressions", \
5514  this->SafeOpcodeNameAt(this->pc())); \
5515  return 0; \
5516  }
5517 
5518  Value PopDescriptor(ModuleTypeIndex described_index) {
5519  const TypeDefinition& type = this->module_->type(described_index);
5520  if (!type.has_descriptor()) return Value{nullptr, kWasmVoid};
5521  DCHECK(this->enabled_.has_custom_descriptors());
5522  ValueType desc_type =
5523  ValueType::RefNull(this->module_->heap_type(type.descriptor)).AsExact();
5524  return Pop(desc_type);
5525  }
5526 
5527  int DecodeGCOpcode(WasmOpcode opcode, uint32_t opcode_length) {
5528  // Bigger GC opcodes are handled via {DecodeStringRefOpcode}, so we can
5529  // assume here that opcodes are within [0xfb00, 0xfbff].
5530  // This assumption might help the big switch below.
5531  V8_ASSUME(opcode >> 8 == kGCPrefix);
5532  switch (opcode) {
5533  case kExprStructNew: {
5534  StructIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
5535  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
5536  Value descriptor = PopDescriptor(imm.index);
5537  PoppedArgVector args = PopArgs(imm.struct_type);
5538  Value* value = Push(
5539  ValueType::Ref(imm.heap_type()).AsExactIfEnabled(this->enabled_));
5540  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StructNew, imm, descriptor,
5541  args.data(), value);
5542  return opcode_length + imm.length;
5543  }
5544  case kExprStructNewDefault: {
5545  StructIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
5546  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
5547  if (ValidationTag::validate) {
5548  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < imm.struct_type->field_count(); i++) {
5549  ValueType ftype = imm.struct_type->field(i);
5550  if (!VALIDATE(ftype.is_defaultable())) {
5551  this->DecodeError(
5552  "%s: struct type %d has field %d of non-defaultable type %s",
5553  WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode), imm.index.index, i,
5554  ftype.name().c_str());
5555  return 0;
5556  }
5557  }
5558  }
5559  Value descriptor = PopDescriptor(imm.index);
5560  Value* value = Push(
5561  ValueType::Ref(imm.heap_type()).AsExactIfEnabled(this->enabled_));
5562  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StructNewDefault, imm, descriptor,
5563  value);
5564  return opcode_length + imm.length;
5565  }
5566  case kExprStructGet: {
5567  NON_CONST_ONLY
5568  FieldImmediate field(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
5569  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, field)) return 0;
5570  ValueType field_type =
5571  field.struct_imm.struct_type->field(field.field_imm.index);
5572  if (!VALIDATE(!field_type.is_packed())) {
5573  this->DecodeError(
5574  "struct.get: Field %d of type %d has packed type %s. "
5575  "Use struct.get_s or struct.get_u instead.",
5576  field.field_imm.index, field.struct_imm.index.index,
5577  field_type.name().c_str());
5578  return 0;
5579  }
5580  Value struct_obj =
5581  Pop(ValueType::RefNull(field.struct_imm.heap_type()));
5582  Value* value = Push(field_type);
5583  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StructGet, struct_obj, field, true,
5584  value);
5585  return opcode_length + field.length;
5586  }
5587  case kExprStructGetU:
5588  case kExprStructGetS: {
5589  NON_CONST_ONLY
5590  FieldImmediate field(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
5591  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, field)) return 0;
5592  ValueType field_type =
5593  field.struct_imm.struct_type->field(field.field_imm.index);
5594  if (!VALIDATE(field_type.is_packed())) {
5595  this->DecodeError(
5596  "%s: Field %d of type %d has non-packed type %s. Use struct.get "
5597  "instead.",
5598  WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode), field.field_imm.index,
5599  field.struct_imm.index.index, field_type.name().c_str());
5600  return 0;
5601  }
5602  Value struct_obj =
5603  Pop(ValueType::RefNull(field.struct_imm.heap_type()));
5604  Value* value = Push(field_type.Unpacked());
5605  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StructGet, struct_obj, field,
5606  opcode == kExprStructGetS, value);
5607  return opcode_length + field.length;
5608  }
5609  case kExprStructSet: {
5610  NON_CONST_ONLY
5611  FieldImmediate field(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
5612  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, field)) return 0;
5613  const StructType* struct_type = field.struct_imm.struct_type;
5614  if (!VALIDATE(struct_type->mutability(field.field_imm.index))) {
5615  this->DecodeError("struct.set: Field %d of type %d is immutable.",
5616  field.field_imm.index,
5617  field.struct_imm.index.index);
5618  return 0;
5619  }
5620  auto [struct_obj, field_value] =
5621  Pop(ValueType::RefNull(field.struct_imm.heap_type()),
5622  struct_type->field(field.field_imm.index).Unpacked());
5623  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StructSet, struct_obj, field,
5624  field_value);
5625  return opcode_length + field.length;
5626  }
5627  case kExprArrayNew: {
5628  ArrayIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
5629  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
5630  auto [initial_value, length] =
5631  Pop(imm.array_type->element_type().Unpacked(), kWasmI32);
5632  Value* value = Push(
5633  ValueType::Ref(imm.heap_type()).AsExactIfEnabled(this->enabled_));
5634  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ArrayNew, imm, length, initial_value,
5635  value);
5636  return opcode_length + imm.length;
5637  }
5638  case kExprArrayNewDefault: {
5639  ArrayIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
5640  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
5641  if (!VALIDATE(imm.array_type->element_type().is_defaultable())) {
5642  this->DecodeError(
5643  "%s: array type %d has non-defaultable element type %s",
5644  WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode), imm.index.index,
5645  imm.array_type->element_type().name().c_str());
5646  return 0;
5647  }
5648  Value length = Pop(kWasmI32);
5649  Value* value = Push(
5650  ValueType::Ref(imm.heap_type()).AsExactIfEnabled(this->enabled_));
5651  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ArrayNewDefault, imm, length, value);
5652  return opcode_length + imm.length;
5653  }
5654  case kExprArrayNewData: {
5655  // TODO(14616): Add check that array sharedness == segment sharedness?
5656  NON_CONST_ONLY
5657  ArrayIndexImmediate array_imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length,
5658  validate);
5659  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, array_imm)) return 0;
5660  ValueType element_type = array_imm.array_type->element_type();
5661  if (element_type.is_reference()) {
5662  this->DecodeError(
5663  "array.new_data can only be used with numeric-type arrays, found "
5664  "array type #%d instead",
5665  array_imm.index.index);
5666  return 0;
5667  }
5668  const uint8_t* data_index_pc =
5669  this->pc_ + opcode_length + array_imm.length;
5670  IndexImmediate data_segment(this, data_index_pc, "data segment",
5671  validate);
5672  if (!this->ValidateDataSegment(data_index_pc, data_segment)) return 0;
5673 
5674  auto [offset, length] = Pop(kWasmI32, kWasmI32);
5675 
5676  Value* array = Push(ValueType::Ref(array_imm.heap_type())
5677  .AsExactIfEnabled(this->enabled_));
5678  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ArrayNewSegment, array_imm,
5679  data_segment, offset, length, array);
5680  return opcode_length + array_imm.length + data_segment.length;
5681  }
5682  case kExprArrayNewElem: {
5683  // TODO(14616): Add check that array sharedness == segment sharedness?
5684  NON_CONST_ONLY
5685  ArrayIndexImmediate array_imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length,
5686  validate);
5687  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, array_imm)) return 0;
5688  ValueType element_type = array_imm.array_type->element_type();
5689  if (element_type.is_numeric()) {
5690  this->DecodeError(
5691  "array.new_elem can only be used with reference-type arrays, "
5692  "found array type #%d instead",
5693  array_imm.index.index);
5694  return 0;
5695  }
5696  const uint8_t* elem_index_pc =
5697  this->pc_ + opcode_length + array_imm.length;
5698  IndexImmediate elem_segment(this, elem_index_pc, "element segment",
5699  validate);
5700  if (!this->ValidateElementSegment(elem_index_pc, elem_segment)) {
5701  return 0;
5702  }
5703 
5704  ValueType elem_segment_type =
5705  this->module_->elem_segments[elem_segment.index].type;
5706  if (V8_UNLIKELY(
5707  !IsSubtypeOf(elem_segment_type, element_type, this->module_))) {
5708  this->DecodeError(
5709  "array.new_elem: segment type %s is not a subtype of array "
5710  "element type %s",
5711  elem_segment_type.name().c_str(), element_type.name().c_str());
5712  return 0;
5713  }
5714 
5715  auto [offset, length] = Pop(kWasmI32, kWasmI32);
5716  Value* array = Push(ValueType::Ref(array_imm.heap_type())
5717  .AsExactIfEnabled(this->enabled_));
5718  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ArrayNewSegment, array_imm,
5719  elem_segment, offset, length, array);
5720  return opcode_length + array_imm.length + elem_segment.length;
5721  }
5722  case kExprArrayInitData: {
5723  NON_CONST_ONLY
5724  // TODO(14616): Add check that array sharedness == segment sharedness?
5725  ArrayIndexImmediate array_imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length,
5726  validate);
5727  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, array_imm)) return 0;
5728  if (!array_imm.array_type->mutability()) {
5729  this->DecodeError(
5730  "array.init_data can only be used with mutable arrays, found "
5731  "array type #%d instead",
5732  array_imm.index.index);
5733  return 0;
5734  }
5735  ValueType element_type = array_imm.array_type->element_type();

5737  this->DecodeError(
5738  "array.init_data can only be used with numeric-type arrays, "

5746  validate);
5747  if (!this->ValidateDataSegment(data_index_pc, data_segment)) return 0;

5750  Pop(ValueType::RefNull(array_imm.heap_type()), kWasmI32, kWasmI32,
5751  kWasmI32);
5752  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ArrayInitSegment, array_imm,
5753  data_segment, array, array_index,
5754  data_offset, length);
5755  return opcode_length + array_imm.length + data_segment.length;
5756  }
5757  case kExprArrayInitElem: {
5758  NON_CONST_ONLY
5759  // TODO(14616): Add check that array sharedness == segment sharedness?
5760  ArrayIndexImmediate array_imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length,
5761  validate);
5762  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, array_imm)) return 0;
5763  if (!array_imm.array_type->mutability()) {
5764  this->DecodeError(

5767  array_imm.index.index);
5768  return 0;

5771  if (element_type.is_numeric()) {
5772  this->DecodeError(

5776  return 0;

5780  IndexImmediate elem_segment(this, elem_index_pc, "element segment",

5783  return 0;

5791  segment_type.name().c_str(), element_type.name().c_str());
5792  return 0;
5793  }
5794 
5795  auto [array, array_index, elem_offset, length] =
5796  Pop(ValueType::RefNull(array_imm.heap_type()), kWasmI32, kWasmI32,
5797  kWasmI32);
5798  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ArrayInitSegment, array_imm,
5799  elem_segment, array, array_index,
5800  elem_offset, length);
5801  return opcode_length + array_imm.length + elem_segment.length;
5802  }
5803  case kExprArrayGetS:
5804  case kExprArrayGetU: {
5805  NON_CONST_ONLY
5806  ArrayIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
5807  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
5808  if (!VALIDATE(imm.array_type->element_type().is_packed())) {
5809  this->DecodeError(
5810  "%s: Array type %d has non-packed type %s. Use "
5811  "array.get instead.",
5812  WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode), imm.index.index,
5813  imm.array_type->element_type().name().c_str());
5814  return 0;
5815  }

5817  Pop(ValueType::RefNull(imm.heap_type()), kWasmI32);
5818  Value* value = Push(imm.array_type->element_type().Unpacked());
5819  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ArrayGet, array_obj, imm, index,
5820  opcode == kExprArrayGetS, value);
5821  return opcode_length + imm.length;
5822  }
5823  case kExprArrayGet: {
5824  NON_CONST_ONLY
5825  ArrayIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
5826  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
5827  if (!VALIDATE(!imm.array_type->element_type().is_packed())) {
5828  this->DecodeError(
5829  "array.get: Array type %d has packed type %s. Use "
5830  "array.get_s or array.get_u instead.",
5831  imm.index.index, imm.array_type->element_type().name().c_str());
5832  return 0;
5833  }

5835  Pop(ValueType::RefNull(imm.heap_type()), kWasmI32);
5836  Value* value = Push(imm.array_type->element_type());
5837  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ArrayGet, array_obj, imm, index,
5838  true, value);
5839  return opcode_length + imm.length;
5840  }
5841  case kExprArraySet: {
5842  NON_CONST_ONLY
5843  ArrayIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
5844  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
5845  if (!VALIDATE(imm.array_type->mutability())) {
5846  this->DecodeError("array.set: Array type %d is immutable",
5847  imm.index.index);
5848  return 0;

5851  Pop(ValueType::RefNull(imm.heap_type()), kWasmI32,

5853  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ArraySet, array_obj, imm, index,
5854  value);
5855  return opcode_length + imm.length;
5856  }
5857  case kExprArrayLen: {
5858  NON_CONST_ONLY
5859  const bool is_shared = Peek().type.is_shared();
5860  Value array_obj =
5861  Pop(IndependentHeapType{GenericKind::kArray, kNullable, is_shared});
5862  Value* value = Push(kWasmI32);
5863  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ArrayLen, array_obj, value);
5864  return opcode_length;
5865  }
5866  case kExprArrayCopy: {
5867  NON_CONST_ONLY
5868  ArrayIndexImmediate dst_imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
5869  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, dst_imm)) return 0;
5870  if (!VALIDATE(dst_imm.array_type->mutability())) {
5871  this->DecodeError(
5872  "array.copy: immediate destination array type #%d is immutable",
5873  dst_imm.index.index);
5874  return 0;
5875  }
5876  ArrayIndexImmediate src_imm(
5877  this, this->pc_ + opcode_length + dst_imm.length, validate);
5878  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length + dst_imm.length,
5879  src_imm)) {
5880  return 0;
5881  }
5882  if (!IsSubtypeOf(src_imm.array_type->element_type(),
5883  dst_imm.array_type->element_type(), this->module_)) {
5884  this->DecodeError(
5885  "array.copy: source array's #%d element type is not a subtype of "
5886  "destination array's #%d element type",
5887  src_imm.index.index, dst_imm.index.index);
5888  return 0;

5890  auto [dst, dst_index, src, src_index, length] =
5891  Pop(ValueType::RefNull(dst_imm.heap_type()), kWasmI32,
5892  ValueType::RefNull(src_imm.heap_type()), kWasmI32, kWasmI32);
5893  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ArrayCopy, dst, dst_index, src,
5894  src_index, src_imm, length);
5895  return opcode_length + dst_imm.length + src_imm.length;
5896  }
5897  case kExprArrayFill: {
5898  NON_CONST_ONLY
5899  ArrayIndexImmediate array_imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length,
5900  validate);
5901  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, array_imm)) return 0;
5902  if (!VALIDATE(array_imm.array_type->mutability())) {
5903  this->DecodeError("array.init: Array type #%d is immutable",
5904  array_imm.index.index);
5905  return 0;
5906  }
5907

5909  Pop(ValueType::RefNull(array_imm.heap_type()), kWasmI32,
5910  array_imm.array_type->element_type().Unpacked(), kWasmI32);
5911  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ArrayFill, array_imm, array, offset,
5912  value, length);
5913  return opcode_length + array_imm.length;
5914  }
5915  case kExprArrayNewFixed: {
5916  ArrayIndexImmediate array_imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length,
5917  validate);
5918  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, array_imm)) return 0;
5919  IndexImmediate length_imm(this,
5920  this->pc_ + opcode_length + array_imm.length,
5921  "array.new_fixed length", validate);
5922  uint32_t elem_count = length_imm.index;
5923  if (!VALIDATE(elem_count <= kV8MaxWasmArrayNewFixedLength)) {
5924  this->DecodeError(
5925  "Requested length %u for array.new_fixed too large, maximum is "
5926  "%zu",
5927  length_imm.index, kV8MaxWasmArrayNewFixedLength);
5928  return 0;
5929  }
5930  ValueType element_type = array_imm.array_type->element_type();
5931  std::vector<ValueType> element_types(elem_count,
5932  element_type.Unpacked());
5933  FunctionSig element_sig(0, elem_count, element_types.data());
5934  PoppedArgVector elements = PopArgs(&element_sig);
5935  Value* result = Push(ValueType::Ref(array_imm.heap_type())
5936  .AsExactIfEnabled(this->enabled_));
5937  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ArrayNewFixed, array_imm, length_imm,
5938  elements.data(), result);
5939  return opcode_length + array_imm.length + length_imm.length;
5940  }
5941  case kExprRefI31: {
5942  Value input = Pop(kWasmI32);
5943  Value* value = Push(ValueType::Ref(kWasmI31Ref));
5944  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(RefI31, input, value);
5945  return opcode_length;
5946  }
5947  case kExprRefI31Shared: {
5948  CHECK_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(shared);
5949  Value input = Pop(kWasmI32);
5950  Value* value =
5951  Push(IndependentHeapType{GenericKind::kI31, kNonNullable, true});
5952  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(RefI31, input, value);
5953  return opcode_length;
5954  }
5955  case kExprI31GetS: {
5956  NON_CONST_ONLY
5957  const bool is_shared = Peek().type.is_shared();
5958  Value i31 =
5959  Pop(IndependentHeapType{GenericKind::kI31, kNullable, is_shared});
5960  Value* value = Push(kWasmI32);
5961  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(I31GetS, i31, value);
5962  return opcode_length;
5963  }
5964  case kExprI31GetU: {
5965  NON_CONST_ONLY
5966  const bool is_shared = Peek().type.is_shared();
5967  Value i31 =
5968  Pop(IndependentHeapType{GenericKind::kI31, kNullable, is_shared});
5969  Value* value = Push(kWasmI32);
5970  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(I31GetU, i31, value);
5971  return opcode_length;
5972  }
5973  case kExprRefGetDesc: {
5974  NON_CONST_ONLY
5975  CHECK_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(custom_descriptors);
5976  // We may need to generalize this to any TypeIndex in the future, but
5977  // for now only structs can have descriptors.
5978  StructIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
5979  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
5980  const TypeDefinition& type = this->module_->type(imm.index);
5981  if (!VALIDATE(type.has_descriptor())) {
5982  this->DecodeError(
5983  this->pc_ + opcode_length,
5984  "Invalid type for ref.get_desc: type %s has no custom descriptor",
5985  imm.heap_type().name().c_str());
5986  return 0;
5987  }
5988  Value ref = Pop(ValueType::RefNull(imm.heap_type()));
5989  Value* desc =
5990  Push(ValueType::Ref(this->module_->heap_type(type.descriptor))
5991  .AsExact(ref.type.exactness()));
5992  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(RefGetDesc, ref, desc);
5993  return opcode_length + imm.length;
5994  }
5995  case kExprRefCastDesc:
5996  case kExprRefCastDescNull: {
5997  NON_CONST_ONLY
5998  CHECK_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(custom_descriptors);
5999  HeapTypeImmediate imm(this->enabled_, this->detected_, this,
6000  this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
6001  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
6002  if (!VALIDATE(imm.type.has_index())) {
6003  this->DecodeError(
6004  this->pc_ + opcode_length,
6005  "ref.cast_desc: immediate type must have an index, but was %s",
6006  imm.type.name().c_str());
6007  return 0;
6008  }
6009  ModuleTypeIndex expected_desc_index =
6010  this->module_->type(imm.type.ref_index()).descriptor;
6011  if (!VALIDATE(expected_desc_index.valid())) {
6012  this->DecodeError(
6013  this->pc_ + opcode_length,
6014  "ref.cast_desc: immediate type %s must have a descriptor",
6015  imm.type.name().c_str());
6016  return 0;
6017  }
6018  ValueType expected_desc_type =
6019  ValueType::RefNull(this->module_->heap_type(expected_desc_index))
6020  .AsExact(imm.type.exactness());
6021  Value desc = Pop(expected_desc_type);
6022  // We will have to generalize the object's expected type to "top type of
6023  // imm.type" if/when values outside the anyref hierarchy can have custom
6024  // descriptors. This DCHECK should point that out when the time comes:
6025  DCHECK_EQ(imm.type.ref_type_kind(), RefTypeKind::kStruct);
6026  ValueType expected_obj_type = ValueType::Generic(
6027  GenericKind::kAny, kNullable, imm.type.is_shared());
6028  Value obj = Pop(expected_obj_type);
6029 
6030  bool null_succeeds = (opcode == kExprRefCastDescNull);
6031  ValueType target_type = ValueType::RefMaybeNull(
6032  imm.type, null_succeeds ? kNullable : kNonNullable);
6033  Value* value = Push(target_type);
6034 
6035  // TODO(403372470): Do we need to special-case casts that always fail
6036  // or always succeed?
6037 
6038  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(RefCastDesc, obj, desc, value);
6039 
6040  return opcode_length + imm.length;
6041  }
6042  case kExprRefCast:
6043  case kExprRefCastNull: {
6044  NON_CONST_ONLY
6045  HeapTypeImmediate imm(this->enabled_, this->detected_, this,
6046  this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
6047  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
6048  opcode_length += imm.length;
6049 
6050  Value obj = Pop();
6051 
6052  HeapType target_type = imm.type;
6053 
6054  if (!VALIDATE((obj.type.is_object_reference() &&
6055  IsSameTypeHierarchy(obj.type.heap_type(), target_type,
6056  this->module_)) ||
6057  obj.type.is_bottom())) {
6058  this->DecodeError(obj.pc(),
6059  "Invalid types for %s: %s of type %s has to "
6060  "be in the same reference type hierarchy as %s",
6061  WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode),
6062  SafeOpcodeNameAt(obj.pc()), obj.type.name().c_str(),
6063  ValueType::Ref(target_type).name().c_str());
6064  return 0;
6065  }
6066  if (!VALIDATE(!target_type.is_string_view())) {
6067  // TODO(12868): This reflects the current state of discussion at
6068  // https://github.com/WebAssembly/stringref/issues/40
6069  // It is suboptimal because it allows classifying a stringview_wtf16
6070  // as a stringref. This would be solved by making the views types
6071  // that aren't subtypes of anyref, which is one of the possible
6072  // resolutions of that discussion.
6073  this->DecodeError(
6074  this->pc_,
6075  "Invalid type for %s: string views are not classifiable",
6076  WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode));
6077  return 0;
6078  }
6079 
6080  bool null_succeeds = opcode == kExprRefCastNull;
6081  Value* value = Push(ValueType::RefMaybeNull(
6082  target_type, null_succeeds ? kNullable : kNonNullable));
6083  if (current_code_reachable_and_ok_) {
6084  // This logic ensures that code generation can assume that functions
6085  // can only be cast to function types, and data objects to data types.
6086  if (V8_UNLIKELY(TypeCheckAlwaysSucceeds(obj, target_type))) {
6087  if (obj.type.is_nullable() && !null_succeeds) {
6088  CALL_INTERFACE(AssertNotNullTypecheck, obj, value);
6089  } else {
6090  CALL_INTERFACE(Forward, obj, value);
6091  }
6092  } else if (V8_UNLIKELY(TypeCheckAlwaysFails(obj, target_type,
6093  null_succeeds))) {
6094  // Unrelated types. The only way this will not trap is if the object
6095  // is null.
6096  if (obj.type.is_nullable() && null_succeeds) {
6097  CALL_INTERFACE(AssertNullTypecheck, obj, value);
6098  } else {
6099  CALL_INTERFACE(Trap, TrapReason::kTrapIllegalCast);
6100  // We know that the following code is not reachable, but according
6101  // to the spec it technically is. Set it to spec-only reachable.
6102  SetSucceedingCodeDynamicallyUnreachable();
6103  }
6104  } else {
6105  if (target_type.is_index()) {
6106  CALL_INTERFACE(RefCast, obj, value);
6107  } else {
6108  CALL_INTERFACE(RefCastAbstract, obj, target_type, value,
6109  null_succeeds);
6110  }
6111  }
6112  }
6113  return opcode_length;
6114  }
6115  case kExprRefTestNull:
6116  case kExprRefTest: {
6117  NON_CONST_ONLY
6118  HeapTypeImmediate imm(this->enabled_, this->detected_, this,
6119  this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
6120  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
6121  opcode_length += imm.length;
6122 
6123  Value obj = Pop();
6124  HeapType target_type = imm.type;
6125  Value* result = Push(kWasmI32);
6126 
6127  if (!VALIDATE((obj.type.is_object_reference() &&
6128  IsSameTypeHierarchy(obj.type.heap_type(), target_type,
6129  this->module_)) ||
6130  obj.type.is_bottom())) {
6131  this->DecodeError(obj.pc(),
6132  "Invalid types for %s: %s of type %s has to "
6133  "be in the same reference type hierarchy as %s",
6134  WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode),
6135  SafeOpcodeNameAt(obj.pc()), obj.type.name().c_str(),
6136  ValueType::Ref(target_type).name().c_str());
6137  return 0;
6138  }
6139  if (!VALIDATE(!target_type.is_string_view())) {
6140  // TODO(12868): This reflects the current state of discussion at
6141  // https://github.com/WebAssembly/stringref/issues/40
6142  // It is suboptimal because it allows classifying a stringview_wtf16
6143  // as a stringref. This would be solved by making the views types
6144  // that aren't subtypes of anyref, which is one of the possible
6145  // resolutions of that discussion.
6146  this->DecodeError(
6147  this->pc_,
6148  "Invalid type for %s: string views are not classifiable",
6149  WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode));
6150  return 0;
6151  }
6152  bool null_succeeds = opcode == kExprRefTestNull;
6153  if (V8_LIKELY(current_code_reachable_and_ok_)) {
6154  // This logic ensures that code generation can assume that functions
6155  // can only be cast to function types, and data objects to data types.
6156  if (V8_UNLIKELY(TypeCheckAlwaysSucceeds(obj, target_type))) {
6157  // Type checking can still fail for null.
6158  if (obj.type.is_nullable() && !null_succeeds) {
6159  // We abuse ref.as_non_null, which isn't otherwise used as a unary
6160  // operator, as a sentinel for the negation of ref.is_null.
6161  CALL_INTERFACE(UnOp, kExprRefAsNonNull, obj, result);
6162  } else {
6163  CALL_INTERFACE(Drop);
6164  CALL_INTERFACE(I32Const, result, 1);
6165  }
6166  } else if (V8_UNLIKELY(TypeCheckAlwaysFails(obj, target_type,
6167  null_succeeds))) {
6168  CALL_INTERFACE(Drop);
6169  CALL_INTERFACE(I32Const, result, 0);
6170  } else {
6171  if (imm.type.is_index()) {
6172  CALL_INTERFACE(RefTest, imm.type, obj, result, null_succeeds);
6173  } else {
6174  CALL_INTERFACE(RefTestAbstract, obj, target_type, result,
6175  null_succeeds);
6176  }
6177  }
6178  }
6179  return opcode_length;
6180  }
6181  case kExprRefCastNop: {
6182  NON_CONST_ONLY
6183  // Temporary non-standard instruction, for performance experiments.
6184  if (!VALIDATE(v8_flags.experimental_wasm_ref_cast_nop)) {
6185  this->DecodeError(
6186  "Invalid opcode 0xfb4c (enable with "
6187  "--experimental-wasm-ref-cast-nop)");
6188  return 0;
6189  }
6190  HeapTypeImmediate imm(this->enabled_, this->detected_, this,
6191  this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
6192  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
6193  opcode_length += imm.length;
6194  HeapType target_type = imm.type;
6195  Value obj = Pop();
6196  if (!VALIDATE((obj.type.is_object_reference() &&
6197  IsSameTypeHierarchy(obj.type.heap_type(), target_type,
6198  this->module_)) ||
6199  obj.type.is_bottom())) {
6200  this->DecodeError(obj.pc(),
6201  "Invalid types for %s: %s of type %s has to "
6202  "be in the same reference type hierarchy as %s",
6203  WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode),
6204  SafeOpcodeNameAt(obj.pc()), obj.type.name().c_str(),
6205  ValueType::Ref(target_type).name().c_str());
6206  return 0;
6207  }
6208  Value* value = Push(ValueType::Ref(target_type));
6209  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(Forward, obj, value);
6210  return opcode_length;
6211  }
6212  case kExprBrOnCast:
6213  case kExprBrOnCastFail: {
6214  NON_CONST_ONLY
6215  return ParseBrOnCast(opcode, opcode_length);
6216  }
6217  case kExprBrOnCastDesc:
6218  case kExprBrOnCastDescFail: {
6219  NON_CONST_ONLY
6220  CHECK_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(custom_descriptors);
6221  return ParseBrOnCast(opcode, opcode_length);
6222  }
6223  case kExprAnyConvertExtern: {
6224  const bool is_shared = Peek().type.is_shared();
6225  Value extern_val = Pop(
6226  IndependentHeapType{GenericKind::kExtern, kNullable, is_shared});
6227  ValueType intern_type = IndependentHeapType{
6228  GenericKind::kAny, Nullability(extern_val.type.is_nullable()),
6229  is_shared};
6230  Value* intern_val = Push(intern_type);
6231  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(UnOp, kExprAnyConvertExtern,
6232  extern_val, intern_val);
6233  return opcode_length;
6234  }
6235  case kExprExternConvertAny: {
6236  const bool is_shared = Peek().type.is_shared();
6237  Value val =
6238  Pop(IndependentHeapType{GenericKind::kAny, kNullable, is_shared});
6239  ValueType extern_type =
6240  IndependentHeapType{GenericKind::kExtern,
6241  Nullability(val.type.is_nullable()), is_shared};
6242  Value* extern_val = Push(extern_type);
6243  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(UnOp, kExprExternConvertAny, val,
6244  extern_val);
6245  return opcode_length;
6246  }
6247  default:
6248  this->DecodeError("invalid gc opcode: %x", opcode);
6249  return 0;
6250  }
6251  }
6252 
6253  enum class WasmArrayAccess { kRead, kWrite };
6254 
6255  int ParseBrOnCast(WasmOpcode opcode, uint32_t pc_offset) {
6256  BrOnCastImmediate flags_imm(this, this->pc_ + pc_offset, validate);
6257  pc_offset += flags_imm.length;
6258  BrOnCastFlags flags = flags_imm.flags;
6259 
6260  BranchDepthImmediate branch_depth(this, this->pc_ + pc_offset, validate);
6261  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + pc_offset, branch_depth, control_.size())) {
6262  return 0;
6263  }
6264  pc_offset += branch_depth.length;
6265 
6266  HeapTypeImmediate src_imm(this->enabled_, this->detected_, this,
6267  this->pc_ + pc_offset, validate);
6268  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + pc_offset, src_imm)) return 0;
6269  pc_offset += src_imm.length;
6270  ValueType src_type = ValueType::RefMaybeNull(
6271  src_imm.type, flags.src_is_null ? kNullable : kNonNullable);
6272 
6273  const uint8_t* target_imm_pc = this->pc_ + pc_offset;
6274  HeapTypeImmediate target_imm(this->enabled_, this->detected_, this,
6275  target_imm_pc, validate);
6276  if (!this->Validate(target_imm_pc, target_imm)) return 0;
6277  pc_offset += target_imm.length;
6278  bool null_succeeds = flags.res_is_null;
6279  ValueType target_type = ValueType::RefMaybeNull(
6280  target_imm.type, null_succeeds ? kNullable : kNonNullable);
6281 
6282  if (!VALIDATE(IsSubtypeOf(target_type, src_type, this->module_))) {
6283  this->DecodeError("invalid types for %s: %s is not a subtype of %s",
6284  WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode),
6285  target_type.name().c_str(), src_type.name().c_str());
6286  return 0;
6287  }
6288 
6289  Value descriptor{nullptr, kWasmVoid};
6290  if (opcode == kExprBrOnCastDesc || opcode == kExprBrOnCastDescFail) {
6291  if (!VALIDATE(target_imm.type.has_index())) {
6292  this->DecodeError(
6293  target_imm_pc, "%s: target type must have an index, but was %s",
6294  WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode), target_imm.type.name().c_str());
6295  return 0;
6296  }
6297  ModuleTypeIndex target_desc_index =
6298  this->module_->type(target_imm.type.ref_index()).descriptor;
6299  if (!VALIDATE(target_desc_index.valid())) {
6300  this->DecodeError(
6301  target_imm_pc, "%s: target type %s must have a descriptor",
6302  WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode), target_imm.type.name().c_str());
6303  return 0;
6304  }
6305  ValueType desc_type =
6306  ValueType::RefNull(this->module_->heap_type(target_desc_index))
6307  .AsExact(target_type.exactness());
6308  descriptor = Pop(desc_type);
6309  }
6310 
6311  Value obj = Pop(src_type);
6312 
6313  if (!VALIDATE(
6314  (obj.type.is_object_reference() &&
6315  IsSameTypeHierarchy(obj.type.heap_type(), target_type.heap_type(),
6316  this->module_)) ||
6317  obj.type.is_bottom())) {
6318  this->DecodeError(obj.pc(),
6319  "invalid types for %s: %s of type %s has to "
6320  "be in the same reference type hierarchy as %s",
6321  WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode),
6322  SafeOpcodeNameAt(obj.pc()), obj.type.name().c_str(),
6323  target_type.name().c_str());
6324  return 0;
6325  }
6326 
6327  Control* c = control_at(branch_depth.depth);
6328  if (c->br_merge()->arity == 0) {
6329  this->DecodeError("%s must target a branch of arity at least 1",
6330  WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode));
6331  return 0;
6332  }
6333 
6334  if (opcode == kExprBrOnCast || opcode == kExprBrOnCastDesc) {
6335  Value* value_on_branch = Push(target_type);
6336  if (!VALIDATE(
6337  (TypeCheckBranch<PushBranchValues::kYes, RewriteStackTypes::kYes>(
6338  c)))) {
6339  return 0;
6340  }
6341  if (V8_LIKELY(current_code_reachable_and_ok_)) {
6342  // This logic ensures that code generation can assume that functions
6343  // can only be cast to function types, and data objects to data types.
6344  if (V8_UNLIKELY(
6345  TypeCheckAlwaysSucceeds(obj, target_type.heap_type()))) {
6346  // The branch will still not be taken on null if not
6347  // {null_succeeds}.
6348  if (obj.type.is_nullable() && !null_succeeds) {
6349  CALL_INTERFACE(BrOnNonNull, obj, value_on_branch,
6350  branch_depth.depth, false);
6351  } else {
6352  CALL_INTERFACE(Forward, obj, value_on_branch);
6353  CALL_INTERFACE(BrOrRet, branch_depth.depth);
6354  // We know that the following code is not reachable, but according
6355  // to the spec it technically is. Set it to spec-only reachable.
6356  SetSucceedingCodeDynamicallyUnreachable();
6357  }
6358  c->br_merge()->reached = true;
6359  } else if (V8_LIKELY(!TypeCheckAlwaysFails(obj, target_type.heap_type(),
6360  null_succeeds))) {
6361  if (opcode == kExprBrOnCastDesc) {
6362  CALL_INTERFACE(BrOnCastDesc, target_imm.type, obj, descriptor,
6363  value_on_branch, branch_depth.depth, null_succeeds);
6364  } else if (target_imm.type.is_index()) {
6365  CALL_INTERFACE(BrOnCast, target_imm.type, obj, value_on_branch,
6366  branch_depth.depth, null_succeeds);
6367  } else {
6368  CALL_INTERFACE(BrOnCastAbstract, obj, target_type.heap_type(),
6369  value_on_branch, branch_depth.depth, null_succeeds);
6370  }
6371  c->br_merge()->reached = true;
6372  }
6373  }
6374 
6375  Drop(*value_on_branch);
6376  Push(obj); // Restore stack state on fallthrough.
6377  // The fallthrough type is the source type as specified in the br_on_cast
6378  // instruction. This can be a super type of the stack value. Furthermore
6379  // nullability gets refined to non-nullable if the cast target is
6380  // nullable, meaning the branch will be taken on null.
6381  DCHECK(!src_type.heap_type().is_bottom());
6382  bool fallthrough_nullable = flags.src_is_null && !flags.res_is_null;
6383  stack_value(1)->type = ValueType::RefMaybeNull(
6384  src_type.heap_type(),
6385  fallthrough_nullable ? kNullable : kNonNullable);
6386  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(Forward, obj, stack_value(1));
6387  return pc_offset;
6388 
6389  } else {
6390  DCHECK(opcode == kExprBrOnCastFail || opcode == kExprBrOnCastDescFail);
6391  // The branch type is set based on the source type immediate (independent
6392  // of the actual stack value). If the target type is nullable, the branch
6393  // type is non-nullable.
6394  Push(flags.res_is_null ? src_type.AsNonNull() : src_type);
6395  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(Forward, obj, stack_value(1));
6396 
6397  if (!VALIDATE(
6398  (TypeCheckBranch<PushBranchValues::kYes, RewriteStackTypes::kYes>(
6399  c)))) {
6400  return 0;
6401  }
6402 
6403  Value result_on_fallthrough = CreateValue(target_type);
6404  if (V8_LIKELY(current_code_reachable_and_ok_)) {
6405  // This logic ensures that code generation can assume that functions
6406  // can only be cast between compatible types.
6407  if (V8_UNLIKELY(TypeCheckAlwaysFails(obj, target_type.heap_type(),
6408  null_succeeds))) {
6409  // The types are incompatible (i.e. neither of the two types is a
6410  // subtype of the other). Always branch.
6411  CALL_INTERFACE(Forward, obj, stack_value(1));
6412  CALL_INTERFACE(BrOrRet, branch_depth.depth);
6413  // We know that the following code is not reachable, but according
6414  // to the spec it technically is. Set it to spec-only reachable.
6415  SetSucceedingCodeDynamicallyUnreachable();
6416  c->br_merge()->reached = true;
6417  } else if (V8_UNLIKELY(
6418  TypeCheckAlwaysSucceeds(obj, target_type.heap_type()))) {
6419  // The branch can still be taken on null.
6420  if (obj.type.is_nullable() && !null_succeeds) {
6421  CALL_INTERFACE(BrOnNull, obj, branch_depth.depth, true,
6422  &result_on_fallthrough);
6423  c->br_merge()->reached = true;
6424  } else {
6425  // Otherwise, the type check always succeeds. Do not branch. Also,
6426  // make sure the object remains on the stack.
6427  result_on_fallthrough = obj;
6428  }
6429  } else {
6430  if (opcode == kExprBrOnCastDescFail) {
6431  CALL_INTERFACE(BrOnCastDescFail, target_imm.type, obj, descriptor,
6432  &result_on_fallthrough, branch_depth.depth,
6433  null_succeeds);
6434  } else if (target_imm.type.is_index()) {
6435  CALL_INTERFACE(BrOnCastFail, target_imm.type, obj,
6436  &result_on_fallthrough, branch_depth.depth,
6437  null_succeeds);
6438  } else {
6439  CALL_INTERFACE(BrOnCastFailAbstract, obj, target_type.heap_type(),
6440  &result_on_fallthrough, branch_depth.depth,
6441  null_succeeds);
6442  }
6443  c->br_merge()->reached = true;
6444  }
6445  }
6446  // Make sure the correct value is on the stack state on fallthrough.
6447  Drop(obj);
6448  Push(result_on_fallthrough);
6449  return pc_offset;
6450  }
6451  }
6452 
6453  int DecodeStringNewWtf8(unibrow::Utf8Variant variant,
6454  uint32_t opcode_length) {
6455  NON_CONST_ONLY
6456  bool null_on_invalid = variant == unibrow::Utf8Variant::kUtf8NoTrap;
6457  MemoryIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
6458  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
6459  ValueType addr_type = MemoryAddressType(imm.memory);
6460  auto [offset, size] = Pop(addr_type, kWasmI32);
6461  Value* result = Push(ValueType::RefMaybeNull(
6462  kWasmStringRef, null_on_invalid ? kNullable : kNonNullable));
6463  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringNewWtf8, imm, variant, offset,
6464  size, result);
6465  return opcode_length + imm.length;
6466  }

6468  int DecodeStringMeasureWtf8(unibrow::Utf8Variant variant,
6469  uint32_t opcode_length) {
6470  NON_CONST_ONLY
6471  Value str = Pop(kWasmStringRef);
6472  Value* result = Push(kWasmI32);
6473  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringMeasureWtf8, variant, str, result);
6474  return opcode_length;
6475  }

6477  int DecodeStringEncodeWtf8(unibrow::Utf8Variant variant,
6478  uint32_t opcode_length) {

6481  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
6482  ValueType addr_type = MemoryAddressType(imm.memory);
6483  auto [str, addr] = Pop(kWasmStringRef, addr_type);
6484  Value* result = Push(kWasmI32);
6485  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringEncodeWtf8, imm, variant, str,
6486  addr, result);
6487  return opcode_length + imm.length;
6488  }

6490  int DecodeStringViewWtf8Encode(unibrow::Utf8Variant variant,
6491  uint32_t opcode_length) {
6492  NON_CONST_ONLY

6494  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
6495  ValueType addr_type = MemoryAddressType(imm.memory);
6496  auto [view, addr, pos, bytes] =
6497  Pop(kWasmStringViewWtf8, addr_type, kWasmI32, kWasmI32);
6498  Value* next_pos = Push(kWasmI32);
6499  Value* bytes_out = Push(kWasmI32);
6500  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringViewWtf8Encode, imm, variant, view,
6501  addr, pos, bytes, next_pos, bytes_out);
6502  return opcode_length + imm.length;
6503  }

6505  int DecodeStringNewWtf8Array(unibrow::Utf8Variant variant,
6506  uint32_t opcode_length) {
6507  NON_CONST_ONLY
6508  Value end = Pop(2, kWasmI32);
6509  Value start = Pop(1, kWasmI32);
6510  Value array = PopPackedArray(0, kWasmI8, WasmArrayAccess::kRead);
6511  bool null_on_invalid = variant == unibrow::Utf8Variant::kUtf8NoTrap;
6512  Value* result = Push(ValueType::RefMaybeNull(
6513  kWasmStringRef, null_on_invalid ? kNullable : kNonNullable));
6514  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringNewWtf8Array, variant, array,
6515  start, end, result);
6516  return opcode_length;
6517  }

6519  int DecodeStringEncodeWtf8Array(unibrow::Utf8Variant variant,

6521  NON_CONST_ONLY
6522  Value start = Pop(2, kWasmI32);
6523  Value array = PopPackedArray(1, kWasmI8, WasmArrayAccess::kWrite);
6524  Value str = Pop(0, kWasmStringRef);
6525  Value* result = Push(kWasmI32);

6527  array, start, result);
