6531  int DecodeStringRefOpcode(WasmOpcode opcode, uint32_t opcode_length) {
6532  // Fast check for out-of-range opcodes (only allow 0xfbXX).
6533  // This might help the big switch below.
6534  if (!VALIDATE((opcode >> 8) == kGCPrefix)) {
6535  this->DecodeError("invalid stringref opcode: %x", opcode);
6536  return 0;
6537  }
6538 
6539  switch (opcode) {
6540  case kExprStringNewUtf8:
6541  return DecodeStringNewWtf8(unibrow::Utf8Variant::kUtf8, opcode_length);
6542  case kExprStringNewUtf8Try:
6543  return DecodeStringNewWtf8(unibrow::Utf8Variant::kUtf8NoTrap,
6544  opcode_length);
6545  case kExprStringNewLossyUtf8:
6546  return DecodeStringNewWtf8(unibrow::Utf8Variant::kLossyUtf8,
6547  opcode_length);
6548  case kExprStringNewWtf8:
6549  return DecodeStringNewWtf8(unibrow::Utf8Variant::kWtf8, opcode_length);
6550  case kExprStringNewWtf16: {
6551  NON_CONST_ONLY
6552  MemoryIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
6553  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
6554  ValueType addr_type = MemoryAddressType(imm.memory);
6555  auto [offset, size] = Pop(addr_type, kWasmI32);
6556  Value* result = Push(kWasmRefString);
6557  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringNewWtf16, imm, offset, size,
6558  result);
6559  return opcode_length + imm.length;
6560  }
6561  case kExprStringConst: {
6562  StringConstImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
6563  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
6564  Value* result = Push(kWasmRefString);
6565  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringConst, imm, result);
6566  return opcode_length + imm.length;
6567  }
6568  case kExprStringMeasureUtf8:
6569  return DecodeStringMeasureWtf8(unibrow::Utf8Variant::kUtf8,
6570  opcode_length);
6571  case kExprStringMeasureWtf8:
6572  return DecodeStringMeasureWtf8(unibrow::Utf8Variant::kWtf8,
6573  opcode_length);
6574  case kExprStringMeasureWtf16: {
6575  NON_CONST_ONLY
6576  Value str = Pop(kWasmStringRef);
6577  Value* result = Push(kWasmI32);
6578  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringMeasureWtf16, str, result);
6579  return opcode_length;
6580  }
6581  case kExprStringEncodeUtf8:
6582  return DecodeStringEncodeWtf8(unibrow::Utf8Variant::kUtf8,
6583  opcode_length);
6584  case kExprStringEncodeLossyUtf8:
6585  return DecodeStringEncodeWtf8(unibrow::Utf8Variant::kLossyUtf8,
6586  opcode_length);
6587  case kExprStringEncodeWtf8:
6588  return DecodeStringEncodeWtf8(unibrow::Utf8Variant::kWtf8,
6589  opcode_length);
6590  case kExprStringEncodeWtf16: {
6591  NON_CONST_ONLY
6592  MemoryIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
6593  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
6594  ValueType addr_type = MemoryAddressType(imm.memory);
6595  auto [str, addr] = Pop(kWasmStringRef, addr_type);
6596  Value* result = Push(kWasmI32);
6597  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringEncodeWtf16, imm, str, addr,
6598  result);
6599  return opcode_length + imm.length;
6600  }
6601  case kExprStringConcat: {
6602  NON_CONST_ONLY
6603  auto [head, tail] = Pop(kWasmStringRef, kWasmStringRef);
6604  Value* result = Push(kWasmRefString);
6605  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringConcat, head, tail, result);
6606  return opcode_length;
6607  }
6608  case kExprStringEq: {
6609  NON_CONST_ONLY
6610  auto [a, b] = Pop(kWasmStringRef, kWasmStringRef);
6611  Value* result = Push(kWasmI32);
6612  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringEq, a, b, result);
6613  return opcode_length;
6614  }
6615  case kExprStringIsUSVSequence: {
6616  NON_CONST_ONLY
6617  Value str = Pop(kWasmStringRef);
6618  Value* result = Push(kWasmI32);
6619  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringIsUSVSequence, str, result);
6620  return opcode_length;
6621  }
6622  case kExprStringAsWtf8: {
6623  NON_CONST_ONLY
6624  Value str = Pop(kWasmStringRef);
6625  Value* result = Push(kWasmStringViewWtf8);
6626  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringAsWtf8, str, result);
6627  return opcode_length;
6628  }
6629  case kExprStringViewWtf8Advance: {
6630  NON_CONST_ONLY
6631  auto [view, pos, bytes] = Pop(kWasmStringViewWtf8, kWasmI32, kWasmI32);
6632  Value* result = Push(kWasmI32);
6633  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringViewWtf8Advance, view, pos,
6634  bytes, result);
6635  return opcode_length;
6636  }
6637  case kExprStringViewWtf8EncodeUtf8:
6638  return DecodeStringViewWtf8Encode(unibrow::Utf8Variant::kUtf8,
6639  opcode_length);
6640  case kExprStringViewWtf8EncodeLossyUtf8:
6641  return DecodeStringViewWtf8Encode(unibrow::Utf8Variant::kLossyUtf8,
6642  opcode_length);
6643  case kExprStringViewWtf8EncodeWtf8:
6644  return DecodeStringViewWtf8Encode(unibrow::Utf8Variant::kWtf8,
6645  opcode_length);
6646  case kExprStringViewWtf8Slice: {
6647  NON_CONST_ONLY
6648  auto [view, start, end] = Pop(kWasmStringViewWtf8, kWasmI32, kWasmI32);
6649  Value* result = Push(kWasmRefString);
6650  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringViewWtf8Slice, view, start,
6651  end, result);
6652  return opcode_length;
6653  }
6654  case kExprStringAsWtf16: {
6655  NON_CONST_ONLY
6656  Value str = Pop(kWasmStringRef);
6657  Value* result = Push(kWasmStringViewWtf16);
6658  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringAsWtf16, str, result);
6659  return opcode_length;
6660  }
6661  case kExprStringViewWtf16Length: {
6662  NON_CONST_ONLY
6663  Value view = Pop(kWasmStringViewWtf16);
6664  Value* result = Push(kWasmI32);
6665  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringMeasureWtf16, view, result);
6666  return opcode_length;
6667  }
6668  case kExprStringViewWtf16GetCodeunit: {
6669  NON_CONST_ONLY
6670  auto [view, pos] = Pop(kWasmStringViewWtf16, kWasmI32);
6671  Value* result = Push(kWasmI32);
6672  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringViewWtf16GetCodeUnit, view,
6673  pos, result);
6674  return opcode_length;
6675  }
6676  case kExprStringViewWtf16Encode: {
6677  NON_CONST_ONLY
6678  MemoryIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
6679  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
6680  ValueType addr_type = MemoryAddressType(imm.memory);
6681  auto [view, addr, pos, codeunits] =
6682  Pop(kWasmStringViewWtf16, addr_type, kWasmI32, kWasmI32);
6683  Value* result = Push(kWasmI32);
6684  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringViewWtf16Encode, imm, view,
6685  addr, pos, codeunits, result);
6686  return opcode_length + imm.length;
6687  }
6688  case kExprStringViewWtf16Slice: {
6689  NON_CONST_ONLY
6690  auto [view, start, end] = Pop(kWasmStringViewWtf16, kWasmI32, kWasmI32);
6691  Value* result = Push(kWasmRefString);
6692  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringViewWtf16Slice, view, start,
6693  end, result);
6694  return opcode_length;
6695  }
6696  case kExprStringAsIter: {
6697  NON_CONST_ONLY
6698  Value str = Pop(kWasmStringRef);
6699  Value* result = Push(kWasmStringViewIter);
6700  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringAsIter, str, result);
6701  return opcode_length;
6702  }
6703  case kExprStringViewIterNext: {
6704  NON_CONST_ONLY
6705  Value view = Pop(kWasmStringViewIter);
6706  Value* result = Push(kWasmI32);
6707  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringViewIterNext, view, result);
6708  return opcode_length;
6709  }
6710  case kExprStringViewIterAdvance: {
6711  NON_CONST_ONLY
6712  auto [view, codepoints] = Pop(kWasmStringViewIter, kWasmI32);
6713  Value* result = Push(kWasmI32);
6714  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringViewIterAdvance, view,
6715  codepoints, result);
6716  return opcode_length;
6717  }
6718  case kExprStringViewIterRewind: {
6719  NON_CONST_ONLY
6720  auto [view, codepoints] = Pop(kWasmStringViewIter, kWasmI32);
6721  Value* result = Push(kWasmI32);
6722  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringViewIterRewind, view,
6723  codepoints, result);
6724  return opcode_length;
6725  }
6726  case kExprStringViewIterSlice: {
6727  NON_CONST_ONLY
6728  auto [view, codepoints] = Pop(kWasmStringViewIter, kWasmI32);
6729  Value* result = Push(kWasmRefString);
6730  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringViewIterSlice, view,
6731  codepoints, result);
6732  return opcode_length;
6733  }
6734  case kExprStringNewUtf8Array:
6735  return DecodeStringNewWtf8Array(unibrow::Utf8Variant::kUtf8,
6736  opcode_length);
6737  case kExprStringNewUtf8ArrayTry:
6738  return DecodeStringNewWtf8Array(unibrow::Utf8Variant::kUtf8NoTrap,
6739  opcode_length);
6740  case kExprStringNewLossyUtf8Array:
6741  return DecodeStringNewWtf8Array(unibrow::Utf8Variant::kLossyUtf8,
6742  opcode_length);
6743  case kExprStringNewWtf8Array:
6744  return DecodeStringNewWtf8Array(unibrow::Utf8Variant::kWtf8,
6745  opcode_length);
6746  case kExprStringNewWtf16Array: {
6747  NON_CONST_ONLY
6748  Value end = Pop(2, kWasmI32);
6749  Value start = Pop(1, kWasmI32);
6750  Value array = PopPackedArray(0, kWasmI16, WasmArrayAccess::kRead);
6751  Value* result = Push(kWasmRefString);
6752  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringNewWtf16Array, array, start,
6753  end, result);
6754  return opcode_length;
6755  }
6756  case kExprStringEncodeUtf8Array:
6757  return DecodeStringEncodeWtf8Array(unibrow::Utf8Variant::kUtf8,
6758  opcode_length);
6759  case kExprStringEncodeLossyUtf8Array:
6760  return DecodeStringEncodeWtf8Array(unibrow::Utf8Variant::kLossyUtf8,
6761  opcode_length);
6762  case kExprStringEncodeWtf8Array:
6763  return DecodeStringEncodeWtf8Array(unibrow::Utf8Variant::kWtf8,
6764  opcode_length);
6765  case kExprStringEncodeWtf16Array: {
6766  NON_CONST_ONLY
6767  Value start = Pop(2, kWasmI32);
6768  Value array = PopPackedArray(1, kWasmI16, WasmArrayAccess::kWrite);
6769  Value str = Pop(0, kWasmStringRef);
6770  Value* result = Push(kWasmI32);
6771  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringEncodeWtf16Array, str, array,
6772  start, result);
6773  return opcode_length;
6774  }
6775  case kExprStringCompare: {
6776  NON_CONST_ONLY
6777  auto [lhs, rhs] = Pop(kWasmStringRef, kWasmStringRef);
6778  Value* result = Push(kWasmI32);
6779  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringCompare, lhs, rhs, result);
6780  return opcode_length;
6781  }
6782  case kExprStringFromCodePoint: {
6783  NON_CONST_ONLY
6784  Value code_point = Pop(kWasmI32);
6785  Value* result = Push(kWasmRefString);
6786  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringFromCodePoint, code_point,
6787  result);
6788  return opcode_length;
6789  }
6790  case kExprStringHash: {
6791  NON_CONST_ONLY
6792  Value string = Pop(kWasmStringRef);
6793  Value* result = Push(kWasmI32);
6794  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StringHash, string, result);
6795  return opcode_length;
6796  }
6797  default:
6798  this->DecodeError("invalid stringref opcode: %x", opcode);
6799  return 0;
6800  }
6801  }
6802 
6803  uint32_t DecodeAtomicOpcode(WasmOpcode opcode, uint32_t opcode_length) {
6804  // Fast check for out-of-range opcodes (only allow 0xfeXX).
6805  if (!VALIDATE((opcode >> 8) == kAtomicPrefix)) {
6806  this->DecodeError("invalid atomic opcode: 0x%x", opcode);
6807  return 0;
6808  }
6809 
6810  MachineType memtype;
6811  switch (opcode) {
6812 #define CASE_ATOMIC_STORE_OP(Name, Type) \
6813  case kExpr##Name: { \
6814  this->detected_->add_threads(); \
6815  memtype = MachineType::Type(); \
6816  break; /* to generic mem access code below */ \
6817  }
6818  ATOMIC_STORE_OP_LIST(CASE_ATOMIC_STORE_OP)
6819 #undef CASE_ATOMIC_STORE_OP
6820 #define CASE_ATOMIC_OP(Name, Type) \
6821  case kExpr##Name: { \
6822  this->detected_->add_threads(); \
6823  memtype = MachineType::Type(); \
6824  break; /* to generic mem access code below */ \
6825  }
6826  ATOMIC_OP_LIST(CASE_ATOMIC_OP)
6827 #undef CASE_ATOMIC_OP
6828  case kExprAtomicFence: {
6829  this->detected_->add_threads();
6830  uint8_t zero = this->template read_u8<ValidationTag>(
6831  this->pc_ + opcode_length, "zero");
6832  if (!VALIDATE(zero == 0)) {
6833  this->DecodeError(this->pc_ + opcode_length,
6834  "invalid atomic operand");
6835  return 0;
6836  }
6837  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(AtomicFence);
6838  return 1 + opcode_length;
6839  }
6840  case kExprStructAtomicGetS:
6841  case kExprStructAtomicGetU: {
6842  CHECK_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(shared);
6843  NON_CONST_ONLY
6844  MemoryOrderImmediate memory_order(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length,
6845  validate);
6846  if (!this->ok()) return 0;
6847  FieldImmediate field(
6848  this, this->pc_ + opcode_length + memory_order.length, validate);
6849  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length + memory_order.length,
6850  field)) {
6851  return 0;
6852  }
6853  ValueType field_type =
6854  field.struct_imm.struct_type->field(field.field_imm.index);
6855  if (!VALIDATE(field_type.is_packed())) {
6856  this->DecodeError(
6857  "%s: Field %d of type %d has non-packed type %s. Use "
6858  "struct.atomic.get instead.",
6859  WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode), field.field_imm.index,
6860  field.struct_imm.index.index, field_type.name().c_str());
6861  return 0;
6862  }
6863  Value struct_obj =
6864  Pop(ValueType::RefNull(field.struct_imm.heap_type()));
6865  Value* value = Push(field_type.Unpacked());
6866  const bool is_signed = opcode == kExprStructAtomicGetS;
6867  if (struct_obj.type.is_shared()) {
6868  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StructAtomicGet, struct_obj, field,
6869  is_signed, memory_order.order,
6870  value);
6871  } else {
6872  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StructGet, struct_obj, field,
6873  is_signed, value);
6874  }
6875  return opcode_length + memory_order.length + field.length;
6876  }
6877  case kExprStructAtomicGet: {
6878  CHECK_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(shared);
6879  NON_CONST_ONLY
6880  MemoryOrderImmediate memory_order(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length,
6881  validate);
6882  if (!this->ok()) return 0;
6883  FieldImmediate field(
6884  this, this->pc_ + opcode_length + memory_order.length, validate);
6885  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length + memory_order.length,
6886  field)) {
6887  return 0;
6888  }
6889  ValueType field_type =
6890  field.struct_imm.struct_type->field(field.field_imm.index);
6891  if (!VALIDATE(field_type == kWasmI32 || field_type == kWasmI64 ||
6892  (field_type.is_ref() &&
6893  (IsSubtypeOf(field_type, kWasmAnyRef, this->module_) ||
6894  IsSubtypeOf(field_type, kWasmSharedAnyRef,
6895  this->module_))))) {
6896  this->DecodeError(
6897  "struct.atomic.get: Field %d of type %d has invalid type %s ",
6898  field.field_imm.index, field.struct_imm.index.index,
6899  field_type.name().c_str());
6900  return 0;
6901  }
6902  Value struct_obj =
6903  Pop(ValueType::RefNull(field.struct_imm.heap_type()));
6904  Value* value = Push(field_type);
6905  if (struct_obj.type.is_shared()) {
6906  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StructAtomicGet, struct_obj, field,
6907  true, memory_order.order, value);
6908  } else {
6909  // Emitting atomic operations for unshared types as well would require
6910  // aligning all i64 fields in them, potentially regressing memory
6911  // usage.
6912  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StructGet, struct_obj, field, true,
6913  value);
6914  }
6915  return opcode_length + memory_order.length + field.length;
6916  }
6917  case kExprStructAtomicSet: {
6918  CHECK_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(shared);
6919  NON_CONST_ONLY
6920  MemoryOrderImmediate memory_order(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length,
6921  validate);
6922  if (!this->ok()) return 0;
6923  FieldImmediate field(
6924  this, this->pc_ + opcode_length + memory_order.length, validate);
6925  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length + memory_order.length,
6926  field)) {
6927  return 0;
6928  }
6929  const StructType* struct_type = field.struct_imm.struct_type;
6930  if (!VALIDATE(struct_type->mutability(field.field_imm.index))) {
6931  this->DecodeError(
6932  "struct.atomic.set: Field %d of type %d is immutable.",
6933  field.field_imm.index, field.struct_imm.index.index);
6934  return 0;
6935  }
6936  ValueType field_type = struct_type->field(field.field_imm.index);
6937  if (!VALIDATE(field_type == kWasmI8 || field_type == kWasmI16 ||
6938  field_type == kWasmI32 || field_type == kWasmI64 ||
6939  (field_type.is_ref() &&
6940  (IsSubtypeOf(field_type, kWasmAnyRef, this->module_) ||
6941  IsSubtypeOf(field_type, kWasmSharedAnyRef,
6942  this->module_))))) {
6943  this->DecodeError(
6944  "struct.atomic.set: Field %d of type %d has invalid type %s ",
6945  field.field_imm.index, field.struct_imm.index.index,
6946  field_type.name().c_str());
6947  return 0;
6948  }
6949  auto [struct_obj, field_value] =
6950  Pop(ValueType::RefNull(field.struct_imm.heap_type()),
6951  struct_type->field(field.field_imm.index).Unpacked());
6952  if (struct_obj.type.is_shared()) {
6953  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StructAtomicSet, struct_obj, field,
6954  field_value, memory_order.order);
6955  } else {
6956  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StructSet, struct_obj, field,
6957  field_value);
6958  }
6959  return opcode_length + field.length + memory_order.length;
6960  }
6961  case kExprStructAtomicAdd:
6962  case kExprStructAtomicSub:
6963  case kExprStructAtomicAnd:
6964  case kExprStructAtomicOr:
6965  case kExprStructAtomicXor:
6966  case kExprStructAtomicExchange: {
6967  CHECK_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(shared);
6968  NON_CONST_ONLY
6969  MemoryOrderImmediate memory_order(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length,
6970  validate);
6971  if (!this->ok()) return 0;
6972  FieldImmediate field(
6973  this, this->pc_ + opcode_length + memory_order.length, validate);
6974  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length + memory_order.length,
6975  field)) {
6976  return 0;
6977  }
6978  const StructType* struct_type = field.struct_imm.struct_type;
6979  if (!VALIDATE(struct_type->mutability(field.field_imm.index))) {
6980  this->DecodeError("%s: Field %d of type %d is immutable.",
6981  WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode),
6982  field.field_imm.index,
6983  field.struct_imm.index.index);
6984  return 0;
6985  }
6986  ValueType field_type = struct_type->field(field.field_imm.index);
6987  if (!VALIDATE(field_type == kWasmI32 || field_type == kWasmI64 ||
6988  (opcode == kExprStructAtomicExchange &&
6989  IsSubtypeOf(field_type.AsNonShared(), kWasmAnyRef,
6990  this->module_)))) {
6991  this->DecodeError("%s: Field %d of type %d has invalid type %s ",
6992  WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode),
6993  field.field_imm.index, field.struct_imm.index.index,
6994  field_type.name().c_str());
6995  return 0;
6996  }
6997  auto [struct_obj, field_value] =
6998  Pop(ValueType::RefNull(field.struct_imm.heap_type()), field_type);
6999  Value* result = Push(field_type);
7000  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(StructAtomicRMW, opcode, struct_obj,
7001  field, field_value,
7002  memory_order.order, result);
7003  return opcode_length + field.length + memory_order.length;
7004  }
7005  case kExprStructAtomicCompareExchange: {
7006  CHECK_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(shared);
7007  NON_CONST_ONLY
7008  MemoryOrderImmediate memory_order(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length,
7009  validate);
7010  if (!this->ok()) return 0;
7011  FieldImmediate field(
7012  this, this->pc_ + opcode_length + memory_order.length, validate);
7013  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length + memory_order.length,
7014  field)) {
7015  return 0;
7016  }
7017  const StructType* struct_type = field.struct_imm.struct_type;
7018  if (!VALIDATE(struct_type->mutability(field.field_imm.index))) {
7019  this->DecodeError("%s: Field %d of type %d is immutable.",
7020  WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode),
7021  field.field_imm.index,
7022  field.struct_imm.index.index);
7023  return 0;
7024  }
7025  ValueType field_type = struct_type->field(field.field_imm.index);
7026  if (!VALIDATE(field_type == kWasmI32 || field_type == kWasmI64 ||
7027  IsSubtypeOf(field_type.AsNonShared(), kWasmEqRef,
7028  this->module_))) {
7029  this->DecodeError("%s: Field %d of type %d has invalid type %s ",
7030  WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode),
7031  field.field_imm.index, field.struct_imm.index.index,
7032  field_type.name().c_str());
7033  return 0;
7034  }
7035  auto [struct_obj, expected_value, new_value] =
7036  Pop(ValueType::RefNull(field.struct_imm.heap_type()), field_type,
7037  field_type);
7038  Value* result = Push(field_type);
7039  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(
7040  StructAtomicCompareExchange, opcode, struct_obj, field,
7041  expected_value, new_value, memory_order.order, result);
7042  return opcode_length + field.length + memory_order.length;
7043  }
7044  case kExprArrayAtomicGet: {
7045  CHECK_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(shared);
7046  NON_CONST_ONLY
7047  MemoryOrderImmediate memory_order(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length,
7048  validate);
7049  if (!this->ok()) return 0;
7050  ArrayIndexImmediate imm(
7051  this, this->pc_ + memory_order.length + opcode_length, validate);
7052  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + memory_order.length + opcode_length,
7053  imm)) {
7054  return 0;
7055  }
7056  ValueType element_type = imm.array_type->element_type();
7057  if (!VALIDATE(element_type == kWasmI32 || element_type == kWasmI64 ||
7058  (element_type.is_ref() &&
7059  (IsSubtypeOf(element_type, kWasmAnyRef, this->module_) ||
7060  IsSubtypeOf(element_type, kWasmSharedAnyRef,
7061  this->module_))))) {
7062  this->DecodeError(
7063  "array.atomic.get: Array %d has invalid element type %s ",
7064  imm.index.index, imm.array_type->element_type().name().c_str());
7065  return 0;
7066  }
7067  auto [array_obj, index] =
7068  Pop(ValueType::RefNull(imm.heap_type()), kWasmI32);
7069  Value* value = Push(imm.array_type->element_type());
7070  if (array_obj.type.is_shared()) {
7071  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ArrayAtomicGet, array_obj, imm,
7072  index, true, memory_order.order,
7073  value);
7074  } else {
7075  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ArrayGet, array_obj, imm, index,
7076  true, value);
7077  }
7078  return opcode_length + memory_order.length + imm.length;
7079  }
7080  case kExprArrayAtomicGetS:
7081  case kExprArrayAtomicGetU: {
7082  CHECK_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(shared);
7083  NON_CONST_ONLY
7084  MemoryOrderImmediate memory_order(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length,
7085  validate);
7086  if (!this->ok()) return 0;
7087  ArrayIndexImmediate imm(
7088  this, this->pc_ + memory_order.length + opcode_length, validate);
7089  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + memory_order.length + opcode_length,
7090  imm)) {
7091  return 0;
7092  }
7093  if (!VALIDATE(imm.array_type->element_type().is_packed())) {
7094  this->DecodeError(
7095  "%s: Array type %d has non-packed type %s. Use "
7096  "array.atomic.get instead.",
7097  WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode), imm.index.index,
7098  imm.array_type->element_type().name().c_str());
7099  return 0;
7100  }
7101  auto [array_obj, index] =
7102  Pop(ValueType::RefNull(imm.heap_type()), kWasmI32);
7103  Value* value = Push(imm.array_type->element_type().Unpacked());
7104  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ArrayGet, array_obj, imm, index,
7105  opcode == kExprArrayAtomicGetS,
7106  value);
7107  return opcode_length + memory_order.length + imm.length;
7108  }
7109  case kExprArrayAtomicSet: {
7110  CHECK_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(shared);
7111  NON_CONST_ONLY
7112  MemoryOrderImmediate memory_order(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length,
7113  validate);
7114  if (!this->ok()) return 0;
7115  ArrayIndexImmediate imm(
7116  this, this->pc_ + opcode_length + memory_order.length, validate);
7117  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length + memory_order.length,
7118  imm)) {
7119  return 0;
7120  }
7121  if (!VALIDATE(imm.array_type->mutability())) {
7122  this->DecodeError("array.atomic.set: Array type %d is immutable",
7123  imm.index.index);
7124  return 0;
7125  }
7126  ValueType element_type = imm.array_type->element_type();
7127  if (!VALIDATE(element_type == kWasmI8 || element_type == kWasmI16 ||
7128  element_type == kWasmI32 || element_type == kWasmI64 ||
7129  (element_type.is_ref() &&
7130  (IsSubtypeOf(element_type, kWasmAnyRef, this->module_) ||
7131  IsSubtypeOf(element_type, kWasmSharedAnyRef,
7132  this->module_))))) {
7133  this->DecodeError(
7134  "array.atomic.set: Array type %d has invalid type %s ", imm.index,
7135  element_type.name().c_str());
7136  return 0;
7137  }
7138  auto [array_obj, index, value] =
7139  Pop(ValueType::RefNull(imm.heap_type()), kWasmI32,
7140  imm.array_type->element_type().Unpacked());
7141  if (imm.heap_type().is_shared()) {
7142  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ArrayAtomicSet, array_obj, imm,
7143  index, value, memory_order.order);
7144  } else {
7145  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ArraySet, array_obj, imm, index,
7146  value);
7147  }
7148  return opcode_length + memory_order.length + imm.length;
7149  }
7150  case kExprArrayAtomicAdd:
7151  case kExprArrayAtomicSub:
7152  case kExprArrayAtomicAnd:
7153  case kExprArrayAtomicOr:
7154  case kExprArrayAtomicXor:
7155  case kExprArrayAtomicExchange: {
7156  CHECK_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(shared);
7157  NON_CONST_ONLY
7158  MemoryOrderImmediate memory_order(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length,
7159  validate);
7160  if (!this->ok()) return 0;
7161  ArrayIndexImmediate imm(
7162  this, this->pc_ + opcode_length + memory_order.length, validate);
7163  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length + memory_order.length,
7164  imm)) {
7165  return 0;
7166  }
7167  if (!VALIDATE(imm.array_type->mutability())) {
7168  this->DecodeError("%s: Array type %d is immutable",
7169  WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode), imm.index.index);
7170  return 0;
7171  }
7172  ValueType element_type = imm.array_type->element_type();
7173  if (!VALIDATE(element_type == kWasmI32 || element_type == kWasmI64 ||
7174  (opcode == kExprArrayAtomicExchange &&
7175  IsSubtypeOf(element_type.AsNonShared(), kWasmAnyRef,
7176  this->module_)))) {
7177  this->DecodeError("%s: Array type %d has invalid type %s ",
7178  WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode), imm.index,
7179  element_type.name().c_str());
7180  return 0;
7181  }
7182  auto [array_obj, index, value] =
7183  Pop(ValueType::RefNull(imm.heap_type()), kWasmI32, element_type);
7184  Value* result = Push(element_type);
7185  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ArrayAtomicRMW, opcode, array_obj,
7186  imm, index, value,
7187  memory_order.order, result);
7188  return opcode_length + memory_order.length + imm.length;
7189  }
7190  case kExprArrayAtomicCompareExchange: {
7191  CHECK_PROTOTYPE_OPCODE(shared);
7192  NON_CONST_ONLY
7193  MemoryOrderImmediate memory_order(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length,
7194  validate);
7195  if (!this->ok()) return 0;
7196  ArrayIndexImmediate imm(
7197  this, this->pc_ + opcode_length + memory_order.length, validate);
7198  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length + memory_order.length,
7199  imm)) {
7200  return 0;
7201  }
7202  if (!VALIDATE(imm.array_type->mutability())) {
7203  this->DecodeError("%s: Array type %d is immutable",
7204  WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode), imm.index.index);
7205  return 0;
7206  }
7207  ValueType element_type = imm.array_type->element_type();
7208  if (!VALIDATE(element_type == kWasmI32 || element_type == kWasmI64 ||
7209  IsSubtypeOf(element_type.AsNonShared(), kWasmEqRef,
7210  this->module_))) {
7211  this->DecodeError("%s: Array type %d has invalid type %s ",
7212  WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode), imm.index,
7213  element_type.name().c_str());
7214  return 0;
7215  }
7216  auto [array_obj, index, expected_value, new_value] =
7217  Pop(ValueType::RefNull(imm.heap_type()), kWasmI32, element_type,
7218  element_type);
7219  Value* result = Push(element_type);
7220  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(
7221  ArrayAtomicCompareExchange, opcode, array_obj, imm, index,
7222  expected_value, new_value, memory_order.order, result);
7223  return opcode_length + memory_order.length + imm.length;
7224  }
7225 
7226  default:
7227  // This path is only possible if we are validating.
7228  V8_ASSUME(ValidationTag::validate);
7229  this->DecodeError("invalid atomic opcode: 0x%x", opcode);
7230  return 0;
7231  }
7232 
7233  const uint32_t element_size_log2 =
7234  ElementSizeLog2Of(memtype.representation());
7235  MemoryAccessImmediate imm =
7236  MakeMemoryAccessImmediate(opcode_length, element_size_log2);
7237  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return false;
7238  if (!VALIDATE(imm.alignment == element_size_log2)) {
7239  this->DecodeError(this->pc_,
7240  "invalid alignment for atomic operation; expected "
7241  "alignment is %u, actual alignment is %u",
7242  element_size_log2, imm.alignment);
7243  }
7244 
7245  const FunctionSig* sig =
7246  WasmOpcodes::SignatureForAtomicOp(opcode, imm.memory->is_memory64());
7247  V8_ASSUME(sig != nullptr);
7248  PoppedArgVector args = PopArgs(sig);
7249  Value* result = sig->return_count() ? Push(sig->GetReturn()) : nullptr;
7250  if (V8_LIKELY(!CheckStaticallyOutOfBounds(imm.memory, memtype.MemSize(),
7251  imm.offset))) {
7252  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(AtomicOp, opcode, args.data(),
7253  sig->parameter_count(), imm, result);
7254  }
7255 
7256  return opcode_length + imm.length;
7257  }
7258 
7259 #undef NON_CONST_ONLY
7260 
7261  unsigned DecodeNumericOpcode(WasmOpcode opcode, uint32_t opcode_length) {
7262  // Fast check for out-of-range opcodes (only allow 0xfcXX).
7263  // This avoids a dynamic check in signature lookup, and might also help the
7264  // big switch below.
7265  if (!VALIDATE((opcode >> 8) == kNumericPrefix)) {
7266  this->DecodeError("invalid numeric opcode: 0x%x", opcode);
7267  return 0;
7268  }
7269 
7270  const FunctionSig* sig = WasmOpcodes::Signature(opcode);
7271  switch (opcode) {
7272  case kExprI32SConvertSatF32:
7273  case kExprI32UConvertSatF32:
7274  case kExprI32SConvertSatF64:
7275  case kExprI32UConvertSatF64:
7276  case kExprI64SConvertSatF32:
7277  case kExprI64UConvertSatF32:
7278  case kExprI64SConvertSatF64:
7279  case kExprI64UConvertSatF64: {
7280  BuildSimpleOperator(opcode, sig);
7281  return opcode_length;
7282  }
7283  case kExprMemoryInit: {
7284  MemoryInitImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
7285  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
7286  ValueType mem_type = MemoryAddressType(imm.memory.memory);
7287  auto [dst, offset, size] = Pop(mem_type, kWasmI32, kWasmI32);
7288  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(MemoryInit, imm, dst, offset, size);
7289  return opcode_length + imm.length;
7290  }
7291  case kExprDataDrop: {
7292  IndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length,
7293  "data segment index", validate);
7294  if (!this->ValidateDataSegment(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) {
7295  return 0;
7296  }
7297  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(DataDrop, imm);
7298  return opcode_length + imm.length;
7299  }
7300  case kExprMemoryCopy: {
7301  MemoryCopyImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
7302  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
7303  ValueType dst_type = MemoryAddressType(imm.memory_dst.memory);
7304  ValueType src_type = MemoryAddressType(imm.memory_src.memory);
7305  // size_type = min(dst_type, src_type), where kI32 < kI64.
7306  ValueType size_type = dst_type == kWasmI32 ? kWasmI32 : src_type;
7307 
7308  auto [dst, src, size] = Pop(dst_type, src_type, size_type);
7309  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(MemoryCopy, imm, dst, src, size);
7310  return opcode_length + imm.length;
7311  }
7312  case kExprMemoryFill: {
7313  MemoryIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
7314  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
7315  ValueType mem_type = MemoryAddressType(imm.memory);
7316  auto [dst, value, size] = Pop(mem_type, kWasmI32, mem_type);
7317  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(MemoryFill, imm, dst, value, size);
7318  return opcode_length + imm.length;
7319  }
7320  case kExprTableInit: {
7321  TableInitImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
7322  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
7323  ValueType table_address_type = TableAddressType(imm.table.table);
7324  auto [dst, src, size] = Pop(table_address_type, kWasmI32, kWasmI32);
7325  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(TableInit, imm, dst, src, size);
7326  return opcode_length + imm.length;
7327  }
7328  case kExprElemDrop: {
7329  IndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length,
7330  "element segment index", validate);
7331  if (!this->ValidateElementSegment(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) {
7332  return 0;
7333  }
7334  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(ElemDrop, imm);
7335  return opcode_length + imm.length;
7336  }
7337  case kExprTableCopy: {
7338  TableCopyImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
7339  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
7340  ValueType dst_type = TableAddressType(imm.table_dst.table);
7341  ValueType src_type = TableAddressType(imm.table_src.table);
7342  // size_type = min(dst_type, src_type), where kI32 < kI64.
7343  ValueType size_type = dst_type == kWasmI32 ? kWasmI32 : src_type;
7344 
7345  auto [dst, src, size] = Pop(dst_type, src_type, size_type);
7346  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(TableCopy, imm, dst, src, size);
7347  return opcode_length + imm.length;
7348  }
7349  case kExprTableGrow: {
7350  TableIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
7351  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
7352  ValueType table_address_type = TableAddressType(imm.table);
7353  auto [value, delta] = Pop(imm.table->type, table_address_type);
7354  Value* result = Push(table_address_type);
7355  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(TableGrow, imm, value, delta,
7356  result);
7357  return opcode_length + imm.length;
7358  }
7359  case kExprTableSize: {
7360  TableIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
7361  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
7362  Value* result = Push(TableAddressType(imm.table));
7363  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(TableSize, imm, result);
7364  return opcode_length + imm.length;
7365  }
7366  case kExprTableFill: {
7367  TableIndexImmediate imm(this, this->pc_ + opcode_length, validate);
7368  if (!this->Validate(this->pc_ + opcode_length, imm)) return 0;
7369  ValueType table_address_type = TableAddressType(imm.table);
7370  auto [start, value, count] =
7371  Pop(table_address_type, imm.table->type, table_address_type);
7372  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(TableFill, imm, start, value, count);
7373  return opcode_length + imm.length;
7374  }
7375  case kExprF32LoadMemF16: {
7376  if (!this->enabled_.has_fp16()) {
7377  this->DecodeError(
7378  "invalid numeric opcode: 0x%x, "
7379  "enable with --experimental-wasm-fp16",
7380  opcode);
7381  return 0;
7382  }
7383  return DecodeLoadMem(LoadType::kF32LoadF16, 2);
7384  }
7385  case kExprF32StoreMemF16: {
7386  if (!this->enabled_.has_fp16()) {
7387  this->DecodeError(
7388  "invalid numeric opcode: 0x%x, "
7389  "enable with --experimental-wasm-fp16",
7390  opcode);
7391  return 0;
7392  }
7393  return DecodeStoreMem(StoreType::kF32StoreF16, 2);
7394  }
7395  default:
7396  this->DecodeError("invalid numeric opcode: 0x%x", opcode);
7397  return 0;
7398  }
7399  }
7400 
7401  unsigned DecodeAsmJsOpcode(WasmOpcode opcode, uint32_t opcode_length) {
7402  if ((opcode >> 8) != kAsmJsPrefix) {
7403  this->DecodeError("Invalid opcode: 0x%x", opcode);
7404  return 0;
7405  }
7406 
7407  switch (opcode) {
7408 #define ASMJS_CASE(Op, ...) case kExpr##Op:
7409  FOREACH_ASMJS_COMPAT_OPCODE(ASMJS_CASE)
7410 #undef ASMJS_CASE
7411  {
7412  // Deal with special asmjs opcodes.
7413  if (!VALIDATE(is_asmjs_module(this->module_)))
7414  break;
7415  const FunctionSig* asmJsSig = WasmOpcodes::AsmjsSignature(opcode);
7416  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(asmJsSig);
7417  BuildSimpleOperator(opcode, asmJsSig);
7418  return opcode_length;
7419  }
7420  default:
7421  break;
7422  }
7423  this->DecodeError("Invalid opcode: 0x%x", opcode);
7424  return 0;
7425  }
7426 
7427  V8_INLINE Value CreateValue(ValueType type) { return Value{this->pc_, type}; }
7428 
7429  V8_INLINE Value* Push(Value value) {
7430  DCHECK_IMPLIES(this->ok(), value.type != kWasmVoid);
7431  if (!VALIDATE(!this->is_shared_ || value.type.is_shared())) {
7432  this->DecodeError(value.pc(), "%s does not have a shared type",
7433  SafeOpcodeNameAt(value.pc()));
7434  return nullptr;
7435  }
7436  // {stack_.EnsureMoreCapacity} should have been called before, either in the
7437  // central decoding loop, or individually if more than one element is
7438  // pushed.
7439  stack_.push(value);
7440  return &stack_.back();
7441  }
7442 
7443  V8_INLINE Value* Push(ValueType type) { return Push(CreateValue(type)); }
7444 
7445  void PushMergeValues(Control* c, Merge<Value>* merge) {
7446  if constexpr (decoding_mode == kConstantExpression) return;
7447  DCHECK_EQ(c, &control_.back());
7448  DCHECK(merge == &c->start_merge || merge == &c->end_merge);
7449  stack_.shrink_to(c->stack_depth);
7450  if (merge->arity == 1) {
7451  // {stack_.EnsureMoreCapacity} should have been called before in the
7452  // central decoding loop.
7453  Push(merge->vals.first);
7454  } else {
7455  stack_.EnsureMoreCapacity(merge->arity, this->zone_);
7456  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < merge->arity; i++) {
7457  Push(merge->vals.array[i]);
7458  }
7459  }
7460  DCHECK_EQ(c->stack_depth + merge->arity, stack_.size());
7461  }
7462 
7463  V8_INLINE void PushReturns(ReturnVector values) {
7464  stack_.EnsureMoreCapacity(static_cast<int>(values.size()), this->zone_);
7465  for (Value& value : values) Push(value);
7466  }
7467 
7468  Value* PushValueTypes(const base::Vector<const ValueType> types) {
7469  size_t count = types.size();
7470  stack_.EnsureMoreCapacity(static_cast<int>(count), this->zone_);
7471  for (size_t i = 0; i < count; ++i) {
7472  Push(types[i]);
7473  }
7474  return stack_.end() - count;
7475  }
7476 
7477  Value* PushParameters(const FunctionSig* sig) {
7478  return PushValueTypes(sig->parameters());
7479  }
7480 
7481  Value* PushReturns(const FunctionSig* sig) {
7482  return PushValueTypes(sig->returns());
7483  }
7484 
7485  // We do not inline these functions because doing so causes a large binary
7486  // size increase. Not inlining them should not create a performance
7487  // degradation, because their invocations are guarded by V8_LIKELY.
7488  V8_NOINLINE V8_PRESERVE_MOST void PopTypeError(int index, Value val,
7489  const char* expected) {
7490  this->DecodeError(val.pc(), "%s[%d] expected %s, found %s of type %s",
7491  SafeOpcodeNameAt(this->pc_), index, expected,
7492  SafeOpcodeNameAt(val.pc()), val.type.name().c_str());
7493  }
7494 
7495  V8_NOINLINE V8_PRESERVE_MOST void PopTypeError(int index, Value val,
7496  std::string expected) {
7497  PopTypeError(index, val, expected.c_str());
7498  }
7499 
7500  V8_NOINLINE V8_PRESERVE_MOST void PopTypeError(int index, Value val,
7501  ValueType expected) {
7502  PopTypeError(index, val, ("type " + expected.name()).c_str());
7503  }

7505  V8_NOINLINE V8_PRESERVE_MOST void NotEnoughArgumentsError(int needed,
7506  int actual) {
7507  DCHECK_LT(0, needed);
7508  DCHECK_LE(0, actual);
7509  DCHECK_LT(actual, needed);
7510  this->DecodeError(
7511  "not enough arguments on the stack for %s (need %d, got %d)",
7512  SafeOpcodeNameAt(this->pc_), needed, actual);
7513  }
7514 
7515  V8_INLINE Value Pop(int index, ValueType expected) {
7516  Value value = Pop();
7517  ValidateStackValue(index, value, expected);
7518  return value;
7519  }
7520 
7521  V8_INLINE void ValidateStackValue(int index, Value value,
7522  ValueType expected) {
7523  if (!VALIDATE(IsSubtypeOf(value.type, expected, this->module_) ||
7524  value.type == kWasmBottom || expected == kWasmBottom)) {
7525  PopTypeError(index, value, expected);
7526  }
7527  }
7528 
7529  V8_INLINE Value Pop() {
7530  DCHECK(!control_.empty());
7531  uint32_t limit = control_.back().stack_depth;
7532  if (V8_UNLIKELY(stack_size() <= limit)) {
7533  // Popping past the current control start in reachable code.
7534  if (!VALIDATE(control_.back().unreachable())) {
7535  NotEnoughArgumentsError(1, 0);
7536  }
7537  return UnreachableValue(this->pc_);
7538  }
7539  Value top_of_stack = stack_.back();
7540  stack_.pop();
7541  return top_of_stack;
7542  }
7543 
7544  V8_INLINE Value Peek(int depth, int index, ValueType expected) {
7545  Value value = Peek(depth);
7546  ValidateStackValue(index, value, expected);
7547  return value;
7548  }
7549 
7550  V8_INLINE Value Peek(int depth = 0) {
7551  DCHECK(!control_.empty());
7552  uint32_t limit = control_.back().stack_depth;
7553  if (V8_UNLIKELY(stack_.size() <= limit + depth)) {
7554  // Peeking past the current control start in reachable code.
7555  if (!VALIDATE(decoding_mode == kFunctionBody &&
7556  control_.back().unreachable())) {
7557  NotEnoughArgumentsError(depth + 1, stack_.size() - limit);
7558  }
7559  return UnreachableValue(this->pc_);
7560  }
7561  DCHECK_LT(depth, stack_.size());
7562  return *(stack_.end() - depth - 1);
7563  }
7564 
7565  V8_INLINE Value Peek(ValueType expected) { return Peek(0, 0, expected); }
7566 
7567  // Pop multiple values at once; faster than multiple individual {Pop}s.
7568  // Returns an array of the popped values if there are multiple, or the popped
7569  // value itself if a single type is passed.
7570  template <typename... ValueTypes>
7571  // Pop is only allowed to be called with ValueType parameters.
7572  requires((std::is_same_v<ValueType, ValueTypes> ||
7573  std::is_base_of_v<IndependentValueType, ValueTypes>) &&
7574  ...)
7575  V8_INLINE std::conditional_t<sizeof...(ValueTypes) == 1, Value,
7576  std::array<Value, sizeof...(ValueTypes)>>
7577  Pop(ValueTypes... expected_types) {
7578  constexpr int kCount = sizeof...(ValueTypes);
7579  EnsureStackArguments(kCount);
7580  DCHECK_LE(control_.back().stack_depth, stack_size());
7581  DCHECK_GE(stack_size() - control_.back().stack_depth, kCount);
7582  // Note: Popping from the {FastZoneVector} does not invalidate the old (now
7583  // out-of-range) elements.
7584  stack_.pop(kCount);
7585  auto ValidateAndGetNextArg = [this, i = 0](ValueType type) mutable {
7586  ValidateStackValue(i, stack_.end()[i], type);
7587  return stack_.end()[i++];
7588  };
7589  return {ValidateAndGetNextArg(expected_types)...};
7590  }
7591 
7592  Value PopPackedArray(uint32_t operand_index, ValueType expected_element_type,
7593  WasmArrayAccess access) {
7594  Value array = Pop();
7595  if (array.type.is_bottom()) {
7596  // We are in a polymorphic stack. Leave the stack as it is.
7597  DCHECK(!current_code_reachable_and_ok_);
7598  return array;
7599  }
7600  // Inputs of type "none" are okay due to implicit upcasting. The stringref
7601  // spec doesn't say this explicitly yet, but it's consistent with the rest
7602  // of Wasm. (Of course such inputs will trap at runtime.) See:
7603  // https://github.com/WebAssembly/stringref/issues/66
7604  if (array.type.is_reference_to(HeapType::kNone)) return array;
7605  if (VALIDATE(array.type.is_object_reference() && array.type.has_index())) {
7606  ModuleTypeIndex ref_index = array.type.ref_index();
7607  if (VALIDATE(this->module_->has_array(ref_index))) {
7608  const ArrayType* array_type = this->module_->array_type(ref_index);
7609  if (VALIDATE(array_type->element_type() == expected_element_type &&
7610  (access == WasmArrayAccess::kRead ||
7611  array_type->mutability()))) {
7612  return array;
7613  }
7614  }
7615  }
7616  PopTypeError(operand_index, array,
7617  (std::string("array of ") +
7618  (access == WasmArrayAccess::kWrite ? "mutable " : "") +
7619  expected_element_type.name())
7620  .c_str());
7621  return array;
7622  }
7623 
7624  // Drop the top {count} stack elements, or all of them if less than {count}
7625  // are present.
7626  V8_INLINE void Drop(int count = 1) {
7627  DCHECK(!control_.empty());
7628  uint32_t limit = control_.back().stack_depth;
7629  if (V8_UNLIKELY(stack_.size() < limit + count)) {
7630  // Pop what we can.
7631  count = std::min(count, static_cast<int>(stack_.size() - limit));
7632  }
7633  stack_.pop(count);
7634  }
7635  // Drop the top stack element if present. Takes a Value input for more
7636  // descriptive call sites.
7637  V8_INLINE void Drop(const Value& /* unused */) { Drop(1); }
7638 
7639  enum StackElementsCountMode : bool {
7640  kNonStrictCounting = false,
7641  kStrictCounting = true
7642  };
7643 
7644  enum MergeType {
7645  kBranchMerge,
7646  kReturnMerge,
7647  kFallthroughMerge,
7648  kInitExprMerge
7649  };
7650 
7651  enum class PushBranchValues : bool {
7652  kNo = false,
7653  kYes = true,
7654  };
7655  enum class RewriteStackTypes : bool {
7656  kNo = false,
7657  kYes = true,
7658  };
7659 
7660  // - If the current code is reachable, check if the current stack values are
7661  // compatible with {merge} based on their number and types. If
7662  // {strict_count}, check that #(stack elements) == {merge->arity}, otherwise
7663  // #(stack elements) >= {merge->arity}.
7664  // - If the current code is unreachable, check if any values that may exist on
7665  // top of the stack are compatible with {merge}. If {push_branch_values},
7666  // push back to the stack values based on the type of {merge} (this is
7667  // needed for conditional branches due to their typing rules, and
7668  // fallthroughs so that the outer control finds the expected values on the
7669  // stack). TODO(manoskouk): We expect the unreachable-code behavior to
7670  // change, either due to relaxation of dead code verification, or the
7671  // introduction of subtyping.
7672  template <StackElementsCountMode strict_count,
7673  PushBranchValues push_branch_values, MergeType merge_type,
7674  RewriteStackTypes rewrite_types>
7675  V8_INLINE bool TypeCheckStackAgainstMerge(Merge<Value>* merge) {
7676  uint32_t arity = merge->arity;
7677  uint32_t actual = stack_.size() - control_.back().stack_depth;
7678  // Handle trivial cases first. Arity 0 is the most common case.
7679  if (arity == 0 && (!strict_count || actual == 0)) return true;
7680  // Arity 1 is still common enough that we handle it separately (only doing
7681  // the most basic subtype check).
7682  if (arity == 1 && (strict_count ? actual == arity : actual >= arity)) {
7683  if (stack_.back().type == merge->vals.first.type) return true;
7684  }
7685  return TypeCheckStackAgainstMerge_Slow<strict_count, push_branch_values,
7686  merge_type, rewrite_types>(merge);
7687  }
7688 
7689  // Slow path for {TypeCheckStackAgainstMerge}.
7690  template <StackElementsCountMode strict_count,
7691  PushBranchValues push_branch_values, MergeType merge_type,
7692  RewriteStackTypes rewrite_types>
7693  V8_PRESERVE_MOST V8_NOINLINE bool TypeCheckStackAgainstMerge_Slow(
7694  Merge<Value>* merge) {
7695  constexpr const char* merge_description =
7696  merge_type == kBranchMerge ? "branch"
7697  : merge_type == kReturnMerge ? "return"
7698  : merge_type == kInitExprMerge ? "constant expression"
7699  : "fallthru";
7700  uint32_t arity = merge->arity;
7701  uint32_t actual = stack_.size() - control_.back().stack_depth;
7702  // Here we have to check for !unreachable(), because we need to typecheck as
7703  // if the current code is reachable even if it is spec-only reachable.
7704  if (V8_LIKELY(decoding_mode == kConstantExpression ||
7705  !control_.back().unreachable())) {
7706  if (V8_UNLIKELY(strict_count ? actual != arity : actual < arity)) {
7707  this->DecodeError("expected %u elements on the stack for %s, found %u",
7708  arity, merge_description, actual);
7709  return false;
7710  }
7711  // Typecheck the topmost {merge->arity} values on the stack.
7712  Value* stack_values = stack_.end() - arity;
7713  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < arity; ++i) {
7714  Value& val = stack_values[i];
7715  Value& old = (*merge)[i];
7716  if (!IsSubtypeOf(val.type, old.type, this->module_)) {
7717  this->DecodeError("type error in %s[%u] (expected %s, got %s)",
7718  merge_description, i, old.type.name().c_str(),
7719  val.type.name().c_str());
7720  return false;
7721  }
7722  if constexpr (static_cast<bool>(rewrite_types)) {
7723  // Upcast type on the stack to the target type of the label.
7724  val.type = old.type;
7725  }
7726  }
7727  return true;
7728  }
7729  // Unreachable code validation starts here.
7730  if (V8_UNLIKELY(strict_count && actual > arity)) {
7731  this->DecodeError("expected %u elements on the stack for %s, found %u",
7732  arity, merge_description, actual);
7733  return false;
7734  }
7735  // TODO(manoskouk): Use similar code as above if we keep unreachable checks.
7736  for (int i = arity - 1, depth = 0; i >= 0; --i, ++depth) {
7737  Peek(depth, i, (*merge)[i].type);
7738  }
7739  if constexpr (static_cast<bool>(push_branch_values)) {
7740  uint32_t inserted_value_count =
7741  static_cast<uint32_t>(EnsureStackArguments(arity));
7742  if (inserted_value_count > 0) {
7743  // stack_.EnsureMoreCapacity() may have inserted unreachable values into
7744  // the bottom of the stack. If so, mark them with the correct type. If
7745  // drop values were also inserted, disregard them, as they will be
7746  // dropped anyway.
7747  Value* stack_base = stack_value(arity);
7748  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < std::min(arity, inserted_value_count); i++) {
7749  if (stack_base[i].type == kWasmBottom) {
7750  stack_base[i].type = (*merge)[i].type;
7751  }
7752  }
7753  }
7754  }
7755  return VALIDATE(this->ok());
7756  }
7757 
7758  template <StackElementsCountMode strict_count, MergeType merge_type>
7759  bool DoReturn() {
7760  if (!VALIDATE(
7761  (TypeCheckStackAgainstMerge<strict_count, PushBranchValues::kNo,
7762  merge_type, RewriteStackTypes::kNo>(
7763  &control_.front().end_merge)))) {
7764  return false;
7765  }
7766  DCHECK_IMPLIES(current_code_reachable_and_ok_,
7767  stack_.size() >= this->sig_->return_count());
7768  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(DoReturn, 0);
7769  EndControl();
7770  return true;
7771  }
7772 
7773  int startrel(const uint8_t* ptr) {
7774  return static_cast<int>(ptr - this->start_);
7775  }
7776 
7777  void FallThrough() {
7778  Control* c = &control_.back();
7779  DCHECK_NE(c->kind, kControlLoop);
7780  if (!VALIDATE(TypeCheckFallThru())) return;
7781  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(FallThruTo, c);
7782  if (c->reachable()) c->end_merge.reached = true;
7783  }
7784 
7785  bool TypeCheckOneArmedIf(Control* c) {
7786  DCHECK(c->is_onearmed_if());
7787  if (c->end_merge.arity != c->start_merge.arity) {
7788  this->DecodeError(c->pc(),
7789  "start-arity and end-arity of one-armed if must match");
7790  return false;
7791  }
7792  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < c->start_merge.arity; ++i) {
7793  Value& start = c->start_merge[i];
7794  Value& end = c->end_merge[i];
7795  if (!IsSubtypeOf(start.type, end.type, this->module_)) {
7796  this->DecodeError("type error in merge[%u] (expected %s, got %s)", i,
7797  end.type.name().c_str(), start.type.name().c_str());
7798  return false;
7799  }
7800  }
7801  return true;
7802  }
7803 
7804  bool TypeCheckFallThru() {
7805  return TypeCheckStackAgainstMerge<kStrictCounting, PushBranchValues::kYes,
7806  kFallthroughMerge,
7807  RewriteStackTypes::kNo>(
7808  &control_.back().end_merge);
7809  }
7810 
7811  // If the current code is reachable, check if the current stack values are
7812  // compatible with a jump to {c}, based on their number and types.
7813  // Otherwise, we have a polymorphic stack: check if any values that may exist
7814  // on top of the stack are compatible with {c}. If {push_branch_values},
7815  // push back to the stack values based on the type of {c} (this is needed for
7816  // conditional branches due to their typing rules, and fallthroughs so that
7817  // the outer control finds enough values on the stack).
7818  template <PushBranchValues push_branch_values,
7819  RewriteStackTypes rewrite_types>
7820  bool TypeCheckBranch(Control* c) {
7821  return TypeCheckStackAgainstMerge<kNonStrictCounting, push_branch_values,
7822  kBranchMerge, rewrite_types>(
7823  c->br_merge());
7824  }
7825 
7826  void onFirstError() override {
7827  this->end_ = this->pc_; // Terminate decoding loop.
7828  this->current_code_reachable_and_ok_ = false;
7829  TRACE(" !%s\n", this->error_.message().c_str());
7830  // Cannot use CALL_INTERFACE_* macros because we emitted an error.
7831  interface().OnFirstError(this);
7832  }
7833 
7834  // There are currently no simple prototype operators.
7835  int BuildSimplePrototypeOperator(WasmOpcode opcode) {
7836  const FunctionSig* sig = WasmOpcodes::Signature(opcode);
7837  return BuildSimpleOperator(opcode, sig);
7838  }
7839 
7840  int BuildSimpleOperator(WasmOpcode opcode, const FunctionSig* sig) {
7841  DCHECK_GE(1, sig->return_count());
7842  if (sig->parameter_count() == 1) {
7843  // All current simple unary operators have exactly 1 return value.
7844  DCHECK_EQ(1, sig->return_count());
7845  return BuildSimpleOperator(opcode, sig->GetReturn(0), sig->GetParam(0));
7846  } else {
7847  DCHECK_EQ(2, sig->parameter_count());
7848  ValueType ret = sig->return_count() == 0 ? kWasmVoid : sig->GetReturn(0);
7849  return BuildSimpleOperator(opcode, ret, sig->GetParam(0),
7850  sig->GetParam(1));
7851  }
7852  }
7853 
7854  int BuildSimpleOperator(WasmOpcode opcode, ValueType return_type,
7855  ValueType arg_type) {
7856  DCHECK_NE(kWasmVoid, return_type);
7857  Value val = Pop(arg_type);
7858  Value* ret = Push(return_type);
7859  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(UnOp, opcode, val, ret);
7860  return 1;
7861  }
7862 
7863  int BuildSimpleOperator(WasmOpcode opcode, ValueType return_type,
7864  ValueType lhs_type, ValueType rhs_type) {
7865  auto [lval, rval] = Pop(lhs_type, rhs_type);
7866  Value* ret = return_type == kWasmVoid ? nullptr : Push(return_type);
7867  CALL_INTERFACE_IF_OK_AND_REACHABLE(BinOp, opcode, lval, rval, ret);
7868  return 1;
7869  }
7870 
7871 #define DEFINE_SIMPLE_SIG_OPERATOR(sig, ...) \
7872  int BuildSimpleOperator_##sig(WasmOpcode opcode) { \
7873  return BuildSimpleOperator(opcode, __VA_ARGS__); \
7874  }
7875  FOREACH_SIGNATURE(DEFINE_SIMPLE_SIG_OPERATOR)
7876 #undef DEFINE_SIMPLE_SIG_OPERATOR
7877 
7878  static constexpr ValidationTag validate = {};
7879 };

7881 class EmptyInterface {
7882  public:
7883  using ValidationTag = Decoder::FullValidationTag;
7884  static constexpr DecodingMode decoding_mode = kFunctionBody;
7885  static constexpr bool kUsesPoppedArgs = false;
7886  using Value = ValueBase<ValidationTag>;
7887  using Control = ControlBase<Value, ValidationTag>;
7888  using FullDecoder = WasmFullDecoder<ValidationTag, EmptyInterface>;
7889 
7890 #define DEFINE_EMPTY_CALLBACK(name, ...) \
7891  void name(FullDecoder* decoder, ##__VA_ARGS__) {}
7892  INTERFACE_FUNCTIONS(DEFINE_EMPTY_CALLBACK)
7893 #undef DEFINE_EMPTY_CALLBACK
7894 };
